title: flavorful onion soup
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over low heat; add onion. Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes or until onion is lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Add water, bouillon granules and Worcestershire sauce, stirring well.
Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Yields 4 servings at 3/4 cup each.
Calories:
Exchanges:
1 vegetable.

title: marinated brisket
directions: Marinate the brisket in the marinade in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Place brisket in a large pan with large piece of foil. Pour marinade over meat.
Seal foil edges together and bake at 250° for 4 hours.
Uncover and bake for 2 to 3 more hours.

title: yummy peanut butter balls
directions: In a large bowl, mix oats, peanut butter, milk, honey, vanilla, cinnamon and raisins.
Stir with wooden spoon until well blended.
Using your hands, form into small balls. Spread wheat germ on a plate and roll each ball in it.
Pour big glasses of milk for everyone. Roll balls right into your mouth.
Makes about 24 balls.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Skin potatoes while hot and mash.
Add all ingredients to potatoes.
Mix thoroughly and pour into a well-greased, 2-quart baking dish.

title: pineapple picnic salad
directions: In large bowl, gradually stir undrained crushed pineapple into the cream cheese.
Stir in the pudding mix.
Fold in chunk pineapple and Cool Whip.
Cover and chill.

title: soo-per salad
directions: Tear lettuce and place in bottom of bowl (use clear bowl as salad is colorful).
Put layers of celery, peppers, onion and peas.
Spread mayonnaise over peas.
Sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise.
Add eggs, cheese and bacon.
Cover lightly with Saran Wrap.
Store overnight in refrigerator.
Uncover; sprinkle with croutons.
To serve, toss or dig deep.

title: cracker jack
directions: Cook until very crisp, threads.
Then add 1/2 teaspoon butter and 1/8 teaspoon soda.
Put popcorn in syrup.

title: lemon treats
directions: Grease cookie sheet; heat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, whipped topping and egg in a large bowl.
Stir until well mixed. Drop by teaspoonful into powdered sugar; roll to coat.
Place cookie balls 1 1/2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until light golden brown.
Remove to cool.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit; pat dry.
Place in glass baking dish.
Add curry, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, then brown sugar.
Lightly mix.
Add butter by bits to top of fruit.
Cook 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Refrigerate overnight.
Reheat in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: lemony chicken(serves 4)
directions: Remove skin from chicken; pat dry.
Grate rind from 1 lemon; set aside.
Squeeze juice from this lemon over chicken.
Combine flour and paprika in shallow dish.
Turn each breast in flour to coat.
In skillet, saute chicken in hot oil until brown on all sides, approximately 10 minutes.
Mix reserved lemon rind, brown sugar and salt; sprinkle over chicken.
Add broth to skillet. Cook, covered, over low heat for 25 minutes.
Thinly slice second lemon; arrange over chicken.
Cook, covered, an additional 10 minutes or until fork-tender.

title: old fashioned baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in 9 cups water.
Cook beans in water until softened.
Drain and stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low setting for 6 to 12 hours (on high for 3 to 4 hours).
Yields 8 servings.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and onion.
Mix beans, hamburger, chilies and salsa; heat. Add cheese. Continue to heat until cheese is melted. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 5 hours at 275 degrees.

title: banana shake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Mix at high speed for 30 seconds.
Makes 1 shake.

title: grilled pizza sandwiches
directions: Butter one side of 2 slices of bread.
On unbuttered side, spread pizza sauce on each slice.
Top 1 slice with pepperoni (optional).
Sprinkle with shredded Mozzarella cheese on 1 slice. Cover with remaining slice of bread, butter side out.
Grill like a grilled cheese sandwich.

title: creamy pineapple mold
directions: Boil the crushed pineapple in juice and sugar; mix.
Add the unflavored gelatin and cold water to the boiled mixture.
Add the cream cheese.
Beat with beater.
Let cool in refrigerator until partially set.
Beat in the Cool Whip.
Top with nuts, if you wish.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and salt according to directions; do not overcook.
Drain well.
Add all other ingredients.
Chill.
Best if allowed to marinate for several hours or overnight.
Spaghetti will "swell up."

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces.
This will take about 3 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over wood burning fire for three and a half weeks at 525°.
If you expect more, the rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary, as most people do not like to find hare in their stew.

title: creamy peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and peanut butter with electric mixer until combined.
Add sugar, milk and vanilla; beat until combined.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon half of the cheese mixture in pie shell.
Spread with 1/2 cup fudge topping.
Place remaining cheese mixture in crust.
Cover and let freeze at least 6 hours or until firm.
Let pie stand at room temperature 15 minutes before serving.
Drizzle with topping and sprinkle with chopped peanuts, if desired.

title: charlene's shrimp macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well in large bowl.
Serve on top of lettuce.

title: easy does it peanut chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch oven dish.
Prepare cake batter per package directions, using eggs, water and oil.
Blend in peanut butter. Spoon 1/2 batter into baking pan.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup chocolate chips over batter.
Gently spread remaining batter and sprinkle remaining chips and peanuts. Bake 45 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean. Cool in pan. Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Make in layers.
Bake at 350° in uncovered casserole or pan for 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add one egg at a time.
Beat well after each one.
Add vanilla to milk and add alternately with dry ingredients which have been sifted together. Chill at least three hours or overnight.
Roll out and cut into various shapes.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: crispy pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in flour and beat until smooth.	Add extract.
Beat on medium speed of electric mixer for 10 to 15 minutes or until very fluffy.
Spoon into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: jello fruit mold
directions: Drain fruit; reserve 1 1/2 cups juice.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Add fruit juice.
Let stand for at least 1 1/2 hours in refrigerator to start to jell.
Whip in sour cream.
Fold in fruit.
Pour in mold.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter together, then add eggs, nutmeg and flour.
Beat until well mixed.
Form the dough into three 2-inch rolls and wrap in waxed paper.
Chill for 3 hours, then slice in 1/4-inch thick pieces and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Add chicken that has been cooked to mayonnaise, chestnuts, celery, mushroom soup and green beans. Saute onion and celery in margarine before adding other ingredients.
Stir together and put on simmer.

title: crab quiche
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, milk, green pepper, onion, crabmeat, Swiss cheese and flour.
Beat the eggs separately and add to mixture.
Pour into browned pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until firm.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into patties and fry in butter or margarine.
May be made ahead and frozen until needed.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine and add other ingredients.
Mix well and shape into balls.
Dip into chocolate made by melting 6 ounces chocolate bits and 3/4 block paraffin wax.
Drain, lay on wax paper and let cool.

title: "my favorite cake frosting"
directions: Cream well the sugar, shortening and butter or oleo.
When fluffy, add the scalded milk, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Add vanilla, if desired.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and rinse with warm water.
Put spaghetti in a bowl and put 1/2 pound shredded Mozzarella cheese on top.
Melt margarine; pour on top of Mozzarella cheese and spaghetti.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir and mix well. Brown hamburger and chopped onion; drain well.
Stir in can of spaghetti sauce until mixed well with hamburger mixture.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with margarine.
Layer 1/2 spaghetti mixture, Ricotta cheese and spaghetti sauce.
Repeat layer and top with remaining 4 ounces of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot cornbread
directions: Grease yo skillet 'r muffin tin 'r yo cornstick pan...git hot...then pore in mixture 'n bake fur an hour at 350°.

title: swiss cheese cloud
directions: Brown sausage, stirring to break up.
Drain.
Place bread in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Spread crumbled sausage over bread.
Top with cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, pepper, nutmeg, mustard and Worcestershire sauce and pour over casserole.
Let stand, covered, in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: horseradish cheese(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Mix together well and store in tightly covered jar or container.

title: cilantro pesto-curry shrimp with garlic beurre blanc
directions: Combine dry ingredients and process in processor gradually adding olive oil.

title: green or yellow split pea soup
directions: Wash peas, cut up all vegetables very fine.
Put into pot with water the peas and all vegetables.
Bring to a boil, lower flame. Cook 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
When almost cooked, add thyme.
When done, eat hearty.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add enough milk to make paste.
Add eggs; stir until mixed well.
Add remaining milk; stir well.
Cook until bubbly and thick.
Pour into pie shell.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Melt butter and cheese together.
Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well and pat into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix and pour over cake mixture the next 4 ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Blend cabbage, butter, cream of celery soup, milk and mayonnaise.
Top with crumbled corn flakes and grated cheese.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Sift flour and sugar together. Add oil, yeast mixture and mix well. Shape into rolls or roll out and cut. Let rise for one hour. Bake at 400° until brown. Makes 12 rolls.

title: spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bring water to boil.
Add cornmeal and salt slowly and cook, stirring 1 minute.
Beat in butter, eggs and milk until smooth.
Pour in casserole and bake 40 minutes until straw inserted in center comes out clean.

title: steak marinade italiano
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate steak (any beef) for at least 1 hour.
Heat remaining sauce to a boil.
Use to baste while meat cooks.

title: pecan squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 12 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sift sugar and flour together.
Cut in butter, using two knives or a pastry blender, until fine crumbs form.
Pat crust into the prepared baking pan.
Bake for 20 minutes; remove from oven.

title: cheese spread
directions: Blend all in a food processor.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook in crock-pot for 3 to 4 hours, until it falls apart.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in pan.
Sprinkle mixture made from remaining ingredients over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop the broccoli.
Add the onion (sliced thin), bacon, celery and carrots.
Add dressing of mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Can leave to stand overnight, covered.

title: rainbow pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini in water until tender (about 8 minutes).
Drain and cool in cold water until real cool.
Drain.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over rotini.
Stir now and then. Refrigerate.
I mix the ingredients while the rotini is cooking and cooling.
The big Tupperware marinade container is great to keep it in.
It's so handy to turn it over and shake gently to stir it.

title: beef and macaroni casserole
directions: Spray 2-quart baking dish with cooking spray.
Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Mix beef, milk, eggs, ketchup, onion and salt.
Set aside.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening.
Add brown sugar.
Mix well.
Allow to cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add dry ingredients, then nuts and bits. Pour into greased pan.
Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool. Slice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain.
Add 1/2 stick butter and Velveeta.
Stir until mixed.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.

title: tea cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well and set aside.
Combine flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add to butter mixture.
Stir well until blended.
Stir in vanilla.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Form 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar sprinkles.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Mix egg yolks and sugar; beat well.
Add chocolate, flour, margarine, milk and vanilla and cook until thickened.
Pour into cooked pie shells (2).

title: italian icebox cake
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with the Anisette Toasts, reserving one.
Pour flavored milk over each biscuit.
Set aside.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13 pan with Pam.
Roll crescent roll dough on bottom of pan, pinching together any seams in the dough.
Sprinkle cooked sausage and cheese over the dough.
In a bowl, mix together eggs, milk, and seasonings. Pour mixture over sausage and cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: cornish hens
directions: Place hens, breast side down in a heavy plastic bag.
Mix marinade and pour over hens.
Seal and marinate 8 hours in refrigerator, turning occasionally.
Remove hens from marinade. Bring marinade to a boil and set aside.
Place hens breast side up in a lightly greased 13 x 9 pan.
Bake uncovered at 450° for 15 minutes, then lower temperature to 400° for 1 hour or until golden brown and tender.
Baste with marinade or butter every 15 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown and crumble sausage in frying pan.
Press crescent rolls onto greased pizza pan for crust.
Sprinkle sausage and the potatoes on top of crust.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour evenly over pizza.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Serves 8.

title: hot fudge pudding cake(serves 6)
directions: Mix Bisquick, 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons cocoa in greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Stir in milk and vanilla until well blended.
Sprinkle evenly with remaining 1/3 cup cocoa and 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour on water.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes or until top is firm.
Dust with confectioners sugar. Serve at once in dessert bowls with sauce spooned over cake.

title: old fashioned apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine together the first 7 ingredients.
Fill a 9-inch pie crust with the mixture.
Cut the butter into pieces and place on top of apple mixture.
Put 2nd pie crust on top.
Rub top crust with a little milk (this will make it crusty and brown).
Sprinkle a teaspoon of sugar on top crust. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Add sugar to apples and let set for 10 or 15 minutes.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Bake in 350° oven 35 minutes or until done.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Mix butter, sugar and salt until light.
Add rest of ingredients and beat thoroughly.
Put in muffin tins.
May sprinkle top with sugar and nutmeg or fold in blueberries or bake plain.
Bake at 400° for 15 plus minutes, until slightly brown. Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: fiesta fish and shells
directions: Allow unwrapped frozen fish to stand at room temperature about 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook macaroni according to package directions; drain thoroughly.
In medium saucepan stir together undrained tomatoes, onion and taco seasoning mix.
Add macaroni and green pepper strips; bring mixture just to boiling.
Pour tomato-macaroni mixture into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Fold each fish portion as necessary to fit pan; place over the mixture. Spoon some of the sauce over fish.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Uncover; sprinkle cheese over fish.
Bake 5 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Add cream to sugar and syrup; cook 30 minutes in double boiler, stirring occasionally.
Add salt, butter and vanilla. Serve warm or cold.

title: dutch pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water using a large bowl.
Add flour and sugar and gradually pour in remaining water.
Knead dough until smooth and easy to handle.
Cover with damp cloth and allow to rise for 20 minutes at room temperature.
Separate into 12 balls.
Roll each and twist to shape pretzels.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Coat with beaten egg and sprinkle with salt to taste.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add sugars gradually and cream thoroughly.
Add beaten eggs and milk, mixing well.
Sift flour with soda and add to creamed mixture. Blend well.
Drop from teaspoon on greased baking sheets. Press cookies lightly with fork to flatten and make attractive ridged tops.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Spread broccoli on bottom of large casserole dish, then arrange chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix soup and mayonnaise together and spread over chicken, then sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine and combine with breadcrumbs.
Spread over cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes until cheese melts.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Bake pie shell at 325° for 20 minutes.
Saute vegetables in butter until crisp, but not soft.
Drain well and add seasonings. Place tomato slices in bottom of pie shell.
Add vegetables. Spread mayonnaise-cheese mixture over vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook hen until tender.
Cool, bone and chop.
Brown onion with flour in bacon drippings.
Add tomatoes, bell pepper, garlic and sugar.
Cook until thick.
Add tomato paste and chicken.
Mix in boiled spaghetti.
Let simmer.
Keep moist with chicken broth. Serve hot with cheese, if desired.
Mushrooms may be added to the sauce.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together and store in an airtight container.
Put 1 tablespoon in a cup of water or to taste.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in milk, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Place a 1-quart casserole in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in oven.
Pour custard in; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Pour boiling water in pan to depth of 1 inch.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes, or for 30 to 40 minutes in cups.

title: persian sweets
directions: Mix raisins, dates and nuts. Knead on breadboard dredged with powdered sugar.
When mixture is fairly stiff, roll to 1/2-inch thickness and cut in 1-inch lengths.
Roll each piece in powdered sugar and store in covered container.
This candy will keep for 3 weeks.

title: corn cake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, margarine and eggs.
Bake in greased pan at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: vichyssoise
directions: Combine onion, bouillon cubes, water and salt in large saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/2 c. milk.
Stir in potato buds and whip with fork until fluffy.
Gradually stir in 1 1/2 cup milk; heat just to boiling.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Just before serving stir in cream, beat vigorously with fork until well mixed.
Spoon into small cups or bowls.
Sprinkle with chives or watercress.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked tilapia with black beans
directions: Marinate Tilapia fillets in lime juice for 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In shallow 1 1/2 qt. baking dish mix together drained black beans, stewed tomatoes and 1 handful of chopped cilantro.
Remove fish from lime juice, blend lime juice into bean mixture and top with fillets.
Mix together 1 c. crushed tortilla chips and 2 Tbsp. melted butter until tortilla chips are moist. Mix in 1 handful chopped cilantro and press gently onto top of fillets.
Bake approximately 40 minutes or until fish flakes easily, then broil until topping is golden brown.

title: sour cream casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook hamburger and drain grease.
Cook noodles; set aside.
Stir tomato sauce into hamburger; simmer while preparing following:
In a bowl, add sour cream, cottage cheese and cut up green onion.
Mix well.

title: banana split salad(serves 6)
directions: Combine and refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight.
Just before serving, add 2 bananas and 1/4 cup crushed nuts.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Stir together sugar and flour.
Stir in 3 tablespoons pineapple juice.
Add pineapple and cheese.
Pour into greased dish and top with cracker crumbs and oleo mixed together.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes

title: sugar-free fudge
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate.
Stir in sweetener and vanilla. Combine chocolate mixture with cream cheese and beat until smooth. Stir in
nuts and spread mixture in lightly greased 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Yield: 64 squares.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Mix noodle soup, cream of mushroom soup, tuna and evaporated milk. Add Chinese noodles. Put in pan. Sprinkle chips over top. Bake at 350 degrees until it bubbles, about 20 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain broccoli and place in the bottom of an ungreased casserole.
Place sliced, cooked chicken over broccoli.
Combine the soup, no-fat sour cream and cheese in a saucepan.
Heat until cheese is melted and pour sauce over chicken; add lemon juice.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: freezer strawberry jam
directions: Prepare strawberries.
Drain and cut up.
Combine with sugar and stir well.
Set aside 10 minutes.
Stir pectin in water.
Bring to boil 1 minute.
Stir pectin mixture in strawberries.
Stir 3 minutes.
Ladle into plastic containers.
Seal at once.
Let stand 24 hours.
Store in freezer.

title: heavenly coconut cream cake
directions: Bake white cake in 9 x 13 pan as per directions. Mix condensed milk with cream of coconut; pour over warm cake which has been pierced with a fork. Cool in refrigerator. Frost with Cool Whip and coconut. Keep refrigerated.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup in a deep pan, boil until hard ball stage.
Slowly pour over the beaten egg whites.
Beat with electric mixer until it gets pretty thick and loses some of its gloss.
Sprinkle some powdered sugar on countertop and pour out candy.
Knead several times.
Roll out and spread peanut butter on it, roll it up and slice.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix first 8 ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan; top with crushed corn flakes and oleo mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cornmeal squares
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except the cheese and chilies.
Pour half of this mixture in 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch Pyrex dish. Put 1 1/2 cups of cheese and the can of green chilies over mixture.
Cover with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: party potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes about 30 minutes. Mix all other ingredients together well.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Sprinkle on crushed topping. Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Great for potluck.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and add grapes.
Cook pudding in fruit juice. Cool (this can be done the night before).
When ready to serve, add pecans and bananas.
Serves 25.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: saucy pork steaks
directions: Brown pork steaks in butter.
Add onion, green peppers, mushrooms and garlic salt.
Pour in spaghetti sauce.
Cover and simmer over medium heat for 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste. Remove from heat.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate pie(makes 2)
directions: Mix together sugar and cocoa.
Add flour; add milk and eggs. Slowly cook until full boil.
This will stick easily.
Use low heat.
Remove and add a chunk of butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shells.

title: gingerbread(serves 21)
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, gradually.
Beat in the egg, molasses and vinegar.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients, then chill.
Roll 1/8 to 1/4 of an inch thick on a floured surface.
Cut into desired shapes.

title: no-brown hamburger casserole(a meatloaf with macaroni and vegetables)
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put in 2 1/2 quart casserole. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar, add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Frost with vanilla frosting or leave plain.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Salt and pepper ground beef to taste; add onion and green pepper.
Press mixture into 10 x 10-inch baking dish.
Cover with soup; spread cheese over top.
Place potatoes to cover cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: armenian lamb shanks
directions: Trim shanks of excess fat.
Place in an 8-quart casserole.
Add the remaining ingredients except the garnish.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, until the lamb is tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Partially uncover pot for the last half hour.
Garnish with onion mixed with parsley.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Put brown sugar, oleo/butter, Karo and salt in 2-quart dish and bring to boil around 2 1/2 minutes.
Take out and stir.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Remove.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Put popped corn in brown grocery bag.
Pour syrup over corn.
Shake good.
Cook in bag on High in microwave 1/2 minute.
Remove and shake; cook another 1/2 minute on High.
Pour on waxed paper and cool.

title: easy chicken kiev
directions: Pound chicken until thin.
Place 1 teaspoon butter or margarine on each breast half.
Sprinkle with chives.
Roll as tightly as possible.
Dunk in gravy or spread with Miracle Whip. Mix equal amounts of crumbs and cheese.
Dredge chicken rolls. Bake in 450° oven for 25 minutes.
(Rolls may be drizzled with melted butter or margarine.)

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Fry in a large skillet and brown all sides.
Remove and place in shallow baking pan and arrange pieces to fit.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

Reheat oven to 350°. Drain pineapple juice in measuring cup and add water to make 1 1/4 cups of liquid. In medium saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, pineapple juice, vinegar, soy sauce, ginger and bouillon cube. Bring to a boil, stirring until smooth.
Boil 2 minutes; pour over chicken.
Add pineapple chunks and green pepper strips.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered, until tender.

title: brian's apple cinnamon rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Add cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Butter your fingers and press mixture evenly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into 2 x 2-inch squares when cool.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Cook these 3 ingredients together until smooth and creamy.

title: beau monde dip(double recipe)
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
One large loaf and 1 small loaf of marble bread (rye and pumpernickel) or plain rye.
Before serving, cut out large loaf leaving wall of approximately 1-inch and cut up in bite size pieces the portion that was removed.
Cut up about 1/2 of the small loaf in bite size pieces.
Fill center of large loaf with filling.
Place bite size pieces around loaf for dipping.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, Karo and water to thread stage; when you raise your stirring spoon, it strings down.
Pour in peanuts and stir and cook until peanuts are lightly brown; add butter.
Stir until melted and add soda.
Stir.
Pour while foaming into greased cookie sheet pan.
The sooner you pour after adding the soda, the more it foams.
Don't spread with spoon.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Beat
in
eggs.
Sift
together dry ingredients
and add to egg
mixture.
Fold
in
vanilla, apples and pecans.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch
pan
at 325° for 55 minutes. Cool and ice with Vanilla
Cream Cheese Icing.
Cake will keep moist and fresh for days.

title: oatmeal rocks
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: candy apple jelly (lite)
directions: Measure juice and cinnamon candies into saucepan.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar from measured amount and fruit pectin in small bowl. Stir mixture into juice in large pot.
Add margarine.
Bring mixture to full rolling boil on high, stirring constantly.
Stir in remaining sugar.
Return to full rolling boil and boil exactly 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; skim off any foam.
Fill jars to within 1/8-inch from top.
Wipe jars clean. Screw bands tightly.
Invert jars 5 minutes, then turn upright or follow water bath method.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs and all other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 50 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: easy apple dumpling
directions: Prepare apples.
Butter a deep pan.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar with cinnamon.
Roll apples in cinnamon sugar.
Place in pan.
Sprinkle remaining sugar mixture over apple slices.

title: walnut cake
directions: Beat ingredients 5 minutes.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: mother's poor man's pie
directions: Mix first five ingredients together; add enough water to make a nice, full pie.
Dot with butter.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until set.

title: ham-dill dip
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Serve in sour dough or pumpernickel bread by taking the insides of the bread out and using the bread parts for dipping.

title: self-crust turkey or chicken pie
directions: Place turkey or chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer egg slices on this. Blend broth and soup in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour broth and soup mixture over meat and egg slices. Mix margarine (melted), flour, milk and pepper and pour over ingredients in baking dish.
This mixture will not be smooth. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until crust is browned.
(You can add 1 can mixed vegetables, drained.)

title: gumbo
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Add sausage and cook 5 minutes or until browned on all sides.
Remove sausage and set aside.
Add chicken to skillet and cook 7 minutes on each side or until chicken is done.
Remove chicken from skillet and let cool, then shred chicken and set aside.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix together ingredients and marinate chicken all day.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Serve with rice.

title: cheesy chili cups
directions: Spray 2 sets miniature muffin tins with nonstick cooking spray.
With 3-inch cookie cutter, cut won ton skins into circles. Place one circle in each muffin cup, molding it to the cup. Spray lightly with additional nonstick cooking spray.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 7 to 8 minutes or until golden.
Remove from tins and place on cookie sheets.
In medium bowl, combine cheese, chilies, chives or green onions and cumin.
Mix well.
Fill each won ton cup with 2 teaspoons cheese filling.
Top with two olive slices.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 10 minutes or until bubbly. Serve warm.
Light recipe.

title: creamy broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli in saucepan until tender; drain.
Combine with cheese, mayo, onions and eggs in bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: chicken en cocotte(from 1975 edition)
directions: About 2 1/2 hours before serving, preheat oven to 375°. Remove giblets and neck from inside chicken.
Rinse chicken with water and drain well.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika.
Pull neck skin under back; lift wings and fold under back to secure neck skin.
Tie legs and tail together.
Place chicken in 6 or 7-quart Dutch oven or roasting pan.
Pour on undiluted chicken soup. Cover and bake for 45 minutes.

title: sausage and cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together well. Drop spoon-size balls onto cookie sheet.
Bake for about 12 minutes.

title: ripe tomato chow-chow
directions: Mix chopped vegetables, salt and sugar; simmer until it begins to
thicken.
Add
vinegar
and
spices;
cook until it becomes a thick sauce.
Pour
into hot jars and seal.
Process jars 10 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: fruit tea mix
directions: Combine in small bowl and store in jar with tight fitting lid.

title: *sally lunn - williamsburg
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube cake pan or a Bundt pan.
Heat the milk, shortening and 1/4 cup water until very warm, about 120°. Shortening does not need to melt.
Blend 1 1/3 cups flour, the sugar, salt and dry yeast in a large mixing bowl.
Blend warm liquids into flour mixture.
Beat with an electric mixer at medium speed for about 2 minutes, scraping the sides of the bowl occasionally.
Gradually add 2/3 cup of the remaining flour and the eggs; beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Add the remaining flour and mix well.
Batter will be thick, but not stiff.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Mix with other ingredients.
Reserve 1/2 cup cheese to sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven. I place foil over top of casserole to keep cheese from browning too fast.
Remove foil last 15 minutes of baking time.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tomato pie
directions: Pour mixture into 2 well-greased and sugared loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes before removing.

title: zucchini jelly
directions: Peel and grate zucchini.
Add sugar and pineapple.
Stir until mixture goes together.
Cook together.
Let boil until zucchini looks done, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add jello and stir good.
Add to jars while hot and seal.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Saute the onions and celery in butter.
Combine all ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Add butter to cracker crumbs until crust (top).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seven layer cookie
directions: Melt butter in an oblong pan.
Press in graham cracker crumbs, then start layering with chocolate chips, butterscotch, coconut and walnuts.
Pour Eagle Brand milk on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend by hand or mixer until creamy.
Refrigerate overnight for best results.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add oil, sugar and eggs; mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix into chocolate mixture.
Add nuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy holiday cherry salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.

title: oriental asparagus salad
directions: Cook asparagus in water 3 minutes.
Drain and cool.
In bowl, combine sugar, soy sauce and sesame oil.
Add asparagus; toss and chill 2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: crunchy cucumber pickles
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, turmeric, mustard seed and celery seed and bring to boil.
Drop in cucumbers and let come to a boil.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: old fashion apple pie
directions: Put all ingredients, but butter, in a large bowl and mix together.
Put in pie shell; put dots of butter on top of the apple mixture.
Add top pie crust and cut slits in it.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Take out of oven and cool.

title: striped delight
directions: Blend flour, nuts and oleo.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and cool.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: In a saucepan, bring to a boil 1 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon pepper, 1 tablespoon water, 3/4 cup white vinegar, 1/2 cup Wesson oil and 1 cup sugar.
Pour cooled mixture over vegetables and refrigerate 4 hours.

title: persian eggplant stew
directions: In a stew pot, brown meat well in a small amount of vegetable oil (including bone) with onions and garlic.
Add cinnamon, salt and pepper.
When ingredients are well brown, add 3 cups of water. Reduce heat and simmer over low heat for 1 hour or until meat can be cut with a fork and broth is reduced.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli fine, also stems after peeling.
Add onion, sunflower seeds, raisins and bacon.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together.
Pour over veggies.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients except pastry shell; mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and continue baking 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and garnish as desired.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and dry spinach.
Fry bacon and crumble.
Combine oil, vinegar, mustard, garlic and parsley.
Add salt and pepper.
Just before serving, toss all together.

title: mom marshall's baked sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat
oven	to
Boil
sweet	potatoes
until tender.
Peel the potatoes, slice each lengthwise and place in foil-lined	baking	dish.
Layer
the
potatoes
and dust each layer
with
salt,	brown sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Add the Karo syrup	to the top layer of potatoes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1
3/4 hours, or until syrupy.
Add marshmallows and place under broiler until brown.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Chop
chicken
and
mix
with
half
cheese, onions and olives.
Place 2 tablespoons
on tortilla shells.
Roll up and line in a pan, 13 x 9-inch or 15 x 10-inch Pyrex dish.

title: nachos
directions: Cook hamburger and onions until done.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning mix according to directions on package.
Warm beans in microwave until soft and pourable.
Layer dish on cookie sheet with tortilla chips, beans, hamburger and then add as much grated cheese as desired.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips together in a large saucepan and add other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 40 to 50.
Don't overbake.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together and put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown on top.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together and bake in preheated oven at 400°
for 45 minutes.

title: seven layer finger jello
directions: To each box of jello, add 1 cup boiling water and 1 package unflavored gelatin (in 3/4 cup water).

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix flour and margarine.
Add nuts and press into pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, 15 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Press cream cheese with sugar and fold into Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Spoon on pie filling; spread to edges.
Refrigerate overnight to let flavors blend.
Serves 10.

title: salsa fish
directions: Rinse and pat dry Fish.
Place fish in a glass casserole dish. Pour 1/2 to 3/4 of the Salsa Sauce covering the Fish.
Cover and bake at 350 for 30 minutes or until fish is done.

title: okra skillet
directions: Prepare 2 cups sliced okra in cornmeal, salt and pepper.
Coat okra in meal mixture.
Cut enough kernels from cooked corn to make a cup.
Cook and stir pork and onion in skillet until pork is golden.
Stir in okra.
Cook 3 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and corn.
Cover and simmer until corn is tender, 10 to 15 minutes. Stir in pepper.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and stir only until blended.
Drop by tablespoon into deep fat (350°) and fry for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain
on absorbent paper.
Makes 18 hush puppies.

title: tuna tempter
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter until crisp and tender, but not brown.
Blend in soup and milk.
Add tuna (drained) and pimento.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Roll mixture into balls in confectioners sugar while hot. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: mary floyd's chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil chicken until done, then debone the chicken.
Place chicken in glass casseorle dish.
Pour both soups over top of chicken.
You'll need to smooth it over the tops evenly.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating often.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Stir in vanilla. Bake in lightly greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Saute onions and celery in margarine and add to drained broccoli.
Add Cheez Whiz, undiluted soup and rice and stir together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and top with lightly buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: tiny meatballs
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine ingredients and blend well. Form into small balls, about 1-inch in diameter.
Arrange half the meatballs in a single layer in a microproof baking dish.
Cook, uncovered, on 90 (Saute) 5 to 6 minutes.
Place in chafing dish to keep hot.
Cook remaining meatballs and add to chafing dish. Serve hot.
Use toothpicks to spear meatballs and dunk in Curry Dipper.
These may be prepared in advance and reheated just before serving on High (Maximum power) 2 to 3 minutes.
Makes about 60 meatballs.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add onion.
Add egg, milk, then stir lightly.
Drop by spoon into deep fat 360 degrees.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger and onion in a skillet. Combine all ingredients in a very large container except for the stuffing mix and margarine; mix well.
Pour half of the mixture into each of 2 casserole dishes.
Cover with stuffing mix and margarine.
Freeze one casserole for later and bake the other at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Makes enough for 2 casseroles.

title: good cracker dip
directions: Saute pecans in butter.
Mix other ingredients together.
Top with pecans and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain peas and beans.
Marinate peas, beans, celery, onion and pepper in mixture of oil, sugar, salt and vinegar.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef, onion, Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, and garlic salt.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Cook on low.
Cook and drain macaroni.
Add cream cheese and sour cream to macaroni while hot.
Layer meat mixture, noodle mixture, ending with meat.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, stirring well. Drop mixture by tablespoonfuls into hot oil (375°). Cook until golden brown, turning once. Drain on paper towels; serve immediately. Yields 1 dozen fritters.

title: happy hamburger surprise
directions: Brown hamburger, drain.
Mix taco seasoning and 1/4 cup water. Turn down to simmer for 10 minutes.
Mash up nachos in your plate. Put cheese in microwave and heat until hot.
Spoon out hamburger over nachos and pour hot cheese on top.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Put into loaf pan or casserole dish. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: pizza pork chop
directions: Place pork chops in baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce over chops.
Add oregano and garlic.
Cover with aluminum foil and cook 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Fifteen minutes before removing from oven, place cheese slice on top of each chop.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine lightly.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Cover with more crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: green goddess vegetable dip
directions: Put in blender and then serve with your favorite vegetable.

title: soft gingerbread
directions: Mix all together and bake slowly.

title: old-fashioned potato bread
directions: *To make this bread in half the time, substitute 2 packages quick-rise active dry yeast for regular dry yeast.
Cut the rising times in half and bake as directed.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Mix and form ingredients into strawberries.
Green hull is sugar, milk and green food coloring.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Saute crackers in 1 stick margarine; set aside.
Mix slightly thawed potatoes and 1 stick melted butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add all remaining ingredients.
Top with crackers.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: clam dip
directions: Combine clams, onion and garlic on stove; simmer 15 minutes. Turn off heat.
Add butter, Tabasco, parsley, oregano and lemon juice and mix.
Add bread crumbs and pieces of white bread until it starts to firm up.
Layer, in large dish, clam dip and Swiss cheese, alternating layers.
Heat until bubbly.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Cut tips off wings.
Split in half.
Marinate in mixture overnight.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° and turn once.

title: herbed bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Combine vinegar, sugar and oil, and heat slightly to dissolve sugar. Cool. Add beans and herbs to vinegar mixture.
Marinate overnight.

title: cherry pie elegante
directions: Beat egg whites with vinegar and salt until foamy.
Add sugar gradually, beating until stiff.
Spread over bottom and sides of pie shell, sealing to edge.
Bake 10 to 20 minutes or until golden brown; cool.
Spoon pie filling over meringue.
Garnish with whipped cream just before serving.

title: cinnamon streusel cake
directions: Batter:
In a bowl, mix cake mix, pudding mix, oil, eggs and water, making sure not to overmix.

title: grandma's soup
directions: Brown hamburg in 8-quart kettle.
Drain off fat.
Add broth, onion soup mix and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Add vegetables.
Cook on low for 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni separately and add to the soup.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
May be frozen.

title: egg noodles
directions: Stir with fork.
Add flour to make stiff.
Roll out and dry, then cut in strips.

title: fudgy mint squares
directions: In microwave-safe bowl, melt 8 tablespoons butter and unsweetened chocolate; cool slightly. In mixing bowl, beat 2 eggs, sugar and vanilla. Add the chocolate mixture; mix until blended. Gradually beat in flour. Spread into 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15-20 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Beat egg in cup and then add enough water with egg to make 1 cup.
Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Add egg and water and mix together.
Makes enough pie dough for about four pies.	Easy to roll.

title: joe's fragrant vegetable stew
directions: In a pressure cooker, over moderate heat, cook the onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add the carrots, celery, butternut squash, acorn squash, potato and turnip.
Cook for a few minutes until just beginning to soften.
Toss in the turmeric, coriander, cumin and chili pepper.
Add the broth, tomatoes and zucchini. Seal pressure cooker and cook over high heat until steam flows steadily.
Turn heat down so that steam keeps a constant stream. Cook for 4 minutes.
Cool pressure cooker under running cold water and release steam.
Open cooker, return to stove, add chick peas and heat through.
Serve over rice, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for 2 minutes.
Grease Bundt pan and sprinkle sugar lightly in bottom of pan, and also on top of cake batter.
(It makes a light crunchy texture.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Pour into an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: orange sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes in skins.
Peel, quarter and arrange in casserole dish.
Stir 1/2 cup orange juice into cornstarch, stirring until smooth.
Heat rest of orange juice, butter, orange rind and sugar, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Pour in cornstarch, stirring until thickened.
Add a pinch of salt and food coloring.
Pour over sweet potatoes.

title: polish casserole
directions: In bottom of a 9-inch square baking dish, place a layer of potatoes.
Sprinkle lightly with flour, salt and pepper.
Place a layer of sausage and sprinkle with cheese.
Continue layering until pan is full (usually 3 layers).
Pour milk into dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes until potatoes are done.
Remove from oven and let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: sweet-sour chicken
directions: Combine dressing, dry onion soup mix and preserves.
Pour over chicken parts which have been placed skin side up in a large shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 10 minutes, basting occasionally with pan drippings.
Serve hot with plain or yellow rice and the sweet and sour sauce.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding together.
Fold in Cool Whip and remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: texas hash casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add chopped onions and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Put cake mix, shortening, egg and cold water into a bowl.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in nuts, candies, raisins or whatever fruit and flavoring is desired.
Drop by small spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: curried moroccan muffins
directions: Cut muffins in 4 pieces.
Mix ingredients and spread on muffins.
Bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: chicken delights
directions: Coat chicken with the lemon pepper (coat almost black) and garlic powder.
Coat real well (one side only).
Wrap with bacon. Brown in greased skillet (until bacon is crisp).
Put in greased baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Trim stem end on squash.
Boil until almost done.
While boiling, saute onions in butter.
Crumble corn bread crumbs in onions.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Drain squash; cool slightly.
Cut in half.
Scoop out centers.
Mix squash centers with corn bread mixture.
Place squash halves in pan.
Place thin slice of Cheddar cheese in squash boat; add corn bread mixture. Brown in oven at 375°.
Remove, add another slice of cheese on top and broil until cheese melts.
Enjoy!

title: tiny jelly rolls
directions: Beat egg whites stiff but not dry.
Gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar, blending well.
Beat egg yolks, water and vanilla together until thick.
Slowly blend in remaining 1/2 cup sugar.

title: neva's chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Arrange in an 11 x 7-inch
pan. Place chicken on broccoli.
Mix soup, mayo, curry powder and lemon juice and pour over chicken and broccoli.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter and top mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pea salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine beans, cucumber, tomatoes, onion, basil and parsley.
Add vinegar and olive oil and salt and pepper to taste.
Toss to blend.
Let stand 1 hour.

title: rice almondine
directions: Cook and stir onion in hot margarine until tender.
Add broth, lemon juice and garlic powder.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice. Return to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in green beans, almonds and dill; cover. Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate lush dessert
directions: Mix and press the first 4 ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into mold and freeze.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Gently mix together with cream-style corn.
Pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon mashed potatoes atop meat mixture. Top with pats of butter or margarine.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 more minutes, uncovered.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve immediately.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon and onion.
Place in casserole or baking dish.
Mixture should be soupy.
Cover mixture with onion slices, then with bacon.
Bake at 300° uncovered for 1 hour.
Cut off heat and leave for another hour.

title: baked stuffed quahogs(ko-hogs)
directions: Wash and rinse clams.
Steam in 1 inch boiling water 8 minutes or until all are open.
Remove meat; mince coarsely and set aside. Retain water and shells.
Make stuffing according to instructions, except substitute clam juice for water.
Add 1 tablespoon Durkee's hot sauce, dash of sage and 1 tablespoon sherry.
If using some bought clams and juice, add at this time.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: pancake syrup
directions: Mix ingredients together; heat and serve over pancakes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar and butter.
Chill.
Roll into small balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate.

title: baked corn bread casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together; pour into large greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more, until knife comes out clean.

title: vegetable broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
and
drain
packages
frozen chopped broccoli. Add oleo, eggs, cheese, mayonnaise, onions, mushroom soup and water chestnuts.
Put
in
casserole.
Top
with crushed Ritz crackers. Bake on 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sloppy weenies
directions: Slice beef wieners into narrow coins and saute.
Add Sloppy Joes mix and simmer until reduced.
Serve on a hamburger bun with a slice of cheese on top and pickles or/and onions on the side. Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In large bowl, gently fold all ingredients together.
Put in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
Add 3 1/2 ounce can French onion rings.
Bake another 5 minutes.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Wash peppers, remove stems and seeds and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sugar and milk.
Fold into Cool Whip, then fold in the cake pieces.
Spread entire mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with 1 can cherry pie filling and refrigerate overnight.

title: tuna log
directions: Mix well.
Roll in log shape, then roll in chopped nuts.

title: apple pirog
directions: Cook apples and water until soft in a tightly covered pot. Takes about 10 minutes.
Mash apples when they are soft.
Add sugar, cornstarch, salt, cinnamon and lemon juice to the apples. Beat the eggs slightly in a large bowl.
Add the apple mixture to the eggs.
Blend well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in the end comes out clear.

title: christmas snow salad
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water; set aside.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 cup.
Bring pineapple juice mixture to a boil; remove from heat and stir in softened gelatin.
Chill mixture until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Prepare whipped topping mix according to package directions, omitting vanilla.
Fold 1 cup topping into gelatin mixture (reserve remaining topping for other uses). Gently fold next 5 ingredients and pineapple into gelatin mixture. Pour into a lightly oiled 4-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on serving tray.
Garnish with additional cherries, if desired. Yields 8 servings.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper; brown both sides in oil.
Remove chops and drain on paper towels.
Reserve drippings in skillet.
Add onion to skillet; saute until tender.
Stir in rice, tomatoes, salt, sugar and mustard; add pork chops and bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer about 30 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: continental chicken
directions: Arrange dried beef on bottom of greased crock-pot.
Wrap each piece of deboned chicken with a strip of bacon and lay on top of the dried beef.
Mix the soup and sour cream together; pour over chicken.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours (high 3 to 5 hours). Serve over hot buttered noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana pie
directions: In a saucepan, dissolve cornstarch in water.
Stir in condensed milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Slice and arrange two bananas on bottom of pie shell.
Pour filling over this.
Cover and chill 4 hours.
Spread top with whipped cream and slice remaining bananas and garnish top of pie.

title: tater tots
directions: Layer in baking dish, Tater Tots on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rhonda's rice
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° in casserole until done (about 40 minutes).

title: martooni
directions: Combine lemon soda and grapefruit juice in a shaker with ice. Strain into a martini or cocktail glass.
(For an extra-dry drink, use 1 teaspoon grapefruit juice.)
Makes 1 serving.

title: braunschweiger spread
directions: Mix in blender.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours, then serve.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, confectioners sugar, nuts and oleo.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Beat rest of ingredients until smooth; place in 9 x 13 pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and cool.
Spread 1 can blueberry pie filling over baked mixture, then spread whipped cream with sugar added, on top of pie filling.
Chill for 2 hours; cut into squares and serve.
Very rich!

title: lo-cal veggie soup
directions: Put in big pot and simmer 20 minutes; contains 18 calories per cup.

title: cole slaw(serves 50)
directions: Sprinkle cabbage with seasonings and mix well.
Keep chilled. Combine milk, lemon juice or vinegar and onion.
Pour over cabbage before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of salted water.
Drain, mash, then add margarine. Add egg, milk and cheese to squash. Place all in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with crumbs or mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crumbs are browned and mixture bubbly.

title: grizzly bear casserole(north dakota dinner)
directions: Peel, slice and cook potatoes on top of stove until almost done.
Brown and drain ground beef (with onions if desired). Layer ingredients in casserole dish in this order:
potatoes, beef and corn.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes; top with grated cheese for last 10 minutes of baking.

title: weight watcher soup(one cup equals 30 calories)
directions: Combine and simmer 1 hour.

title: thundercake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and vanilla, one at a time. Blend yolks in.
Beat whites until stiff, then fold in.
Add water and tomatoes.
Sift together remaining ingredients.
Mix dry mixture into creamy mixture.
Bake in two greased and floured 8 1/2-inch round pans at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost with Chocolate Butter Frosting.
Top with strawberries.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Heat sauerkraut.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Heat through.
Cool. Add to celery, onion, carrots and peppers.
Mix well.
Let stand overnight before using.
Keep unused portion refrigerated.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla; beat 2 minutes.
Blend in pineapple, carrots and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: oriental tossed salad
directions: Break lettuce up in large bowl.
Add drained bean sprouts and water chestnuts and crumbled bacon.
Whip in blender oil, sugar, onion salt, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour dressing over lettuce.
Garnish with chopped eggs.

title: lemon pecan cake
directions: *Instead of raisins, can use another 1/2 pound each of cherries and pineapple.

title: vanilla granola
directions: Preheat the oven to 300°.
In a large bowl, place the first 4 ingredients; toss well.
Spread the granola onto a large cookie sheet; bake for 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in the coconut and vanilla seed.
Bake for another 20 to 25 minutes, until lightly browned.
Stir in the cherries and raisins.
Cool and store in an airtight container for up to 1 month.
Serves 10.

title: potato-broccoli frittata
directions: In large covered skillet over medium heat, cook potatoes in oil 10 minutes or until lightly browned and tender.
Add broccoli and green onions; cover and cook 5 minutes or until broccoli is crisp-tender.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Beat eggs with cheese and parsley.
Pour over potato mixture.

title: cold vegetable salad
directions: Mix all together and then chill 1 hour before serving.

title: roasted rosemary potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Quarter potatoes.
In large bowl combine potatoes, olive oil, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder and seasoned bread crumbs.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
With your fingers, toss until potatoes are well coated.
Place potatoes on baking sheet and roast until potatoes are golden brown and tender, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: 30-day fruited cake
directions: Use large bowl with tight fitting lid (like Tupperware).
Do not refrigerate during the 30 day process.
Stir with wooden spoon.

title: tasty hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Should have fairly thick consistency.
Drop by tablespoons into boiling Crisco and deep fry until golden brown and crispy.
Serve immediately.

title: black-eyed pea soup
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven, cook bacon until crisp; remove with slotted spoon and drain on paper towel.
Add celery, green pepper and onion to bacon drippings in saucepan; saute until soft, about 5 minutes.
Add beef broth, tomatoes with liquid, peas and bacon.
Bring just to boiling.
Lower heat and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 cups.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onions together; drain well.
Mix together ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lentils and cracked wheat(imjadarah)
directions: Wash lentils, then place in saucepan and cover with water. Boil 10-15 mins. till lentils soften.
Wash cracked wheat or rice. Add to lentil mixture.
Cook till water is almost absorbed.
In another saucepan, saute onion in oil.
Pour into completed lentil dish.
Serve with laban (yogurt).
Great Lenten dish.

title: basic fast sponge cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar; beat in 2 eggs until fluffy.
Fold in flour, salt, baking powder and vanilla.
Pout into buttered 7-inch round tin.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve plain or spread with raspberry jam and dust with powdered sugar, if you have a sweet tooth.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat, onion, garlic and green pepper; add beans, paste, seasonings and small amount of water.
Cover and simmer on low heat, gently until thick and onion and pepper are tender.

title: pull candy
directions: Cook at medium-high heat until it spins a thread. Pour into buttered plates.
Don't forget to put butter on your hands before pulling hot candy.

title: fluffy sponge cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°; have ready an ungreased 10-inch tube pan. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg yolks in small bowl until very thick and lemon colored.
Pour beaten egg yolks into large bowl and beat in sugar gradually.
Beat in dry ingredients alternately with water and flavorings.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in large bowl until stiff.
Fold egg yolk mixture into beaten whites.
Pour in pan.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes.

title: slop(a messy appetizer)
directions: Blend in blender or food processor by pulsing so there is a texture.
Add vinegar and oil to taste.
Serve with slices of French bread.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix pizza sauce, tomato sauce and sugar for sauce.
Cook noodles in boiling water.
Brown hamburger; add salt.
Drain noodles.
While still hot, add sauce, hamburger and 1/4 pound cheese.
Sprinkle 1/4 pound cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: venison casserole
directions: Dredge the steak in flour. Using the shortening in a hot skillet brown the meat. Salt and pepper to taste. It is not necessary to fully cook the meat at this point, just brown the coating. In a large casserole dish, layer the meat and potatoes and onions. Finish with meat on top Cover with water. Bake at 350 degrees for 2-3 hrs. The meat will be very tender.

title: orange-cinnamon carrot sticks
directions: Boil the orange juice, sugar, oil, rind, salt and cinnamon. Add carrots; bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 3 to 5 minutes or just until carrots are crisp-tender, turning carrots occasionally. Chill. Keeps up to 3 days.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well; stir in grated zucchini.
Sift flour with salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture and blend well.
Fold in nuts. Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans and bake in a preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: crab imperial
directions: Salt the crab meat.
Add the pimento and mayonnaise (good with or without).
Add white sauce to this.
Put into slightly buttered casserole.
Cover with bread crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.

title: polish pierogi
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Knead; let rest for 1/2 hour. Roll dough out and cut into squares.
Fill and fold diagonally; seal ends tightly.
Cook in boiling water in a medium or large pot, only 7 to 8 at a time, until they come to the top.
Cook for a few minutes, then drain.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook broccoli until barely tender.
Drain well.
Cool slightly. Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Cover and let chill overnight.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into crust. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 250° until done.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: In
a saucepan, combine all ingredients except the tea. Simmer 5
to
minutes.
Add tea bags;	let steep to taste. Serve hot or chill for iced tea.

title: baked custard
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Slowly stir in slightly cooled milk and vanilla.
Pour into 6 (5 ounce) baking cups or a 1-quart shallow baking dish.
Pour 1 inch of hot water into a larger baking pan and place custard filled dish(es) in water.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until a knife inserted in custard comes out clean.
Serve warm or chilled; either plain, with your favorite sauce or with fruit.
Serves 6.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and syrup, then salt and vanilla.
Add melted butter.
Place pecans on bottom of unbaked pie crust.
Add filling.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Nuts rise to the top to form crusted layer.

title: beef roulades
directions: Sprinkle steaks with salt, pepper and minced onion.
Spread prepared stuffing over steaks, evenly divided.
Roll up steaks, jelly roll style.
Wrap one bacon slice around each roulade and fasten with a toothpick.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: 20 minutes super supper
directions: Microwave ground beef and onion in a glass baking dish for 4 minutes or until cooked.
Drain grease.
Thaw broccoli and mix with ground and other ingredients.
Add 1 soup can of water to a glass dish.
Microwave these on medium for 8 to 10 minutes.
You need to stir mixture at least once while it is cooking.

title: easy broccoli soup
directions: Bring chicken broth and broccoli to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and cook until broccoli is tender, 6 to 8 minutes.

title: quick and easy pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well.
Add vanilla, lemon juice and lemon extract.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes.

title: pit stop chili
directions: Optional:
Two #300 cans pinto or black beans (rinse and drain before adding).

title: hot potato-eckerd salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine potatoes, sausage, eggs, green onion and relish.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Grease cookie sheet, do not flour it.
Spread coconut on pan. Mix chocolate chips, nuts and raisins in a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well and pour onto a cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 45 minutes.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: angel hair primavera
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add garlic and onion.
Saute until onion is translucent.
Add mushrooms; saute 2 minutes more. Add zucchini and herbs.
Saute 1 minute longer.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Bake cake; set aside.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Stir in berries.
Add milk, egg and butter.
Mix until just moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Spoon into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.

title: cheese pine cone
directions: Soften cheese in an aluminum bowl over boiling water until easy to mix.
Mix in the other ingredients (except almonds).
Add salt to taste.
Form mixture into the shape of a pine cone.
Layer surface with almonds to resemble a pine cone.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: oatmeal-granola cookies (1985)
directions: Blend margarine, sugar, water, vanilla and egg until creamy. Mix dry ingredients together; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir well.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool and serve.

title: french bread
directions: Mix 2 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast; add margarine. Gradually add water and beat about 2 minutes.
Add 1 cup flour; beat.
Stir in enough flour to make stiff dough; knead a few times.
Divide into 4 equal pieces.
Roll each piece into a 15-inch long loaf.
Place on greased baking sheet sprinkled with corn meal.
Brush with peanut oil.
Cover with plastic wrap and freeze until firm.
Remove from baking sheet and wrap each loaf with plastic wrap; may keep frozen up to 6 weeks.
Remove from freezer; place on ungreased baking sheets, corn meal side down. Let stand, covered with plastic wrap, at room temperature, about 1 1/2 hours.
Let rise until double, about 1 1/2 hours more.
Gently brush with combined egg white and cold water and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook the meat, onion and garlic until brown.
Add seasonings, tomato soup and tomato paste.

Simmer, covered, 10 minutes. Add cheese. Cook slowly until cheese melts, then stir in rice; cook. Cut peppers. Remove seeds and cook in boiling water (salted) for 3 minutes. Drain and cool on rack. Fill peppers with meat mixture. Freezes well.
When ready to serve, thaw peppers and cook partly thawed peppers in pan covered with foil at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: no fat mocha cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line bottom of 9-inch cake pan with 1 3/4-inch high sides with wax paper.
Spray pan and paper with Pam.

title: skinny gravy
directions: Remove roast or turkey from pan and put pan with drippings into freezer for 10 minutes or until fat in drippings have solidified.
Take pan from freezer and carefully remove fat. Throw away fat.
Put pan with defatted drippings on stove.
Add water and bouillon and cook over medium heat until bouillon dissolves. Add cornstarch mixture and stir until thickened and blended. Season with salt and pepper as desired.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; form into loaf.
Bake in moderate oven at 300° until brown.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix cheese with just enough milk to be ale to spread it on a plate.
Mix chili sauce and onion; spread over cream cheese. Sprinkle crab or shrimp on top.
Serve with crackers, Ritz type are best.

title: strawberry angel delight
directions: Break cake into walnut size pieces into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix instant pudding with milk.
Add ice cream; mix well.
Pour over cake chunks.
Blend Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Pour over cake and filling just before Jell-O jells.
Chill several hours.
After this has set up good, top with Cool Whip.
Chill at least 3 more hours before serving.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt. Blend and cool. Add beaten eggs. Sprinkle dry yeast into warm water. Stir until dissolved. Add to mixture. Add flour. Blend. Cover and place in refrigerator for at least 4 hours before making out.

title: meat cups
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Pat into muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can freeze in meal-size portions, tightly wrapped in plastic wrap.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Cook string beans according to directions and drain.
In casserole, combine beans, soup and 1/2 can onions; do not dilute soup. Top with remaining onions. Bake at 350° until bubbly and onions are golden brown.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Mix first five ingredients in bowl.
Mix last three ingredients into another bowl.
Pour liquid over slaw mix and chill for at least 12 hours.

title: oven herb chicken
directions: Combine envelope of onion salad dressing with 1/2 cup soft butter and paprika.
With spatula spread mixture over chicken pieces, then roll chicken in 1/2 cup fine bread crumbs.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in greased jelly roll pan, skin side up, at 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: centerpiece for table
directions: The
Herb-Ox
instant
broth
and
seasoning
comes
in chicken and beef flavors and has more taste than any other low sodium brand I have found.	It
can be used instead of salt in many dishes and you really can't tell there is no salt.

title: tomato soup cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, eggs and soup and mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 12 dozen cookies.

title: cheese twists
directions: In a bowl, mix flour, cheese and red pepper with a pastry blender or 2 knives.
Cut butter into flour mixture until it resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in mixture of egg yolk and water. Gather dough into a ball; dust with flour.
Wrap and refrigerate until firm.

title: raspberry-beet jelly
directions: Mix lemon juice, beet juice and Sure-Jell.
Bring to boil, then dissolve sugar and Jell-O into mixture.
Bring to hard boil and cook 5 minutes.
Skim top.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Line pan with peaches.
Pour batter over peaches and spread.
Mix 1 cup sugar with 1/2 cup water and pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine soups, soy and water chestnuts.
Add pepper.
Mix well with green beans.
Put 1/2 in 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Layer 1 can of onions and 1/2 of cheese; repeat.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Add condensed milk, cool whip, and crushed vanilla wafers.
Layer pan with crushed wafers.
Add bananas.
Add part of mixture.
Layer with vanilla wafers.
Add rest of mixture.
Top with crushed vanilla wafers.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook bacon, reserving 2 tablespoons grease and drain.
In casserole dish, combine corn, grease from bacon, sour cream and crumbled bacon.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Remove stems from spinach and tear into bite size pieces.
Mix with other ingredients.
When ready to serve, season with salt and pepper.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar to Italian dressing mix.
Bring to boil.
Pour over spinach and toss lightly.

title: beef barcelona
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown pot roast in 1/4 cup of the French dressing.
When roast is well browned, add remaining dressing and the water.
Cover and cook slowly about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Add the onions, olives and potatoes.
Cook another 45 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: easy caramel apples
directions: Pour caramel into a bowl.
Slice apples.
Dip apples in caramel and enjoy.

title: nippy dip
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Put into crock-pot.
Add other ingredients.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Serve over tortilla chips.

title: crispy oatmeal cookies(makes 4 to 5 dozen)
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Mix together last 4 ingredients.
Combine all ingredients together well.
Put large rounded teaspoonfuls of mixture on cookie sheet and press flat with a fork until thin.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 17 minutes, until edges are brown.
Remove and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Crisp and light.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, melt chocolate and butter;
cool slightly.
In medium bowl, with rotary beater, combine
eggs,
corn
syrup,
brown
sugar, molasses, bourbon and salt.
Beat
until
well mixed; stir in chocolate mixture
and chopped
pecans.
Pour
into prepared pie shell. Arrange pecan halves on top of pie.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until filling
is set
in
center
when pie is shaken gently. Cool completely on wire rack, about three hours.
Garnish with whipped cream and additional
pecan halves, if desired.
Makes 10 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour to make smooth paste.
Slowly add milk, stirring with slotted spoon constantly. Stir until mixture slightly thickens.
In Dutch oven layer, potatoes, onion, Spam and cheese, sprinkling each layer with salt and pepper.
Pour milk mixture over.
If mixture does not cover completely, pour in enough milk to cover.
Bake in a 350° oven until potatoes are tender, approximately 1 1/2 hours. Cover for 1 hour, then uncover for the last 1/2 hour.

title: chicken pie
directions: Combine chicken, broth, soup and vegetables.
Place in a large casserole dish.
Mix flour, butter and milk.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.

title: creme de menthe bars
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Beat together 2 cups 10x sugar, 1/2 cup margarine and 2 tablespoons creme de menthe liquor.
Spread on cool cake.
Melt 1 cup sweet morsels and 6 tablespoons margarine. Allow to cool.
Spread on top of creme de menthe mixture.

title: lil's nutritious sunflower cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Add bran, coconut, wheat germ and sunflower seeds. Drop by teaspoonful onto greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: hazel's squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender; drain off all liquid and mash a little.
Pour beaten eggs into milk; mix well.
Add to squash.
Add cheese; mix well.
Pour melted butter into crushed crackers.
Pour 1/2 of cracker crumbs into squash mixture.
Pour squash into a buttered casserole dish.
Add rest of crackers on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: vinegar cole slaw
directions: Chop onion and pepper and add to slaw mix. Pour oil and vinegar over mix. Sprinkle sugar over slaw. Chill 4 to 6 hours before serving.

title: spicy shrimp and rice
directions: Melt butter in skillet over medium-high heat.
