Saute onion, peppers, celery and garlic until tender. Combine oyster sauce, cornstarch, chicken broth, tomato paste, salt, cayenne pepper, ground pepper and brown sugar. Stir until well blended.
Pour into pan with vegetables.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Cook chicken and pull off bone.
Mix chicken broth and flour until thick.
Roll out thin on a floured cloth or aluminum foil; cut with a knife into strips.
Drop into remaining chicken broth on medium heat and cook until noodles are cooked thoroughly.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Melt butter.
Saute garlic for 2 minutes.
Add broth and tortellini.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Season with salt and pepper.
Simmer until pasta is just tender about 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, spinach and basil.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with fresh parmesan cheese and fresh basil.

title: wowie cake
directions: Put all dry ingredients in a baking pan.
Put rest in pan and stir with a fork, about 4 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef across the grain into very thin slices.
In skillet, over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook beef and onion until beef is no longer pink and onion is tender, stirring often. Set aside.
In same skillet, combine soup, sour cream and paprika. Return beef and onion to skillet.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Serve over noodles.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chinese cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage lengthwise.
Fry cabbage in oil; turn often and cook until tender.	Add chicken broth and cook for 5 minutes.
Add ham, mushrooms, salt, and peas.
Add cornstarch mixture and stir in slowly.	Add evaporated milk and butter.
Serve hot.
Serves 8.

title: pepsi pot roast
directions: Place beef roast in roasting pan with tight fitting cover. Pour Pepsi over roast.
Mix garlic and soups.
Spread soup mixture over roast.
Bake in 350° oven for 3 to 4 hours.
Recipe makes its own gravy.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dump undrained pineapple into pan.
Spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling and spread evenly.
Dump dry cake mix into cherry layer; sprinkle evenly over cherry mixture.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Put butter, cut in patties, over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or cooled like cake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook wild rice according to directions on package.
Combine mayo, water and cream of mushroom soup.
Add onion, water chestnuts and chicken.
Add rice last.
Heat in oven 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broiled banana chocolate pudding
directions: In medium mixing bowl combine milk and pudding mix and, using electric mixer at low speed, beat until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Into each of 4 flameproof 6-ounce custard cups pour 1/4 of the pudding.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 10 minutes (can be prepared up to a day in advance).
Arrange 1/4 of the banana slices over each portion of the pudding.
Sprinkle each with 1/2 teaspoon sugar.
Place custard cups on baking sheet; broil until sugar melts and is bubbly, about one minute (be careful not to burn).
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Layer in 8 x 10-inch pan, beginning with one-third of the sauce, one-half of the uncooked lasagna, 1 cup cottage cheese and one-half of the Mozzarella and sour cream.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
May be refrigerated or frozen at this point.
To cook, cover casserole and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
If casserole is frozen, thaw before baking.

title: quesadillas
directions: Place an even amount of cheese, onion, chiles and tomato onto each tortilla.
Fold tortilla over once.
Place in baking dish and cook or bake for 4 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: mom's cream cheese mints
directions: Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar by hand until smooth and doughy.
Divide mixture in half; add a few drops of peppermint extract to one half and a few drops of wintergreen extract to other half.
Taste and adjust flavor.
Blend green food coloring (several drops at a time) into peppermint mixture until soft green; blend red food coloring (several drops at a time) into wintergreen mixture until pastel pink.
Pinch off small pieces of dough; roll into balls and dip into sugar.

title: healthy cole slaw
directions: Preparation time: 10 minutes; chilling time: 15 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl stir together zwieback, sugar and butter until mixture is combined well.
Arrange one third of apples, peeled, cored and sliced thin, in buttered 1 1/2-quart souffle dish.
Top them with one-third of zwieback mixture and layer remaining apples and zwieback mixture in same manner, ending with zwieback mixture.
Bake crisp in middle of oven for 1 hour. Serve crisp warm with ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: garlic cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese and mix with the cream cheese.
Add garlic salt to taste.
Add onion and pickle, mixing well.
Form into a ball and roll in chili powder.
Chill.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Chill until partially set.
Add shredded corned beef, finely chopped onion and celery, grated eggs, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, sprayed lightly with Pam.
When set, cut in squares.
Serve on lettuce.

title: marshmallow delight
directions: Drain juice of pineapple cubes.
Cut marshmallows in small pieces.
Combine this and set in the refrigerator for several hours.
Just before serving, add whipped cream.

title: sour cream drop biscuits
directions: Cream butter, sour cream and sugar in a large bowl.
Sift together remaining dry ingredients.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto buttered baking sheets.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: marco polo casserole
directions: Chop onion, pepper and garlic.
Saute ground beef, onion, pepper and garlic until meat loses color.
Add other ingredients. Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Spoon mixture into dish.
Top with Chinese noodles.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy english trifle
directions: Drain fruits, reserving liquid.
(If too dry you can add a little of the reserved liquid.)
In a glass dish, arrange layers of the cake, large spoonfuls each of blueberries, raspberries, peaches and large dollops of whipped cream.
(Any frozen fruits may be substituted.)

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix egg substitute, sugar, oil and applesauce.
Add flour, orange peel, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Blend well.
Add bananas.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
Cut each loaf into 8 (1-inch) slices.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Add water to juice to make 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Cook pudding with liquid.
Cool.
Add fruit and refrigerate.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Remove the cream from the cookies.
Crush the outer part of the cookie (set aside).
Mix butter, 10x sugar and cream cheese together.
In separate bowl, mix vanilla pudding, milk and Cool Whip together.

title: creamed parsnips
directions: Cook the parsnips in boiling salted water for 35 to 40 minutes until very tender. Drain thoroughly, then return to the pan and mash with a potato masher. Stir in the cream and season to taste. Heat gently.
Serve hot. Garnish with parsley.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In microwave-safe bowl, combine sugar and corn syrup. Microwave on High 4 minutes; stir.
Add nuts and blend well. Microwave on High 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes or until mixture is light brown.
Stir in vanilla and butter.
Microwave 1 minute.
Add baking soda and stir quickly to blend.
Pour immediately onto buttered, foil lined cookie sheet, spreading quickly with wooden spoon.
Cool for 30 minutes.
Break apart.
Store in airtight container.

title: nuna's soda bread
directions: Blend together flour and shortening. Add sugar, salt, baking powder, seeds and raisins. Beat egg with milk. Add to make a soft dough. Mix well. Turn out onto a floured board. Knead lightly. Form into 2 or 3 round loaves and place on greased and floured pie pan. Bake at 450° for 5 minutes. Reduce to 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Let cool on wire rack. Tastes better served 1 to 2 days later. Store at room temperature in a tin or wrapped in waxed paper.

title: shortcut lasagna
directions: Brown
meat,
breaking	up
with wooden spoon.	Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, spaghetti sauce mix, V-8 juice and oregano.	Bring to a boil;
lower heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Cover
bottom
of
oiled,
large pan with a layer of meat sauce.
Add
a
layer of uncooked noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella.
Repeat
the layers until all ingredients are used, ending
with
the
meat
sauce.
Cover
pan tightly with heavy-duty foil.
Set on a large cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 1
hour.
Remove
from
oven and let stand for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Scrub and rinse potatoes.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Fan potatoes slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter. Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake potatoes for another 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned, cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft inside.
Check with fork.
Makes four servings.
May use caraway seed or cumin in place of herbs.

title: tangy meatballs and franks
directions: Note: I always double the recipe.
Combine all and put in crock-pot.

title: creole-style fish
directions: Cook green onions and green pepper in skillet until tender. Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, thyme and bay leaf. Simmer gently for 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Arrange fish in a shallow baking pan. (Pan should be coated with cooking spray.) Spoon sauce over fillets.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Serve with rice.
Yield: 6.

title: blueberry syrup
directions: Crush berries thoroughly; add water and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain through colander, pressing berries to extract all juice.
Strain juice through 3 or 4 thicknesses of damp cheesecloth or jelly bag.
Makes about 2 cups of juice.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend all together and serve on lettuce.

title: one pot bean dinner
directions: Brown hamburg, bacon and onions.
Drain off fat.
Add all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 2 hours.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and heat gently several minutes. Pour into nonmetallic baking dish and add chicken.
Marinate at least 4 hours, turn occasionally.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Layer each ingredient in order listed.
Bake, uncovered at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: clam diggers scallop
directions: Add clam juice to milk to make 1 1/2 cups.
Mix clams; blend ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If using fresh clams, match proportions given.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until well done.
Remove from pot and cut meat into bite-size chunks.
Put chicken back into broth.
Add mushrooms, pimento, pepper and garlic powder.
Simmer 2 hours. Fix 3/4 of 24 ounce package spaghetti in separate pot.
When done, rinse and add to chicken mixture.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese, sprinkled on top.

title: no guilt pumpkin pudding
directions: Makes 2 servings. Mix ingredients. Garnish with sprinkle of cinnamon and cinnamon sticks.

title: egg noodles
directions: Whip egg until frothy.
Mix flour in gradually.
Roll out in flour.
Slice and hang.
Cook in hot broth or soup.

title: chicken lambrusco
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Mix 1/2 cup of the dressing (the less expensive dressings generally have the strongest flavor for cooking) with the wine and pour the mixture into a baking dish. Dip the chicken breasts in the remaining dressing, then lightly coat them with bread crumbs and place them in the baking dish. Cover and bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: syrup candy
directions: Fill an iron skillet with cane syrup about half full; heat to boiling and continue to boil gently until syrup thickens.
(To test for proper consistency, pull a spoon through the candy halfway across the pan; the path of the spoon should remain intact, revealing the bottom of the pan.)
Remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon of baking soda and stir well.
Pour syrup into a buttered dish and allow to cool enough to handle.
Pull candy with well-greased hands until cooled and hardened.
Shape into strips and cut into bite size pieces.

title: lemon meringue nests
directions: Mix salt and egg whites.
Beat until stiff.
Beat in 3/4 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Beat in lemon extract.
Drop meringue onto brown paper lined baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden.
Reduce oven to 250°.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes longer until dry and lightly browned.
Cool.

title: lil's fabulous fudge
directions: Bring to a boil in large pan the milk.
Remove from heat and add sugar.
Stir and then put back on stove.
Bring to boil and cook, covered, 2 to 3 minutes (until steam washes down crystals from sides).
Uncover, reduce heat and cook without stirring until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Cool by placing pan in cold water in sink until you can touch bottom of pan.
Add butter and peanut butter.
Beat partially.
Add vanilla.
Beat until it loses sheen.
Put in buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Tastes like heaven, enjoy!

title: red carpet cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and shortening.
Mix food color and color mixture.
Mix vinegar and soda.
Add dry ingredients and milk. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Wash and cut fruit into chunks.
Assemble in bowl.
Add lemon juice and fruit concentrate.
Mix.
Chill salad.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Drain artichokes; cut into fourths.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put into ovenproof dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with pumpernickel bread.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Prepare moist dressing.
Spread 1/2 of mixture on bottom of large baking dish.
Spread chicken on the mix.
Cook beans 5 minutes.
Then spread over chicken.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Mix soup with 1 can chicken broth and pour over entire mixture.
Top with remaining dressing mix.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: chicken-n-dumplings with angel biscuits
directions: Place chicken breasts into a large pot and cover with water. Add salt and pepper.
Boil for 1 1/2 hours.
Add rosemary, parsley and marjoram.
Add more water if needed.
Add onion and carrots. Boil for another 35 minutes.
Add peas and set aside.
Pour stewed chicken mixture into the bottom of a large casserole dish and place Angel biscuits on top of chicken.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 17 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until butter melts.
Place chicken in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour until tender. Serves 4.

title: chili sauce
directions: Note:
I use my food processor to chop all the ingredients.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs. Add milk, baking soda, baking powder and enough flour to make stiff enough to roll.

title: chicken celeste
directions: Clean and skin chicken; dust with flour that has been seasoned with salt, pepper and paprika. Pour oil in heavy skillet or Dutch oven; brown chicken on both sides. Add onion, sherry and water. Cover and simmer until tender, about 1 hour. Remove chicken to hot platter and keep warm. Add mayonnaise and yogurt to liquid in skillet, blending until smooth. Add parsley and additional seasoning if desired. Pour over chicken. Serves 6.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: Place berries in baking dish.
Cover with pineapple. Pour on dry cake mix. Scatter nuts on top.
Melt butter and drizzle over. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Combine sour cream and whipping cream.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour or until thickened.

title: quick chicken cacciatore
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
In large skillet, brown chicken and garlic in 3 tablespoons oil.
Remove chicken from pan.
Add pasta sauce, then chicken; stir.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes, adding peppers during last 5 minutes. Uncover; top each chicken breast with half cheese slice.
Toss hot cooked macaroni with remaining 1 tablespoon oil and parsley. Serve with chicken and sauce.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 servings.

title: german potato pancakes
directions: Pare the potatoes and grate them.
Add beaten eggs and sifted dry ingredients.
Drop from a spoon into a hot greased frying pan. Bake until golden brown on both sides.
Makes 10 to
12 cakes. Good with applesauce.

title: apple-raisin bread
directions: Grease two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
In a medium bowl stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and ginger.
In a large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat together margarine and sugar until smooth.
Beat in corn syrup.
Add eggs; beat until well mixed.
With a wooden spoon, stir in apples.
Stir in flour mixture, raisins and nuts.

title: working woman's rolls
directions: In the evening, dissolve yeast in water. Stir in milk and sugar. Let liquid mixture stand at room temperature for 1 hour, then beat in eggs, butter, sugar, flour and salt. Let this mixture stand overnight at room temperature, lightly covered.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Put potatoes, egg, sugar and both shortenings and vanilla in bowl.
Mix together.
Add flour and turn out on floured board. Mix well.
Roll and cut out.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° until done.

title: delicious hungarian treats
directions: Mix butter and flour like for pie.
Add sugar, soda, salt and lemon rind.
Make a hollow in mix and add egg yolks.
Mix well, and then add sour cream.
Mix thoroughly.
Take 2/3 of dough and roll out.
Put in a 9 x 12 inch baking pan.
Have dough halfway up sides.
Spread preserves over dough.
Roll out the rest of the crust and cut into strips.
Place strips in lattice fashion over preserves.
Press ends into dough.
Bake 30 - 40 minutes in 350° oven until brown.
Cut into squares while warm.
Sift powdered sugar on top.

title: perfect meringue
directions: Combine cornstarch dissolved in cold water with boiling water in	saucepan.
Cook
until	thick and clear.
Cool completely. Beat
egg
whites
just until frothy.
Add sugar and salt.	When thick, add cooled cornstarch mixture and beat just until
peaks form.
Cover pie filling, seal edges and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hummus
directions: Blend thoroughly in food processor until creamy.
Refrigerate overnight.
Good with pita bread, lamb or beef shish kebabs.

title: dad's baked beans and pork chops
directions: Place beans in pot.
Cover with water.
Boil 2 or 3 minutes. Place on side for 2 hours.
After 2 hours, bring to a boil and cook until tender, about 1 hour.
Combine other ingredients, mix well and put in a casserole.
Lay bacon strips on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
After 1 hour, place pork chops on top and bake for another 1 hour and 15 minutes, turning pork chops after 45 minutes. Add water as needed if beans seem to be dry, they should be moist at all times.
Serves 2.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Cook celery and onion in water in saucepan over low heat until tender; drain.
Combine with corn bread and bread crumbs in bowl. Add eggs, butter, sage, salt and enough broth to make of moist consistency.

title: diet soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Cook for 25 to 30 minutes over medium heat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place 4 slices of the cubed bread in the bottom of a deep casserole dish.
On top of the bread, place the chicken.
Mix the celery, onions, pimento and mayonnaise and spread over the chicken.
Then spoon the mushroom soup evenly over the celery mixture.
Beat together the eggs and milk; pour mixture over the bread.

title: shrimp and broccoli over linguini
directions: Buy shrimp precooked at supermarket or fish market.
Place broccoli in 1 inch boiling water for 3 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Cook linguini according to package directions.
Drain and toss with 1/4 cup butter.
In a large skillet, melt remaining butter and saute garlic for 2 minutes.
Add cooked shrimp and saute for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add broccoli.
Stir in pasta, salt, pepper, Italian seasoning, oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Toss lightly to coat evenly.
Serve immediately.
Bon appetite!

title: new york style cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and cottage cheese together until creamy. Add sugar and eggs.
On low heat, beat in cornstarch, flour, lemon juice and vanilla.
Add margarine and sour cream.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into a greased and floured spring-form pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until firm at 325°.
Turn off heat. Let stand in oven for 2 hours.
Remove and cool completely. Refrigerate for several hours.

title: cake mix cookie
directions: Mix cake mix and pudding together with your hands.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Roll into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Press down slightly with hand.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: peanut butter banana cake
directions: Prepare the yellow cake mix according to the directions and with proper ingredients.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Reserve 1/4 cup crumbs.
Press remainder in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: beef bologna
directions: Mix and shape into long rolls.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Remove Saran Wrap; lay on rack in baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Wrap in paper towels to absorb grease.
Cool and wrap in foil; refrigerate.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and dry spinach.
Shred and place spinach in a large salad bowl.
Prepare remaining ingredients and sprinkle over spinach.
Top with Special Salad Dressing.
Toss and serve.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Soak cabbage in cold water for 30 minutes.
Drain.
Mix corn flakes with margarine for crust.
Add cabbage and salt to taste. Heat mayonnaise, milk and celery soup together.
Pour over cabbage.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes (uncovered).
If you like less crispy, cover and cook 20 minutes more.

title: pearl's rolls
directions: Mix the first two ingredients, then add yeast with water and let stand.
Add sugar, salt, 1/2 cup cold water and 1/4 cup warm water to hot water and Crisco mixture.
Add yeast and flour. Knead lightly.
Set aside to rise until double in bulk.

title: marinated sugar snap peas
directions: Mix ingredients together in a large bowl.
Serve immediately or refrigerate.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: champagne sophisticate
directions: Pour over ice ring in punch bowl and watch the happy faces.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in water until tender.
Drain.
In a greased casserole, layer vegetables with a mixture of soup, cheese and seasonings.
Top with stuffing mix and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Serves 8.

title: brown sugar pound cake(great at christmas)
directions: Beat margarine and Crisco together.
Gradually add the sugars; beat until mixture is light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder and add alternately with milk and vanilla to creamed mixture of butter and sugars.
Stir in nuts.
Beat well.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
(Test with straw.)
Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Place butter in baking dish and place in oven to melt. Combine flour, sugar and milk; beat to a batter.
Pour flour mixture on melted butter; do not stir.
Place fruit and juice evenly on top of pastry.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with ice cream.

title: impossible broccoli and chicken
directions: Run broccoli under cold water to thaw and drain thoroughly. Mix broccoli and 2 cups of cheese, chicken and onion.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick mix until smooth.
Add to chicken and broccoli mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a greased 10-inch pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven and top with remaining cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: stir fried pork(silver bowl winner 1989)
directions: In small bowl, combine the cornstarch, soy sauce mixture. Heat a large skillet for one minute.
Add the oil and heat for 30 seconds longer.
Add the pork, and stir fry until the meat has lost its pink color.
Gradually add all the chicken broth to the pan, pouring it down the side of the pan to heat it.
Stir fry until the sauce begins to thicken.
Add the carrots, celery, bamboo shoots, and onions.
Stir fry for about 20 minutes, or until carrots are tender.
Add green beans and toss well.
Cover pan and simmer for about 5 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Separate dough (crescent rolls) and arrange in deep pan. Press over bottom and up sides, making sure to seal all perforations.
Spoon sausage over dough.
Sprinkle with hash browns and Cheddar cheese.
Set aside.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Make sure pan is deep.

title: claussen pickle rolls
directions: Drain pickles and dry.
Spread softened cream cheese around pickle and wrap in beef.
Refrigerate for about 1 hour.
Slice each pickle in 1 to 2-inch slices.

title: microwave barbecue ribs
directions: Set power select at Medium.
In oblong baking dish, arrange ribs, onion and celery.
Heat, covered, for 10 minutes.
Cover with plastic wrap; set power select at High for 5 minutes and at low for 60 minutes or until ribs are tender.
Rearrange ribs once and baste with sauce occasionally.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients together except franks.
Dip franks into mixture until well coated.
Drop into hot oil until golden brown, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain.

title: easy cheese crescents
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix cheese, egg product, buttermilk and sour cream in large bowl.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Divide dough into halves.
Turn each half onto lightly floured surface; gently roll in flour to coat and shape into ball.
Pat or roll each ball into 9-inch circle.
Cut each circle into 6 wedges.
Roll up wedges, starting at wide end. Place rolls, with points underneath, on cookie sheet; curve slightly.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Cool on wire rack.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Add eggs and oil, stirring until all dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool in pans 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool thoroughly. Frost.

title: potato skins
directions: Clean and bake potatoes until done.
Cool. Halve each potato lengthwise.
Scoop out inside of each potato, leaving approximately 1/4-inch thick shell.
Combine cooking oil, chili powder and Tabasco and brush on inside of potato halves.
Then cut the potato halves in half again lengthwise; return to baking sheet.
Sprinkle with bacon, tomato and green onion.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve with sour cream.

title: apple butter bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
Combine eggs, butter, apple butter and milk; beat well.
Stir in pecans and raisins.
Add flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: english muffins in a loaf(makes two loaves)
directions: Grease 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat liquids until very warm. Add to dry mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in rest of flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon into greased loaf pans.
Sprinkle with cornmeal.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately and cool.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Trim excess fat from pork and cut into 1-inch cubes.
In a bowl combine egg, 1/4 cup cornstarch, flour, 1/4 cup chicken broth and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Beat until smooth.

title: sicilian seafood chowder
directions: Heat oil in heavy large saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add onion, celery and bell pepper and saute until tender, about 7 minutes.
Add garlic, basil, thyme, pepper, oregano and crushed red pepper and cook 2 minutes.
Add clam juice and tomato sauce and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until slightly thickened, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.
(Chowder can be prepared to this point 1 day ahead; refrigerate.
Bring to simmer before continuing.) Cook orzo in medium saucepan of boiling water until tender but still firm to bite, stirring occasionally.
Drain. Rinse under cold water and drain.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cut-out sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Gradually blend in dry ingredients which have been sifted together. Chill dough at least 3 hours. Roll to 1/8 to 1/4-inch on lightly floured surface (sometimes I use powdered sugar to flour the surface). Cut out with favorite cutters. Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Yields about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, corn syrup and water to dissolve.
Place on fire and bring to 250°.
Then add butter and nuts and keep stirring until nuts are thoroughly cooked or to 300°.
Take off fire and stir in soda and salt.
Stir quickly until it foams up.
Pour out on buttered marble.
When cool enough, turn batch over and stretch and pull.
Make it very thin.
When cool, store in airtight jars or tins.

title: quick baked pasta
directions: Bring 4 quarts water to boil.
Heat a large frying pan.
Add oil, beef and garlic.
Saute until meat is tender; drain off fat. Ad spaghetti sauce, gravy, half and half, Parmesan cheese, oregano, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer mixture while pasta cooks tender.
Drain pasta and mix with sauce.
Pour all into 3-quart (9 x 13-inch) dish and top with Mozzarella.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes at 350°; bake until all is bubbly hot.

title: pizza-style sandwiches
directions: Place salami, pizza sauce and cheese between slices of bread. Sprinkle with garlic salt and grill.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and cook for 5 minutes.
Pour over vegetables.
Serve hot or chilled.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Make sure mixture is not over 1/2 to 5/8 inches thick.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook sliced squash and chopped onion in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes, then drain well.
Combine cream of chicken soup, sour cream and grated cheese.
Stir in shredded carrot.
Fold in drained squash and onion.
Combine stuffing mix with the melted oleo.
Spread half of the stuffing mixture in bottom of greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over vegetables.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until it is heated through.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Finely chop apples and pecans.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
If needed, add small amount of milk to moisten.
Cook until done.
Makes one rectangular pan or two round layers.
Needs no icing.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute pork and onion in butter.
Add liquids and spices; let simmer 4 hours or until sauce reduces until about half and thickens.

title: barbecue sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Add chipped ham and mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute bacon and onions in large saucepan until bacon is done and onions tender. Stir remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Simmer 20 minutes.

title: chocolate raspberry yogurt pie
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl for 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir frozen yogurt until melted. Stir in whipped topping and fruit.
Refrigerate until mixture mounds, if necessary.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.
Garnish with shaved chocolate, additional whipped topping and berries.
Store leftovers covered in refrigerator.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook broccoli for 4 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Mix with other ingredients and chill.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Run cold water over it to rinse and cool it.
Toss in other ingredients and pour salad dressing over all.
Toss again to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: orange drop doughnuts
directions: Combine oleo, sugar, egg yolks, milk and orange juice.
Mix well.

title: reduced calorie apple pie
directions: Drain apples and place in diet crust.
In 1/4 cup apple juice, sprinkle Knox gelatine and let set 1 minute.
Heat on High in microwave until dissolved about 1 minute.
Add remaining apple juice to dissolved mixture.
Stir in spice and sweetener.
Place over ice water and stir until mixture starts to thicken.
Pour over apples.
Chill until firm.
Nutrient Exchange: 1 fruit.

title: lemon teriyaki chicken
directions: Roll chicken in flour to coat.
Melt butter in skillet and add chicken breasts.
Cook over medium heat until chicken is lightly browned (5 to 7 minutes).
Remove chicken; set aside.
Stir in teriyaki sauce, lemon juice, garlic and sugar.
Return chicken breasts to pan; simmer 3 minutes.
Turn chicken breasts over; continue cooking until fork-tender (2 to 3 minutes).
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Makes 3 to 6 servings.

title: hobo dinner for two
directions: Line baking dish with foil.
Shape hamburger into patties; place potatoes and carrots around patties.
Cover meat and vegetables with onion slices.
Sprinkle with water.
Cover completely with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old fashion macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package.
Drain and set aside. Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a casserole dish.
Make a white sauce as follows:
In large saucepan over low heat, melt butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper, stirring constantly.
Keep stirring, slowly add milk; when mixture thickens, add cheese and stir until melted.
Combine sauce and macaroni.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with breadcrumbs and dot with butter.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: microwave monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Place butter in round microwave cake dish; microwave for 1 minute and 30 seconds, or until butter melts.
Stir brown sugar and ground cinnamon into butter.
Add biscuits; stir to coat with mixture.
Arrange biscuits evenly in dish.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Best served hot.

title: quick cherry cake
directions: Empty cherries into an 11 x 15-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over top of cherries.
Pour butter over cake mix. Sprinkle walnuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 30 minutes.
Spoon ice cream on top.
Serves 12.

title: ugly duckling pudding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except brown sugar and nuts in large mixer bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed and pulls away from sides of pan.
Do not underbake.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Spoon hot Butter Glaze over warm cake.
Serve warm or cool.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Beat egg and mix together all other ingredients.
Brush on chicken and cook.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (8-inch) foil pans (square).
Cream butter, oil and sugar.
Add and mix eggs, vanilla, sour cream and zucchini.
Sift together flour, all spices, salt, baking soda and cocoa.
Add dry ingredients to other ingredients by hand.
Do not use electric mixer for this step. Pour into prepared pans.
Sprinkle each cake with 6 ounces chocolate chips.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool on cake rack. Leave in pan.
Wrap in foil.
May be frozen (in pans).

title: coney sauce
directions: Brown beef and onions until beef is no longer pink.
Add chili powder, salt, and catsup.
Cook until bubbly and then simmer.

title: marinated calico vegetable salad
directions: Drain beans, corn, peas and pimentos.
Combine all vegetables in large bowl and set aside.

title: roasted turkey thighs with autumn vegetables
directions: Rinse duck inside and out and pat dry; cut off tail and discard.
Reserve giblets for other uses.
Mix together ginger, cinnamon, nutmeg, pepper and cloves.
Sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon of spice mixture inside duck.
Stir 1 tablespoon of the soy into remaining spice mixture, then rub evenly over exterior of bird. Cut one of the green onions in half and tuck inside cavity of duck.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours or until next day.

title: chicken divine
directions: Cook chicken.
Cool and slice into bite-size pieces.
Mix all ingredients except crackers.
Top mixture with crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix together.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured bread pans.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.
Drizzle with glaze while still hot.
Let cool.
Slice and serve or freeze for later.

title: tarragon-dijon chicken
directions: Saute chicken breasts in skillet in 1 teaspoon oil until browned on 1 side.
Turn over and saute with remaining teaspoon oil.
Remove from heat and keep warm.
On low heat in same skillet, add nonfat plain yogurt, Dijon mustard, tarragon, pepper and hot sauce, stirring to combine.
Add chicken breasts to sauce in skillet and heat all thoroughly.
Serves 4.

title: quick corn relish
directions: Place corn, pepper, onion and jalapeno pepper in a medium bowl.
Toss with olive oil.
Stir in cider vinegar and honey; mix until well blended.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and chill until needed.
Yields 4 servings.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Mix first four ingredients and add juice from cocktail and well beaten egg.
Fold in cocktail.
Pour in ungreased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and sugar over top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon, cut into small pieces.
Brown hamburger, chopped pepper and chopped onion.
Drain off grease, then add bacon, catsup, sugar, pork and beans, kidney beans (drained), green beans (drained), butter beans (drained), salt, dry mustard, vinegar and brown sugar.
Mix together and heat at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl. Pour into greased, floured Bundt pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Pour icing on cake immediately after removing from oven.

title: swiss ham pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix altogether with mixer.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Cook for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Fry and drain hamburger and sausage.
Add cheese and stir until cheese melts.
Add remaining seasonings and let cool. Spread on party rye.
Freeze on cookie sheet, then store in freezer in zip lock bags.
When ready to use, place on cookie sheets and bake in preheated 3 50° oven for 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Good dip for all types of fruit.

title: french meat pie
directions: In skillet heat oil over medium heat.
Saute onion until tender.
Remove and set aside.
Brown beef and pork together. Drain. Combine onion, meat, potatoes and seasonings.
Line pie plate with pastry.
Fill with meat mixture.

title: marinated zucchini
directions: Cut unpeeled zucchini into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Spread slices on paper towels and sprinkle both sides lightly with salt. Let stand 30 minutes.
Rinse with water and dry.
Dice zucchini slices into quarters.
Heat oil in heavy frying pan.
Add squash and coat well with oil.
Add water and garlic.
Cover pan; reduce heat and simmer until just tender.
Should still be crunchy.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter.
Pour into casserole dish. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir after 15 minutes.

title: beer batter onion rings
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Beat egg yolks slightly; add beer.
Mix with flour mixture.
Blend well.
Let batter stand at room temperature 20 to 25 minutes.
Fry in oil at 375°.
Brown on both sides, about 2 to 3 minutes.

title: special green beans
directions: Cook beans; drain and set aside.
Cook and drain bacon; cut into bits.
Saute onion in butter.
Add flour and blend well.
Add milk and cook, stirring until smooth and thick.
Add sugar, vinegar and salt to taste.
Add green beans and sour cream.
Heat to serving temperature but do not boil.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add mashed cranberry sauce. Stir until smooth.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in pecans and apples.
Pour into a 6-cup mold.
Chill for 3 hours before serving.

title: zesty pasta salad
directions: Combine ham, pasta, vegetables and salad dressing in large bowl; toss to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: apple seafoam salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add marshmallows; stir until partially dissolved.
Chill until syrupy.
Fold in applesauce, walnuts and the mayo.
Spoon into a 1-quart mold; chill until firm.
Unmold and garnish with watercress or lettuce.
Makes six servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then wet, then altogether.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: congo bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a large mixing bowl, combine Margarine, brown sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add chocolate chips, pecan pieces, and flour.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into an greased 9 x 12 inch baking dish.
Bake for 20 - 30 minutes, until cake springs bach when pressed in middle.
Cool.
Cut into bars and serve.

title: italian skillet dinner
directions: Cook sausage pieces in a large skillet for abut 10 minutes, until lightly browned.
Pour off all but one tablespoon of fat. Add onions, garlic and green pepper.
Saute until onions are transparent.
Stir in beans, tomato sauce and spices.
Simmer, covered, about 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon bars(low-fat)
directions: Blend 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup sugar; cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press mixture on bottom of 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Blend egg product, lemon juice, lemon peel and remaining flour and sugar; pour over pastry crust.
Bake 15 minutes more or until set.
Cool slightly; sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.
Cool completely; cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.

title: ramen noodle salad
directions: Smash Ramen noodles with hammer in package.
Take beef packets out and set aside.
Put noodles, onions, cole slaw mix and sunflower seeds in large bowl.
In jar, add oil, vinegar, sugar and beef packets.
Shake well; pour over ingredients in bowl. Refrigerate.

title: broccoli dish
directions: Mix together and pour into 1-quart casserole dish.
Garnish with Hi Ho Cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Saute ground beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Add brown gravy mix and water.
Bring to a boil; add mushrooms.
Lower heat to simmer; add sour cream.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Enjoy!!

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Add all ingredients together in rice cooker.
Mix well.
Turn cooker on; done in 30 minutes.

title: diabetic lemon pie
directions: Combine
pudding
mix, gelatin and water in a saucepan. Cook over
medium
heat
until
mixture comes to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Add
Equal,
rind and juice; stir well. Pour
into a bowl and cover.
Chill in refrigerator until cold and slightly thickened.

title: chicken fried chops
directions: Combine flour, salt, mustard and garlic powder. Dredge pork chops in flour mixture. Brown pork chops in skillet on both sides in oil. Place in slow cooker. Combine soup and water. Pour over chops. Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or until meat is tender. If desired, thicken pan juices and serve with pork chops.

title: caramel-cheese cake dip
directions: Mix all ingredients (except almonds and caramel topping) in bowl on low speed until well blended.
Pour into 8-inch pie plate. Top with caramel ice cream topping and sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Garnish dip with Granny Smith apple slices.
Yum!

title: green chili
directions: Cube pork and jalapenos and brown. Combine tomatoes, chilies and cumin to pork. Add onion, chopped garlic, salt and pepper to taste. Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients and bake for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash berries, save the prettiest one for
the
crowning garnish; hull the rest.
Put half the berries into a saucepan, crush them.
Add sugar, cornstarch and lemon juice.
Cook
and stir over medium heat until it thickens and
becomes
translucent. Cool.
Cut the remaining berries into halves
and	stir gently into
the
cooked
mixture.
It's the
combination	of cooked and raw berries that gives the wonderful
flavor.
Turn filling
into pie
shell	an
hour before serving.
Chill
in refrigerator. Garnish with whipped cream; top
with unhulled berry.

title: peach cobbler
directions: A
homespun
dessert
that's so good you'll bake it for breakfast, brunch or picnics.

title: oven-fried vegetables
directions: Spray a cold baking sheet with nonstick spray; set aside.
In a pie plate, stir together bread crumbs, cheese and paprika until well mixed.
In a medium bowl, place vegetables.
Drizzle with salad dressing.
Toss until coated.
Roll vegetables in crumb mixture until coated.
Place coated vegetables in a single layer on prepared baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 9 to 11 minutes until golden brown.

title: sweet and sour barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients well.
Use for pork and chicken.
Makes 2 cups.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water (105°).
Mix together 1 cup water, sugar and eggs, then add yeast mixture, oil, salt and flour.
Put in a glass greased bowl.
Cover and let stand in warm place, covered, for 8 hours or overnight.
Divide in thirds.
On well floured surface, roll out each third into 12-inch circle.
Cut with pizza cutter.
Roll up to form crescents.
Let rise 4 hours. Bake on greased sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: 1-2-3-4 sheet cake(recipe passed from mrs. mary rucker wannamaker)
directions: Cream Crisco, butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Sift flour together with baking powder, then add milk, vanilla, salt and food coloring. Bake at 325° for 1 hour in sheet cake pan.

title: chuck roast
directions: Place one package Lipton soup on heavy-duty aluminum foil.
On this, place chuck roast; salt lightly.
On top of roast, add soup (two cans may be used for more gravy).
Fold foil over tightly; bake at 300° for one hour per pound.
(Never cook under 3 hours.) When roast is done, gravy is made.

title: pig licking good cake
directions: Save water and liquid from oranges and pineapple to make liquid for cake.
Bake as directed and let cool.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Shake 2/3 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon in plastic bag.
Melt together margarine, 1 1/3 cups sugar, 1 tablespoon cinnamon and vanilla.
Shake cut biscuits in bag.
Put biscuits in Bundt pan alternating nuts and syrup between rows.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let set for 1 minute and flip over on plate.

title: pineapple cheese balls
directions: Thoroughly blend cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Fold in pineapple, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Chill several hours. Divide in half.
Shape into balls; roll in nuts.
Chill overnight. Serve with crackers.
Make ahead and freeze, if desired.
Makes into 2 balls.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Flatten out crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake as directed on package.
Cool crust.
Mix together cream cheese, Miracle Whip and dressing.
Spread on crust.
Add chopped green onion (blades also).
Add veggies as you like and shredded cheese.
Cut into squares.

title: rollie's mom's apple cake
directions: Mix thoroughly the brown sugar, oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt and stir into the first mixture; do not overbeat.
Add apples and walnuts.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch
pan at 375° for 55 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: holiday cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello with hot water; add cold water, then chill until partially set.
Add oranges, pineapple, cranberry sauce and nuts.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill
until set.
So good you'll never want plain cranberry sauce again!

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Measure out oats and peanut butter in bowl.
Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in medium sized saucepan.
Bring to full boil for 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.	Add salt and vanilla. Blend in peanut butter and oats.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Cool until firm.

title: spiced chicken
directions: Sprinkle paprika on chicken.
In large skillet, melt butter then brown chicken in the butter.
Sprinkle salt and dressing mix over chicken.
Stir in undiluted soup and water.
Simmer covered for 1 hour.
This is excellent served over white rice.

title: spiced cranberry ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin, salt, cinnamon and cloves in boiling water. Add cranberry sauce and orange rind.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in orange sections, chopped walnuts and chopped apples.
Pour into a 6-cup mold.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Unmold.
Or pour into an 11 x 13-inch pan; chill until firm and cut into squares. Yield:
12 servings.
Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.

title: easy and good meat loaf
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients with 1 can of tomato paste.
Chill for 1 hour.
Mold into a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour second can of tomato paste over meat loaf and bake additional 20 minutes or until nicely glazed.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Add cheese to butter and onion; mix.
Add milk, chicken broth and flour.
Add broccoli.

title: old west barbecued chicken
directions: Prepare outdoor grill for barbecue.
Place chicken on grill over medium heat; cook until golden brown on both sides, about 10 minutes.
Then, to avoid charring, stand chicken pieces upright, leaning one against the other.
Rearrange pieces from time to time and cook until chicken is fork-tender, about 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice.
Pour into 1 gallon milk jug and fill with water within 3-inches of top, then place in freezer.
Take out of freezer 5 or 6 hours before you are ready to serve it.
It will be like an "Icee".

title: poor man's pot
directions: Make small patties out of ground beef.
Layer meat, onion and potatoes until all used up.
Add a can of chicken rice soup and a can of water.
Cook until meat and potatoes are tender.
Serve.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients except carrots in saucepan. Bring to a boil and continue boiling for 1 minute. Pour over drained carrots. Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute onion in margarine until golden.
Dilute consomme with water, bring to a boil.
Combine all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole (greased).
Bake covered 30 minutes or until rice feels tender and all the liquid is absorbed in a moderate oven.
Uncover at once.
Sprinkle with toasted slivered almonds.

title: quickie bars
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Set aside to cool and set either in cold water or in refrigerator.
Beat eggs.
Add vanilla. Add brown sugar, soda, flour and nuts.
Pour carefully over the butter in the pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut in squares and roll in sugar or simply dust the sugar on top while it is still warm.

title: orvis salsa
directions: Finely chop half of the ingredients.
Puree remainder in food processor.
Combine with chopped ingredients.
Let sit in refrigerator at least 8 hours.
Keeps 7 days if refrigerated.

title: peach pickles
directions: Drain juice from peaches and place juice in saucepan.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Remove from the heat and cool.
Refrigerate a few hours or overnight before serving.
Keep refrigerated.
This recipe can be halved and is still tasty.

title: fresh corn loaf
directions: Mix
corn, tomatoes, onions and green pepper.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Add all other ingredients to this mixture and bake in a greased casserole at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: linda's spiced pretzels
directions: Pour mixture over pretzels and toss to coat.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Spread on cookie sheets.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes. Store in a tin or plastic bag.

title: three bean baked beans
directions: Drain and rinse kidney beans and butter beans.
Pour off some of the juice from baked beans.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli. Cut off florets, discarding the stems.
Place in large mixing bowl.
Slice the onions into thin slivers and add to the bowl.
In a saute pan or microwave oven, cook the bacon strips until crispy. Dice and add to bowl.
Add the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; mix well.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Refrigerate for 1 hour until well chilled.
Serve cold. Serves 8.

title: polynesian stew
directions: In a large skillet, cook the onions, celery and garlic in the canola oil for 3 minutes.
Add the round steak, cut in thin strips and the strips of green pepper.
Cook until meat is slightly seared.
Add the beef broth, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Mix the soy sauce with the cornstarch until smooth.
Add to meat mixture and cook on medium heat until mixture is clear.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and cream cheese; beat until very fluffy.
Add eggs, 2 at a time, along with one cup flour, beating after each addition until very smooth.
Add flavorings and beat mixture again.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan, greased and floured first.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: dijon chicken
directions: Spread	chicken breast with the Dijon mustard.	Lay the 2 tomato
slices
on	top.
Sprinkle	with
the bread crumbs. Drizzle with the olive oil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; set aside.
Beat butter, peanut butter and sugars; mix well.
Add egg and mix.
Add flour mixture. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Roll into small balls; flatten with a fork.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes on a greased cookie sheet.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flavoring.
Add eggs and dry ingredients, alternating 1 egg to 1/2 cup flour.
Beat until blended at low speed.
Add sour cream.
Blend well.
Use tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar together.
Add eggs and bananas.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients plus milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add nuts and pour into greased loaf pan (1 large or 2 small).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix well.
Cook 1 hour at 400°.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brown sausage. Drain. Mix with softened cream cheese. Wash mushrooms and remove stems. Stuff and bake at 350° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix together the noodles, mushroom soup, Pet milk, corned beef, cheese and onion.
Put 1/2 cup potato chips on top.
Bake.

title: rocky road squares
directions: In top of double boiler, over hot water, melt chips, butter and condensed milk. Remove from heat. Combine peanuts and marshmallows. Add chocolate mixture. Spread in greased wax paper-lined 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill 2 hours.
Makes 20 to 24 servings.

title: caitlin's potatoes
directions: Thinly slice the yams (can use sweet potatoes).
Brush melted butter over bottom of casserole dish and layer a third of the yams in the pan.
Add half of the apple slices and sprinkle with salt, pepper and brown sugar.
Drizzle with some of the butter.
Add another layer of yams, the remaining apples and a final layer of yams.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Drizzle with remaining butter and maple syrup.
Cover and bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Remove lid; continue to bake about 15 minutes, until yams are tender and top is starting to crisp.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease cookie sheets. place sheets of foil on countertop for cooling cookies. Combine sugar and cinnamon in small bowl. combine cake mix, eggs and oil in large bowl. Stir until well blended. Shape dough into 1 inch balls. Roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture. Place balls 2 inches apart on cookie sheets. Flatten balls with bottom of glass. Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes or until set. cool one minute on cookie sheets. Remove to foil to cool completely. Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 400° until done, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: special party punch
directions: In a large bowl, place chilled pineapple juice, sherbet and vanilla ice cream.
Beat until blended. Pour into punch bowl and gently stir in ginger ale. Yields 24 cups.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix all ingredients except for baking soda and popcorn.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Take off stove and add baking soda.
Put over popcorn and stir to coat well.
You can add peanuts to popcorn. Pour on cookie sheet and bake for 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: bean dip surprise
directions: Mix together bean dip and sour cream.
Put in shallow baking dish.
Top with pizza cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.
Serve with "dipping" Fritos.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill at least 30 minutes.
Best if prepared a day ahead.

title: heath bar pie
directions: Melt marshmallows and Heath bars with milk in top of double boiler. (Put Heath bars in first. It takes them longer to melt.) Cool.
Add whipped cream and flavoring.

title: tuna biscuit casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a double boiler or heavy saucepan, place 3 tablespoons margarine over medium heat to melt.
Stir in flour and reduce heat slightly.
Cook until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Slowly whisk in milk.
Whisk constantly over low heat until sauce thickens, about 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and season with garlic salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Set aside.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until almost done; drain.
Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Put chicken over broccoli.
Mix together 3 cans soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; pour over chicken. Spread grated cheese over top.
Melt butter and mix with herb stuffing and spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Cover with foil last 15 minutes.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Cook and stir zucchini and onion in margarine for 10 minutes. Stir in parsley.
Add salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano leaves.
Combine eggs and cheese.
Stir in zucchini mixture.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles and place in ungreased 10-inch pie pan.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust. Spread crust with mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture onto crust. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until center is set.
Can be put in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter, egg yolks and sugar well.
Add lemon extract. Mix pecans and fruit with 2 cups sifted flour in a large pan. Blend in remaining 3 cups of flour to butter and sugar mixture. Add soda which has been mixed with warm water.
Mix well, then add fruit and nuts.
Add slightly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Place a pan of water under cake while baking to prevent burning.

title: fiesta egg nog
directions: In a large punch bowl, stir ice cream until smooth.
Add eggnog and stir.
Add vanilla extract and cinnamon; continue stirring until well blended.
Serve cold with some cinnamon on top.
Give it the real "fiesta" touch by adding some white rum to it.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line 24 muffin cups with paper liners. Combine dry cake mix, flour and baking powder in large bowl.
Beat milk, eggs and oil together with fork.
Add to mixture in bowl and stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon batter into muffin cups 1/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: southwestern pinto beans
directions: Soak beans as directed on package. Do not drain. Cover and simmer beans for 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until tender.
In a large skillet, cook bacon, onions and garlic over medium heat until bacon is crisp. (Do not drain.)
Add bacon mixture, tomato sauce, chili powder, oregano, salt, pepper and cumin to beans. Stir well. Simmer, uncovered, an additional 20 to 30 minutes.

title: shells and stuffing with light tomato sauce
directions: Heat oil in a large, deep skillet and cook the onion for 8 minutes over low heat or until it is very soft, but not browned. Pour the tomatoes into a large bowl and crush them with your hands.
Add the tomatoes to the skillet with the garlic, crushed pepper, salt and pepper.
Bring sauce to a boil; lower the heat and simmer gently for 30 minutes until the sauce is thickened, but not too reduced.

title: brownie apple pie
directions: Peel apples, core and cut into small pieces.
Add cinnamon, flour and sugar; mix well.
Put mixture into pie shell.
Put other pie shell on top.
Close pie by pressing fork along the edge. Poke holes in top of pie. Bake pie for 1 hour at 375°.

title: quick chocolate fudge cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and sugar into large bowl.
Combine water, cocoa and margarine in saucepan; mix well.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over flour mixture; mix well.
Add cinnamon, eggs, buttermilk and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Spread frosting over cake.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions medium fine.
Place in saucepan with hot water to cover.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Drain.
Add vinegar and sugar with salt and celery seed.
Cook 15 minutes over slow fire. Cool and serve.

title: chicken rice supreme(serves 75 to 100)
directions: Bake in large, ungreased baking pans or 9 x 13-inch dishes until golden brown in preheated 350° oven (40 to 60 minutes).

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix ingredients together and roll in wax paper.

title: shady lawn maple fudge
directions: Mix.
Stir only until it starts to boil.
Boil to 238°. Remove from heat.
Cool until just warm.
Add nuts.
Stir until it holds its shape.
Pour into buttered pan.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: petite cheesecakes
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Beat in other ingredients.
Place vanilla wafers in cupcake paper.
Fill 2/3 full of cheese mixture.
Bake 350° for 15-20 minutes.
Before serving, add topping, (cherries, strawberries, blueberries, etc.).

title: italian beef
directions: Place roast in a slow cooker.
Add all ingredients and cook until the beef roast is tender and pulls apart.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix milk and cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise and Good Seasons.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in clams, cheese, peppers and Parmesan.
Spoon into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with vegetable sticks or French bread slices.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Place all ingredients in 2-quart bowl and cover tightly. Microwave 10 minutes at High power, then 4 minutes at 30% power. Remove spices and serve.
Makes four 8-ounce servings.

title: nacho bean dip
directions: Mix refried beans and taco seasoning.
Spread in casserole dish.
Next layer avocado dip, sour cream, chopped chilies, chopped black olives, tomatoes, and green onions.
Top with grated cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Wash, pare and cut potatoes into small pieces.
In 2-quart saucepan, bring water to a boil and add potatoes and onion. Cover and cook over low heat until tender.
Mash slightly.
Do not drain.
Measure the potato mixture and add enough milk to make 5 cups.
Combine melted oleo, flour and parsley and stir into potato mixture.
Cook and stir until thickens.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove from heat and add cheese.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix all in a bowl.

title: salad or dessert
directions: Mix Cool Whip and sour cream.
Drain oranges and pineapple chunks and add to Cool Whip and sour cream.
Add marshmallows and coconut.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: granny's chicken soup
directions: Put cut pieces of chicken in 3-quarts water.
Add seasonings. Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Remove chicken and cool, then debone. Refrigerate broth until fat coagulates; skim off.
Dice meat (discard bones).
Return meat to broth and reheat.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cream sugar and oleo together.
Add 1 cup flour, baking powder and milk.
Mix together until a crumbly mixture.
Sprinkle cornstarch and sugar over peaches in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add boiling water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini egg casserole
directions: Set aside 1/2 cup grated cheese for topping.
Grease or Pam 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or smaller for thicker crust.
Mix all ingredients and spread in dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut up. Mix soup and dip.
If mixture is real thick, you can dilute a little with water.
Place chicken in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with soup mixture.
Sprinkle stuffing on top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: seafood fondue
directions: Drain and rinse shrimp and clams.
Mix all ingredients together and serve in a fondue pot.
Serve with crackers or choice of dippers.

title: split pea soup
directions: Soak peas in water before cooking.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or on high for 5 to 6 hours.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: mom alter's filled mincemeat cookies
directions: Beat together sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Add baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Beat again. Add flour and whole milk alternately.
Beat.
Put in refrigerator for 3
hours.
Take
enough
batter to roll out 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with
or
4-inch round cookie cutter.
Place 1 teaspoon or more
of
mincemeat on 1 round.
Top with another round.
Crimp edges.
Put
on
greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8
to
10 minutes
or until lightly browned.
Excellent!!

title: corned beef stew
directions: In Dutch oven, combine soup, soup can of water, corned beef and undrained vegetables.
Bring to boil.
Stir together the biscuit mix and 1/3 cup water until moistened.
Drop biscuit mix from rounded tablespoonful atop bubbling stew, making 4 to 6 dumplings.
Sprinkle dumplings with dried parsley flakes.
Cover tightly.
Reduce heat; simmer 15 to 18 minutes.

title: liver patties
directions: Grind liver, onion and bread.
Add beaten egg and seasonings. Mix well and drop from tablespoon onto greased frying pan.
When brown on one side, turn and brown on other side.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: In a medium sized bowl mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Put oil in a frying pan and heat.
Stir in dry ingredients in the pan until it is thoroughly blended.
Slowly pour in the milk, stirring constantly until it thickens.
(The amount of milk may vary.)
It is good on biscuits, toast, muffins, etc.

title: rum raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the butter and brown sugar until smooth.
Add egg and mix well.
Dissolve the baking soda in the rum; add to mixture.
Sift salt with the flour and combine with the mixture.
Add the raisins and walnuts; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: steak marinade
directions: Mix in order given.
Pierce the steaks all over; place in Ziploc bag.
Pour marinade over steaks and seal.
Turn bag over once in a while and let set for 2 hours total.
Grill steak, basting with marinade.

title: pastry for single-crust pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together flour, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening until pieces are the size of small peas.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of water over part of the mixture; gently toss with a fork.
Push to one side of bowl.
Repeat until all is moistened. Form dough into a ball.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Add cooked rice to milk and heat to scalding in double boiler. Beat egg yolks with sugar.
Add rice mixture slowly and beat. Pour back in double boiler and cook until thick.
Fold in raisins. Place in buttered casserole; cover with meringue and brown.

title: jack 'n' jill chili
directions: Brown meat, drain and set aside.
Saute onions until tender. Add beef and all remaining ingredients, except beer.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Add beer and simmer for 30 minutes. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serve with saltine crackers. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: microwave shrimp de jonghe
directions: Microwave Velveeta process cheese spread and Pace picante sauce in 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl on High 5 minutes or until Velveeta process cheese spread is melted, stirring after 3 minutes.
Stir in cilantro.
Serve hot with tortilla chips or broiled green, red and yellow pepper wedges.
Makes 3 cups.

title: spice cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Put in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese with ham
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender; drain. In saucepan, melt butter; blend in flour, salt and dash of pepper. Add milk. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly. Add cheese. Stir until melted. Mix cheese sauce with macaroni. Turn into 1 1/2 -quart casserole. Garnish top with rings of bell pepper. Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mom's deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs or egg substitute, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Then stir in 1 cup boiling water.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and spices; set aside.
Cream margarine
and
sugar, add persimmon pulp and baking soda, mix well.
Add egg, mix well.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients then nuts
and
raisins.
Drop
by
teaspoonfuls on lightly greased baking
sheet,
bake
at
350° for 15 minutes.
Store in glass jar, they will keep soft and fresh.
These freeze well too.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Just before serving, add the corn chips and dressing.

title: hot chipped beef appetizer
directions: Top with chopped pecans that have been sauteed in butter. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix stuffing and margarine. Reserve 1/2-cup stuffing mixture. Mix soup, sour cream, squash, carrot and cheese. Add to stuffing mix. Put in 2-quart casserole dish and top with reserved 1/2-cup stuffing mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until hot. Serves 8.

title: cranberry bread
directions: In a bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Make a well in the center of this flour mixture; add the egg, orange juice and butter.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir until well blended.
Grease the sides and bottoms of three 1-pound coffee cans.
fill each with 1/3 batter.
Cover tops lightly with foil.
Place cans on a rack inside a kettle.
Add enough water to come halfway up sides of can.
Cover kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until bread is firm.
More water may be added to kettle if necessary.

title: quick pineapple salad(individual servings)
directions: On lettuce leaves, add 1 slice pineapple.
Put a spoonful of Miracle Whip in pineapple hole.
Add a dab of pineapple juice. Serve cold.

title: orange roughy in orange-mint yogurt sauce
directions: Brush fish fillets with olive oil and sprinkle lightly with ginger and garlic.
Broil 3 to 4-inches from heat source, about 5 minutes or until fish flakes when tested with fork.

title: yams-n-pecans
directions: Beat egg whites until forms stiff peak.
In mixer, beat yams until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Pour yam mixture into casserole and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake uncovered 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dorito chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Layer chicken, Doritos, cheese, onion and corn in greased casserole dish.
Mix soups, milk and tomatoes.
Pour over casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: cloud dough
directions: Mix together flour and salad oil.
Add enough water to make the dough soft and pliable.
If desired, add food coloring.
This dough is soft and elastic and doesn't harden.
Keep it in covered containers or Ziploc plastic bags.
Let the children play with the Cloud Dough; encourage them to think of different ways to describe how it feels.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together.
May add 2 cups miniature marshmallows and coconut.
Cover with Saran Wrap and chill.

title: pizza snack
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Press or roll the biscuit into a 2 1/2-inch circle.
Spoon pizza sauce on biscuit.
Top with pepperoni and cheese.
Place pizza on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 1 serving.

title: monterey rolls
directions: Shred cheese and blend with sherry wine.
Add egg, onion, mustard and salt.
Butter bread and spread with the cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash, dry and stem mushrooms.
Melt butter over low heat.
Add crumbs and cheese and brown lightly, stirring constantly.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Stuff mushroom caps with mixture.
Arrange on cookie sheet.
Center on cooking grill.
Cover kettle and cook 10 to 15 minutes or until mushrooms are tender.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Peel and slice zucchini in 1/2-inch slices.
Place all ingredients in a casserole dish in layers.
Top with extra cheese. Bake at 350° until ingredients are tender.
Season to taste.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix together and store in an airtight container (will fill a 1-gallon jar).
To use, place 1/3 cup of the chocolate mixture in a mug and fill with hot water; stir.

title: happy day cake
directions: Measure words carefully.
Add heaping cup of understanding and forgiveness, using generous amounts of patience.
Cook with gas on the front burner.
Keep temperature low; do not boil Add dash of humor and pinch of love.
Season to taste with spice of life.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and brown sugar; add eggs, then add remaining ingredients.
Roll into walnut size balls. Press with fork.
Bake at 375° until brown around edges.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Add enough flour to make dough stiff. Bake at 350° until done.

title: stella's mystery cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add egg, fruit cocktail and vanilla.
Pour mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Sprinkle ingredients over cream cheese mixture.
Roll tortillas tightly. Chill at least 2 hours.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Serve spirals facing up.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs (light).
Add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter. Line pie pan with plain pastry.
Put in pecans.
Add mixture.
The nuts will rise to the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bob's banana pudding
directions: *Regular Jell-O pudding and pie filling that has to be cooked can also be used.

title: chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package, but do not let stand.
Spoon stuffing across center of 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Arrange chicken breasts on each side of stuffing.
Combine soup, milk and parsley.
Pour over chicken. Cover with foil.
Bake 15 minutes; uncover and bake 10 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Stir sauce before serving.

title: taco pie
directions: Fry down meat and onions and taco sauce.
Then mix Bisquick, milk and eggs together.
Set aside.
In a greased cake pan, spread meat mixture on the bottom, then add Bisquick mixture on top of meat.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Put sour cream, lettuce and tomatoes and cheese on top and serve.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Make up like biscuits.
Roll out and let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 425° or 450° until brown.

title: easter cheese(hruda or sirets)
directions: Pour milk into saucepan and beat eggs in, one at a time.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Add salt and sugar.
Mix slowly.
Do not cook over direct flame since mixture scorches easily.
Use griddle under pan.
Cook over low heat and stir until mixture looks like firm scrambled eggs.
Pour mixture into a cheesecloth bag and tie tightly.
Hang and let drain for about 3 hours or until liquid stops draining.
Carefully remove cheese from bag to avoid breaking.
Store in refrigerator.

title: lizzie's monkey bread
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon. Use scissors to cut each biscuit into 4 pieces. Roll each piece of biscuit in cinnamon-sugar mixture and put into a 10-inch tube pan. Melt margarine in a small saucepan. Add brown sugar and boil. Pour over biscuits. Sprinkle remaining sugar on top. Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool and pull apart and enjoy!!

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine meal, flour and onion.
Add gradually egg and milk. Drop from a spoon into hot oil.
Mixture should be thick.
Cook until golden brown.
Hush puppies can be cooked in same oil as fish was cooked in.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine three dry ingredients together.
Add these slowly.
