Beat until everything is well mixed.
Roll or drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake until bottoms are slightly tan.
Remove immediately and place on paper towels to cool.
Bake approximately 8 minutes at 350°.

title: summer sausage
directions: Knead together every day for 3 days.
Keep refrigerated.
On the fourth day, knead once again, then roll into 6 loaves about 2 inches in diameter.
Place on racks over drip pans.
Bake at 225° for about 5 hours.
Cool completely and wrap well; freeze.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix by hand.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients except egg whites.
Whip egg whites stiff. Fold in corn mixture.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pasta and tuna
directions: Start preparing pasta according to package directions. Meanwhile heat oil over medium heat in pan and saute pepper, mushrooms, onion and basil until onion begins turning translucent. Add oregano and garlic; toss in pan for 1 minute.

title: chicken-broccoli crescent rolls
directions: Blend cream cheese and soup.
Stir in chicken, onion and cooked broccoli.
Spread one can of rolls on cookie sheet.
Next, spread chicken mixture over roll, leaving edges free.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Place other can of rolls over top of this mixture and spread.
Pinch edges and bake at 350° until brown, about 22 to 28 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Mix first 5 ingredients well. Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture. Roll into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour. Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: pineapple torte cake
directions: Bake a 10 x 13-inch sheet cake as directed.
Mix together in bowl the cream cheese, milk, pudding mix and pineapple.
Spoon over cooled cake.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple mixture.
Garnish with nuts and cherries.
Cut in 24 squares.
Keep covered in refrigerator.

title: pralined sweet potatoes and apples
directions: In a large saucepan, parboil potatoes about 20 to 25 minutes or until nearly done, firm, yet soft enough to be pierced with a knife.

Drain and cool; peel and cut into 1/2-inch thick slices. Halve apples lengthwise; core and cut into 1/4-inch slices. Squeeze lemon juice over apples to prevent them from turning brown. Grease a 9-inch quiche dish.
Arrange potatoes and apple slices in alternating rows working from the outside of the dish toward the center and ending with potatoes.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over slices.
Microwave on High, turning the dish every 5 minutes until apples are done.
This can be baked at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pierce with a knife to check if apples and potatoes are cooked.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice.
Set aside.
Coat large skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add pork. Cook until brown on all sides.
Remove pork and drain on paper towels.
Wipe skillet dry.
Return pork to skillet; stir in pineapple juice, broth, vinegar, sugar, soy sauce and ginger. Bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes until pork is tender.
Add pineapple, green pepper and onion. Simmer 4 to 5 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Mix cornstarch and water; pour over pork mixture.
Stir until bubbly.
Serve over rice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tillamook county quiche
directions: Put salmon and cheese into pie crust; spread evenly.
Mix mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth.
Pour over fish and Cheddar.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until center is firm.
Cook up several and freeze extras.
Defrost and warm in oven for 30 minutes.

title: santa's seafood spread
directions: Blend softened cream cheese and milk. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Place in bowl with lettuce leaf.
Serve with small bread chunks or snack crackers of your choice.

title: clay's hot fudge sauce
directions: In double boiler, melt butter and chocolate. Stir in sugar and cocoa. Blend in milk, vanilla and salt. Stir until thickened.
Put in jar with lid and keep in refrigerator.
Reheat in microwave or sit jar in hot water.
Keeps 2 to 3 weeks, if it lasts that long!

title: deviled eggs
directions: Hard boil eggs, let cool.
Cut 12 hard boiled eggs into halves then put yolks through a food mill or mash with fork.
Add other ingredients to egg yolks, then put mixture back into the egg halves.
Garnish with paprika.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Make into small balls and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hearty chicken noodle soup
directions: `In 4-quart saucepan, combine broth, water, carrots, celery, onion and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add All-Bran Noodles and return mixture to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes or until noodles are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in chicken and continue to cook 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat; stir in parsley.
Serve hot; makes 6 servings (1 1/2 cups each).

title: fruit salad deluxe
directions: Stir together Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Add pineapple, nuts and cherries.
Best if made night before.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Cook beef and onion until brown.
Add salt and pepper; drain.
Spread beef and onion in bottom of pie pan.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Thoroughly mix milk, Bisquick and eggs; pour over hamburger mix.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Add all ingredients to broth except chicken. Add cheese and simmer until melts. Add chicken and spaghetti. Put in large casserole dish. Cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mash shrimp with a fork.
Mix dip mix and sour cream.
Add shrimp to this. Chill overnight.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Boil the water and remove from the heat.
Add tea bags and let steep for 15 minutes.
Remove tea bags. Add juices to the tea base.
Heat all the ingredients until piping hot, but do not boil. Add water to taste as the juices and tea base are heating.
The longer you heat this, the better.
Add amounts of juice to your personal taste. Other juices can be substituted from any canned fruit.
Leftover spiced tea can be refrigerated and re-warmed for at least a week.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients. Press into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: tropical chicken salad
directions: Place chicken and celery in a large bowl.
Combine mayo and curry powder; add to chicken mixture and mix well.
Cover; chill for at least 30 minutes.
Before serving, add the pineapple, bananas, oranges and coconut; toss gently.
Serve on salad greens, if desired.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: shrimp and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Prepare rice; keep warm.
Meanwhile, shell and devein shrimp. Rinse with cool water; pat dry.
Cut mushrooms in half or quarters if large.
In nonstick skillet over high heat in 1 tablespoon of oil, cook mushrooms and salt, stirring occasionally.
Remove mushrooms.
In same skillet in 2 teaspoons oil, cook shrimp and garlic until browned.
Cook 1 minute.
In cup mix teriyaki sauce, cornstarch and 3/4 cup water until blended.
To skillet with shrimp, add mushrooms, snap peas and teriyaki mixture.
Boil 1 minute.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate and creamy orange mousse(makes 8 servings)
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt margarine.
Add cocoa, then 2/3 cup sweetened condensed milk, stirring until smooth and slightly thickened.
Pour into medium bowl; cool to room temperature.
Beat in 1 tablespoon orange juice and 1 teaspoon rind.
Fold in half the whipped cream.

title: three flaky pie crusts
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in shortening.
Mix egg, water and vinegar in a cup; beat slightly. Then pour into flour mixture and mix (with fork or pie dough cutter) until you can form one big ball.
Divide into 3 sections. Place each part into a quart size plastic bag.
Mash each flat. Refrigerate extras up to one month in Ziploc bag.

title: classical latvian salad
directions: Mix sour cream with all seasonings and chopped greens.
Place 2/3 lettuce in salad bowl.
Pour dressing and mix gently. Refrigerate for 15 minutes to blend tastes.
Add the other 1/3 lettuce.
Mix lightly and serve at once.
At this point, can add sliced cucumber and/or radishes for color.
But never, never tomato, green pepper or other.

title: individual pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef with onion, green pepper and salt; drain.
Split English muffins; spread with margarine.
Place on baking sheet.
Mix tomato sauce with oregano. Spread on muffin halves (about 1 tablespoon each).
Sprinkle on mushrooms.
Add meat mixture (about 2 tablespoons).
Cover with cheese.
Heat about 15 minutes until cheese melts and muffins begin to brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add salt, soda, eggs, water, flour, pumpkin, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: not edible soapy dough
directions: Mix all ingredients, except water.
Add enough water to make workable dough.
Store in airtight container.

title: mostaccioli (macaroni and cheese)
directions: Cook mostaccioli according to package directions.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add onion, celery and garlic and cook over medium heat until golden.
Add tomato paste, water, seasonings and sugar.
Cover and cook about 20 minutes.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, spread a thin layer of sauce over the bottom.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of the Parmesan cheese.
Layer with half each of the mostaccioli, Ricotta, sauce and half of remaining Parmesan cheese. Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes until hot, bubbly and golden brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spinach cornbread
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook spinach and drain well.
Add spinach to
cornbread mixture
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This cornbread freezes well.

title: zesty broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons margarine in a large heavy skillet over medium heat.
Stir in flour and add water.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well.
Add broccoli and both cheeses to sauce mixture.
Add well beaten eggs.
Pour mixture into flat or oblong baking dish buttered with 1 tablespoon margarine.
Use remaining margarine to butter cracker crumbs used for topping. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: low country shrimp stew(beaufort stew)
directions: Fill large pot 2/3 full with water.
Add seafood seasonings. Bring to boil.
Add sausage (cut into 1-inch pieces).
Boil 20 minutes.
Add corn and boil 15 minutes.
Add shrimp (unpeeled); boil 3 minutes.
Drain and serve warm.
Serves 4.

title: 7-layer casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and drain well.
Layer the hamburg and vegetables in a 2-quart well-greased casserole.
Reverse the layers of vegetables, ending with potatoes.
Season potato and meat layers with salt and pepper to taste.
Mix the tomato soup with the water. Pour over top of layers.
Dot with butter.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves approximately 6.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add taco seasoning.
Let cool.
Layer sour cream, nacho cheese, beef and shredded cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: leftover tetrazzini
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine.
Add soup, water, Cheddar cheese, and sherry.
Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese has melted.
Add meat.
Cook noodles as package directs.
Do not rinse.
Combine noodles with meat mixture.
Pour into shallow buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, or until bubbling.
For a browner top, place under broiler.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Spread bean dip on 10 x 17-inch pan.
Combine beef and taco seasoning.
Spread over bean dip.
Spread picante sauce over the beef.
Sprinkle onion and cheese over the top of everything.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla or tostada chips.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk. Boil 2 minutes. Add vanilla. Let cool.

title: wieners-n-rice
directions: In a heavy frying pan brown wieners and bell pepper.
Add tomatoes and tomato soup; stir and add flour, chili powder, salt and sugar.
Stir and let simmer a few minutes.
Pour over a bed of rice.
Cook rice according to directions on package.

title: frito casserole(makes 8 servings)
directions: Saute onion and garlic.
Add meat and cook until tender.
Add ingredients with water in corn and hominy in order given.

title: american chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, celery and garlic.
Drain after cooking.
Mix spaghetti sauce with tomatoes and soup.
Add hamburger and cooked macaroni.
Can add salt or pepper if needed. Serves 6.

title: easy individual trifles
directions: Split ladyfingers in half lengthwise.
Spread 1 teaspoon raspberry jam on bottom half of each ladyfinger; cover each with top, cut in half crosswise.
Arrange 4 filled halves in each serving dish, drizzle each with 1 teaspoon sherry and 1 teaspoon orange juice.
Combine milk and pudding mix in a 1-quart container; cover tightly; shake 45 seconds.
Pour over ladyfingers.
Chill.
Just before serving, top with whipped cream and almonds.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli just until thawed. Meanwhile, melt 1/2 stick margarine and mix with crushed Ritz crackers. Set aside. Melt in microwave the Velveeta with remaining margarine. Drain broccoli and squeeze out water. Add Velveeta mixture and broccoli together and place in casserole dish. Top with cracker mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate or lemon lust
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients with beater until flaky. Press into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool. Blend next 3 ingredients well and spread on crust carefully. Mix pudding and milk with beater. Pour over top of cheese mixture. Top with more Cool Whip. Garnish with nuts and refrigerate.

title: paprika chicken with sour cream gravy
directions: Mix flour and seasonings.
Coat chicken.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add chicken and cook until browned.
Add soup and onions.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes or until done. Sir in sour cream.
Serve with mashed potatoes or rice if desired. Yield:
Serves 4.

title: tomato cheese casserole
directions: In saucepan, medium heat, saute onions in butter for about 5 minutes.
Stir in croutons and saute for another 3 to 4 minutes. In a well-greased 2-quart casserole, layer croutons with onions and tomatoes, sprinkled with basil and cheese.
Finish with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: light lasagna
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Saute onion and garlic until tender and slightly brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, parsley, salt, pepper, oregano, thyme and marjoram.
Simmer, covered, for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Drain in colander and rinse with cold water.
Cover bottom of a 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish with noodles.
Spread 1/2 of Ricotta on noodles.
Put layer of sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Repeat noodles, Ricotta, sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan. Top with sauce and Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: red snapper victoria
directions: Saute garlic lightly in oil; add vegetables and saute until onion is tender.
Add tomato sauce and stewed tomatoes; sprinkle all with seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Add snapper fillets, cut into serving size portions. Bring to boil; lower heat and simmer for 15 minutes or until fish is firm and flaky.
Can keep warm for 1 to 2 hours.
Serves 4 generously.
Good with cheese bread and salad.
Can also add scallops, shrimp or squid.

title: turkey and biscuits
directions: In saucepan, melt Crisco.
Blend in flour and onion salt. Stir in soups and milk.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly. Stir in cheese until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in turkey and vegetables.
Turn into 2 casseroles.
Cool quickly.
Wrap and freeze.
Place frozen casserole into heated oven.
Bake covered at 425° for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally last 20 minutes.
Prepare quick biscuits.
Place around edge of casserole.
Bake uncovered 15 minutes or until brown.

title: homemade plant food
directions: Mix and use as water on plants once a month.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini until tender; cook together carrots, onion, and oleo.
Mix this with soup and sour cream.
Add 3/4 cup seasoned croutons and stir in zucchini gently.
Cover with 1 cup croutons, bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix in eggs.
Add vanilla and stir in flour.
Add cocoa and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Ice while warm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as instructed on package.
Saute onion in butter.
Cook rice as instructed on box.
Mix all together with Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° until mixture is bubbly.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Combine sugar, water, syrup and cinnamon in saucepan.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Add butter and pecans.
Stir until white.

title: arabian pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides.

Place in square pan (9 x 12-inch). On each chop, place a slice of onion, a slice of tomato and a slice of green pepper (the pepper should be cut in half to form a cup). Fill each pepper cup with cooked rice.
Salt and pepper to taste. Bake in 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.
Add 1 cup water before covering with foil and putting in to bake.

title: no cook strawberry freezer jam
directions: Thoroughly mix fruit and sugar in large bowl. Let stand 10 minutes. Mix water and fruit pectin in small saucepan. Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir into fruit. Continue stirring 3 minutes.
Ladle quickly into six 1 cup containers.
Cover at once with tight lids.
Let stand overnight, then store in freezer.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla together until creamy.
Sift
together
flour,
salt
and soda. Add to creamed mixture. Blend well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake
in
preheated
oven
at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chewies
directions: Dissolve granules in hot water in a bowl.
Stir in egg whites and vanilla.
Combine powdered sugar and next 3 ingredients in a bowl.
Add egg white mixture and beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until blended.
Stir in pecans.
Drop by teaspoon 1-inch apart on greased and floured baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: buttery sourdough pan rolls
directions: In small bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
In large bowl, stir together 2 cups flour, sugar and salt.
Add yeast mixture, 6 tablespoons butter, egg, starter and milk.
Beat with mixer or wooden spoon for 5 minutes, until well blended and smooth. Gradually beat in remaining flour.
Cover and let rise until doubled (about 45 minutes).
Pour 2 tablespoons butter into 9 x 13-inch pan, coating bottom.
Stir dough down, drop into pan by large spoonfuls, making about 15 rolls.
Cover and let rise (about 30 minutes).
Drizzle 2 tablespoons butter over rolls.
Bake in preheated 425° oven (400° glass pan) for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned.
Turn out and pull apart to separate.

title: butter pecan streusel topping
directions: Cover a cookie sheet with foil.
Mix flour and brown sugar. Work in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in pecans.
Spread a thin layer on the sheet and pat down evenly.
Bake 15 minutes or until brown.

title: 1864 savron plantation date and nut cake
directions: Dates must be cut finely and pecans chopped small.
Needs no fat or butter. Nuts will add what's necessary as oil.
Add flour, salt and egg.
Mix well.
Moisten with fruit juice.
Add vanilla. Press fairly dry mixture into loaf pan.
A small 1 1/2 pound bread pan will do.
You can moisten side of pan with oil or line pan with brown paper bag, oiled.
Cook very, very slowly in 250° oven for several hours.
Cool and cut very thinly with hot sharp knife. Very rich.

title: peach pie
directions: Prepare pastry for 9-inch lattice top pie.
Combine sugar, flour, ground nutmeg or cinnamon and dash of salt.
Add to sliced fresh peaches; mix.
Line 9-inch pie plate with pastry; fill.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter or margarine.
(Dash with extra spice, if desired.)
Adjust lattice crust; seal.
Crimp edges.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.
Very good.

title: "eggplant parmesan"
directions: Slice eggplant 1 inch thick.
Soak in cold water for 1 hour. Pat dry with paper towel to absorb water, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place in skillet with four teaspoons olive oil and garlic.
Turn eggplant over once on each side, cook approximately 4 minutes on each side.
Cover with spaghetti sauce and place cover on skillet for one hour.
Sprinkle with fresh grated Parmesan cheese.

title: fast fixin chocolate fudge
directions: In large bowl, mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and butter (do not stir).
Heat in microwave on High until butter is melted (about 4 1/2 to 6 minutes).
Add vanilla and nuts, stirring until smooth.
Kids love to help with this!

title: italian cheese cake
directions: In large bowl, beat the cream cheese until smooth with electric mixer.
Add eggs and sugar, beating until well blended. Add Ricotta, cornstarch, lemon juice and vanilla.
Continue beating until mixture is very smooth (4 to 5 minutes).
Fold in cherries or chocolate chips, if desired.
(Be sure to drain cherries and dry them on paper towels before cutting.)
A handful of chips and 10 cherries are sufficient.
Pour the filling into a 10-inch spring-form pan that has been lined with a graham cracker crust on bottom and an inch or two up on the sides.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour, or until golden and set at the edges. Chill.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Mix all of the above until mixture holds together. *Make sure that the brand of sausage has a lot of grease, otherwise the sausage balls will be dry tasting.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown and drain beef and onions. Combine all ingredients and spread in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix approximately 2 minutes and pour into well-greased and floured oblong pan, 9 x 12 x 2-inches.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Fold and coat pecan halves. Place on cookie sheet. Do not let pecans touch. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Simmer dates, sugar and margarine on low heat until smooth. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Form into balls and roll in coconut.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add egg, milk and butter; then add blueberries.
Fill a greased pan.

title: spanish hamburg rice
directions: In 3-quart casserole, crumble beef.
Microwave on High 6 to 9 minutes; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and microwave on High 12 to 15 minutes.
Stir well.
Let stand, covered, for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: baked shrimp
directions: Melt butter and olive oil together.

title: apricot zucchini jam
directions: Cook zucchini until clear in a little water.
Add sugar, pineapple, lemon juice and MCP.
Boil hard for 6 minutes.
Add jello and stir.
Jar and seal.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Layer bananas on top.
On top of this, spread pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with cherries and chopped nuts. Refrigerate overnight.
Keep refrigerated.
*No Baking*

title: incredible "mall-style" cinnamon rolls
directions: Let frozen bread dough thaw and rise until double.
Punch down dough and pat loaves together.
Roll out dough to 16 x 10-inch rectangle.
Dough should be 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Spread top of dough with all but 2 tablespoons of melted butter.
Sprinkle sugars, cinnamon, nuts and raisins evenly over dough.
With back of spoon, gently pat sugars into dough.
With long side of dough, roll up jelly-roll fashion, pulling dough towards you as you roll up. Cut into 9 even slices.
Rolls will be large.

title: french apple pie
directions: This pie can be
made in a deep dish pottery pie plate. Make pastry for the
bottom only.
Spread half of the 4 ingredients on the
unbaked
pie
crust.
Next
fill the crust with quartered apples.
Add
the rest of the sugar mixture and pour on 1/2 cup cream
evenly.
Bake on bottom shelf for 15 minutes at 450°, then move
to
the
middle
shelf
and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cover meat with water.
Add salt and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 3 hours.
Remove meat from stock.
Let stock cool slightly; skim excess fat from surface.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: williamsburg inn cookies
directions: Beat egg white. Add sugar gradually, then other ingredients in order given. Drop on greased pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apple dumpling
directions: Peel and slice apples.
In a 9 x 13 inch baking dish, put 3/4 c. sugar, 1/2 stick butter and water, set in 325° oven to heat.
Roll out 10 canned biscuits on floured board about the size of a saucer or a little larger.
Hold dough in hand and fill with apples.
Add 1 tsp. sugar and pinch together.
Put pinched side down in hot liquid.
Put pat of butter on each dumpling and sprinkle another 3/4 c. sugar on top with cinnamon.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon, beef and onion.
Drain.
Mix rest of ingredients with browned ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Stir together first four ingredients.
Add brown sugar and oats.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir vigorously until well moistened.
Drop by level tablespoon 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated oven for 12 minutes at 350°.
Remove at once and cool.

title: lake charles dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve immediately or refrigerate. Delicious with chips or as a dip for raw vegetables.

title: fruit punch slush
directions: Mix fruit punch, water and strawberry Bullet in large container and freeze.
When frozen, scoop into glass and mix half and half with 7-Up.

title: oven barbecued ribs
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place ribs in a shallow pan, meaty side up.
Cover with lemons and onions.
Roast for 30 minutes.
While meat is cooking, combine rest of ingredients and bring to a boil. Pour mixture over meat.
Reduce oven heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour until tender, basting every 15 minutes.

title: six 3's ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, milk and cream and freeze in either ice cream freezer or regular freezer, until it thickens.
Add fruits and return to freezer until it is firm.
Don't dry to mix it altogether and freeze.
The fruit gets icy before the ice cream mixture freezes.

title: hawaiian fruit pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch, then add crushed pineapple (juice included).
Mix thoroughly and cook for about 5 minutes, stirring constantly until thickened.
Stir in jello, stirring until dissolved; cool.
Add cherries and nuts.
Line baked pie shells with sliced bananas, sides and bottom.
Fill with jello mixture and top with Cool Whip; refrigerate.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Set aside.
Beat egg yolks. Blend in lemon peel, juice and milk. Add sugar, flour and salt. Beat until smooth.
Fold into whites. Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole.
Place casserole into pan of very hot water (1-inch deep). Bake 45 to 50 minutes. Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Brown ground beef. Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Remove from heat.
Combine cream cheese, cottage cheese, sour cream and green onions.
Spread half of noodles in ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover with cheese mixture and remaining noodles.
Cover with meat mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in boiling water.
Stir in softened cream cheese.
Blend on low speed of mixer until smooth.
Drain 1 small can crushed pineapple, saving juice.
Add cold water to juice to total 1 cup.
Stir in jello mixture.
Add drained pineapple and chopped pecans.
Stir and refrigerate until set.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together until smooth, then spread over cooled cake.

title: caesar salad
directions: Tear romaine lettuce in small pieces; add chopped green onions.
When ready to serve, add bacon bits, croutons and dressing.
Toss and serve.

title: peach sauce
directions: In a 1-quart microwaveproof casserole dish, combine water, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla.
Microwave on High power for 2 to 4 minutes or until boiling rapidly. Stir in peaches. Chill.
Serve over ice cream, cake, pancakes or waffles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In medium-large ovensafe dish layer noodles and cheese, starting with noodles, ending with cheese.
Last layer of cheese should completely cover noodles.
Add egg and milk mixture (beaten well).
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese is golden brown and no more liquid is visible when pressed with fork.

title: chicken and stove top
directions: Prepare Stove Top according to package directions.
Place uncooked breasts in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour soups over chicken; top with stuffing.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour. This is an easy recipe for those busy days.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Stew chicken until meat is very tender.
Remove meat from bones and cut into bite size pieces.
Reserve broth for cooking spaghetti.
Cook spaghetti until tender.
Saute onion, celery and green pepper in butter for about 5 minutes or until tender.
Add soup and milk, mushrooms, pimiento and olives.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place grated cheese on top and bake in moderate oven until brown on top.

title: eggs and cheese on toast
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender.
Blend in cornstarch. Slowly add milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add chunks of Velveeta cheese (to taste) and let melt thoroughly.
Add well beaten eggs.
Stir until cooked.
Serve over toast.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter until smooth. Gradually add milk. Blend well.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into 9-inch graham cracker crust, baked and cooled.
Top with 1 cup crushed peanuts.
Freeze until ready to serve.
Before serving, top with chocolate syrup.

title: bread pudding
directions: Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs in large bowl; add sugar, salt and butter and mix well.
Add warm milk and vanilla.
Add bread crumbs and pour into buttered pan. Sprinkle generously with nutmeg and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or so.
Put a silver knife in the pudding about an inch from the edge.
If blade comes out clean, pudding is done.
Serve warm with lemon sauce.

title: cabbage chowder
directions: Put butter, cabbage and potato in water and cook until tender. Add milk and Swiss cheese.
Heat just enough to melt cheese. Salt and pepper to taste.
Very good.
Can be frozen.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Put strawberries and sugar in pot and bring to boil.
Cook at boiling point for 10 to 15 minutes or until thickened.

title: shrimp pizza
directions: Spread cream cheese mixed with 1/2 cup milk onto a round flat platter to resemble pizza dough.
Spread cocktail sauce to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Sprinkle cheese, onions and pepper on and top with shrimp and black olives.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and parsley.
Chill.
Serve with favorite crackers or corn chips. Serves 12.

title: the black-eyed pea's cheese broccoli soup
directions: Steam broccoli until tender.
Place half-and-half and water in the top of a double boiler; add cheese, salt and pepper.
Heat until all the cheese is melted.
Add steamed broccoli.

title: extra good fresh apple cake
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon, salt and soda together.
Cream oil and sugar; add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture.
Stir in apples, nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for about an hour.

title: orange rolls
directions: Add 4 more cups flour.
Turn onto floured board and knead until elastic and sticky.
Divide in 2 parts.
Roll out flat and spread with melted butter or margarine.
Cut into strips and twist into desired shapes.
Place on ungreased pan; cover and let rise.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
While still warm, brush with glaze.

title: pumpkin chips
directions: Peel pumpkin and cut into thin pieces, 1/2-inch square.
Add sugar and lemon juice (save the skins).
Let stand overnight. Boil until the chips look clear and transparent.
Take chips out and boil syrup until
it thickens a little.
Cut up lemon skins and boil separately until soft.
Add the chips and lemon skins to
the thickened soup and bring to a boil.
Place in jars and seal. Yields 6 to 8 pints.

title: mock tamales
directions: Combine cheeses and onions.
Divide evenly between tortillas, placing mixture in the center of each.
Fold bottom over the cheese, then the sides, then the top down.
Wrap each one individually in foil.
Grill or bake until cheese is melted and hot.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add the can of frozen orange juice.
When melted, add 1 c. cold water plus juice from crushed pineapple.
Take out 1/2 c. of this jello and save.

title: countryside chicken bake
directions: Place rice in greased 8 x 12-inch casserole.
Cover with combined vegetables and seasoning.
Combine soup and mayonnaise and mix well.
Gradually add water to soup mixture.
Mix well until blended.
Pour half soup mixture over rice and vegetables. Top with chicken.
Pour remaining soup mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender and rice is cooked. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: city slicker beans
directions: Combine all beans with onion and garlic.
In small bowl, stir together remaining ingredients.
Pour over bean mixture and stir until beans are coated with sauce.
Pour mixture into a 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Remove cover and cook for another 15 minutes or until mixture is bubbling.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix and beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch (or larger) pan.
Mix rice and soup mixture.
Spread evenly in pan.
Lay chicken breasts and legs on top of rice.
Mix soups and 1 can water.
Pour over top.
Add second cup of water as needed.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Serves 8.

title: pear, cashew and cherry salad
directions: Break romaine hearts into bite size pieces.
Dress lightly and toss to coat.
Add pear chunks, dried cherries and top with cashews.

title: sour cream lemon pie(serves 6)
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, lemon rind, juice, egg yolks and milk in saucepan over medium to medium-high heat until thick.
Stir in butter and cool to room temperature.
Stir in sour cream and pour into pie shell.
Cover with whipped topping and chill. Refrigerate leftover pie.

title: chow mein
directions: Brown meat in oil and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add celery, onion and soy sauce and simmer 10 minutes more.
Add salt, pepper, vegetables and water chestnuts and simmer 5 to 8 minutes.
Mix flour and sugar with water to make a paste and add to thicken.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except crab meat.
Mix thoroughly.
Add crab meat and mix well.
Form into 1 dozen cakes. Deep fry at 350° about 3 to 5 minutes, turning once until golden brown.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut beef into 6 pieces. Sprinkle with seasoning salt. Brown in skillet for about 8 minutes. Layer potatoes, carrots, onions and beef in slow cooker. Combine tomatoes and gravy. Pour over beef and vegetables. Cover. Cook on low 7 to 9 hours. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and mix thoroughly.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until custard is set.
Looks and tastes like coconut pie.

title: potato cheese loaf
directions: Combine in pan:
milk, cheese, salt, sugar and butter.
Heat until cheese melts.
Remove from heat; stir in potato flakes.
Cool to lukewarm.
In large mixing bowl, sprinkle yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar over warm water.
Dissolve, then stir in milk-cheese mixture. Beat in egg.
Beat in flour to make soft sticky dough.
Knead 5 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl.
Let rise.
Punch down. Knead.
Shape into loaf.
Let rise again until double.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the Crisco oil, sugar, wine vinegar, salt, paprika, celery seed and onion powder.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour or more.

title: granny's rolls
directions: Mix warm milk with Crisco, sugar and salt.
Let set until cools.
Mix egg, yeast and flour.
Knead, then cover with wet cloth.
Do over 3 times a day.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: great-grandma devries' sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and salt.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Roll out dough and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: squash
directions: Steam squash and onion; cook until tender.
Drain and add next 5 ingredients to taste; mix well.

title: chicken or turkey a la king
directions: Saute green pepper in oleo; add mushrooms.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat; add the remaining ingredients and heat over low to medium heat until thoroughly heated and thickened.
Serve over drop biscuits or rice.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and 1/2 of flour; beat well.
Add melted margarine and beat in rest of flour.
Cover and place in refrigerator; leave there for at least 2 hours. Shape into rolls while cold and let rise until doubled (about 1 1/4 hours).
Bake in a 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: bob's ala supreme cake
directions: Bake cake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Cut and remove a 5-inch piece from the end of cake.
Slice the remainder 1-inch thick.
Lay it in the cake pan as you cut it on the flat side, leaving a slight space between pieces.
Cook jello pudding; pour over the cake.
Put peaches over the pudding.
Put a layer of Cool Whip over the peaches.
Put pie filling over the Cool Whip.
Put a thin layer of Cool Whip over the cherry or blueberry pie filling. Put 1/2 cup of pecan halves on the Cool Whip (optional).

title: chicken and potatoes
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter for 5 minutes.
Add flour and cook a few minutes.
Add water to make a loose gravy.
Add the chicken and cook for 1 hour on low heat.
Add cut up potatoes. Season to taste.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese with melted margarine; stir in flour, paprika and salt.
Mix well.
Wrap 1 teaspoon of mixture around each olive, covering the olive completely.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
May be frozen before baking.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut peppers in half lengthwise.
Remove stem ends and seeds.
Bring 4 cups water to boil in medium saucepan.
Add peppers and simmer for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Place in 9-inch square baking dish and set aside.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, stirring to remove large lumps. Add oil and next 3 ingredients, mixing until smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: "v-8" fat-free chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place chicken on cookie sheet.
Cook 20 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Let cook and skin.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken, debone and cut in small pieces.
Take part of Ritz crackers, mix with 1/2 of margarine.
Layer on bottom.
Place chicken over Ritz; mix sour cream, soup and poppy seed together and pour over chicken.
Then put balance of Ritz next and pour margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until brown.

title: cheese straws
directions: Let grated cheese and margarine stand until it is room temperature or soft enough to work with.
Mix well. Add flour and salt.
Mix well. Roll into rolls.
Keep in refrigerator overnight. Slice and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pteradactyl wings
directions: In large bowl, combine mustard and vegetable oil.
Add wings, tossing to coat evenly.
Dip wings into cornflake crumbs.
Place on rack in roasting pan.
Bake at 400°, turning occasionally, for 30 minutes or until done.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry yogurt layer cake
directions: Combine cake mix, egg whites and water in a large mixing bowl; beat on high speed for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into 2 (9-inch) round cake pans, coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until toothpick, inserted in middle, comes out clean. Cool on wire racks 15 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.

title: aunt joan's church windows
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter in a double boiler.
Be sure no water gets in the chocolate.
Place marshmallows in a bowl. Pour melted chocolate over the marshmallows.
Thoroughly coat the marshmallows with the chocolate.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar on a long piece of aluminum foil.
Roll coated marshmallows into a log.
Wrap foil completely around the log.
Refrigerate until solid. Cut the log into about 1/2-inch slices.
Serve.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter and shortening together. Add sugars and beat until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time. Mix dry ingredients together and add to the creamed mixture. Add cream and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Heat the milk.
Mix together the flour, cocoa, salt and sugar. Add 3 cups milk to this mixture to make a paste.
When milk is hot, add paste and stir until thick and begins to boil.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Mix sugar and powdered cinnamon in saucepan.
Stir in Pet milk. Boil to 236° or until a soft ball is formed when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add pecans.
Pull apart with hands.

title: almond flavored cookies
directions: Cream oil, sugar, eggs and extract.
Add flour and baking powder.
Stir thoroughly; shape into balls.
Dip in sprinkles and bake on cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken enchilada bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish.
Combine chicken, cheese, beans, olives, salsa and garlic powder in large mixing bowl; blend well.
Put mixture in a casserole dish.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Arrange sliced peaches in a 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1 cup sugar and lemon juice.
Heat in 400° oven while preparing shortcake.
Mix flour, baking powder, 1 tablespoon sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening , add 1/2 cup milk and beaten egg. Don't overmix, stir and spread over peaches.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: fresh limeade
directions: In a large pitcher, combine lime juice and water. Add sugar. Stir well to dissolve sugar. Add ice cubes.
Pour into glasses garnished with lime slices.
Makes 6 (8 ounce) servings.
Per 8 ounce serving contains 90 calories, 4 g fat, .54 mg sodium and 12 mg vitamin C.

title: norma's spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown together first 2 ingredients.
Add
next 7 ingredients. Simmer for one hour.
Cook spaghetti until tender.
Drain and add to meat mixture.
Pour into a casserole and cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly.

title: korozott (cottage cheese spread)
directions: In a bowl, beat cottage cheese and butter until creamy. Add salt,
pepper,
paprika,
mustard,	onion,	caraway seed, anchovies
and capers.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: round steak roll-ups
directions: Cut steaks the long way in 3 or 4-inch strips (you should get 4 from 1 large package).
Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
Lay each strip on top of 2 slices of bacon and sprinkle with soup mix. Roll them up and fasten with toothpicks.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours or so.

title: big mama's tea cakes
directions: Mix ingredients; shape into cookies.
Sprinkle sugar over top of cookies.

title: melon salsa
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl and mix well. Refrigerate. The salsa is excellent with any grilled seafood, pork or chicken.

title: chicken curry surprises
directions: Combine the chicken with the chopped apple, green onion, peanuts, mayonnaise, curry powder and hot sauce in large bowl, blending well.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 4 hours or until chilled.

title: mom's meatballs and cabbage
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients to make the meatballs.
While doing so, heat the cranberry, Arturo and marinara sauces and the cabbage together.
Add the meatballs and simmer for 2 to 2 1/2 hours on low heat.
Serve with rice.
Yum!

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit in a large bowl.
Add marshmallows.
Stir mayonnaise into whipped cream and pour over fruit.
Mix gently.

title: cheesy potato supreme
directions: Melt 1/2 cup margarine in 3-quart casserole.
Combine potatoes, onion, cheese, sour cream and soup; place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; bake covered.
Saute corn flake crumbs in remaining margarine and spread on top of mixture.
Bake for additional 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: bonbons
directions: Combine butter, milk, sugar and coconut.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Make into bite-size balls and chill again.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin; dip balls in mixture.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: fig pickles
directions: 1st Day:
Bring sugar and vinegar to boil.
Drop in figs and cook 20 minutes.
Pour into bowl and let set overnight.

title: snow flakes(cream cheese cookies)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and cream cheese well.
Add sugar gradually.
Continue to cream.
Beat in egg yolk and vanilla extract.
Add flour slowly, then salt and cinnamon.
Fill a cookie press; on a cookie sheet put cookies on and decorate.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: quick chicken parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken patties in glass baking dish.
Put 2 to 3 tablespoons sauce on each patty and spread it around.
Cover thickly with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Make extras for sandwiches the next day.

title: jacob's nutty shake
directions: You need a big bowl.
Put the peanut butter in the bowl.
Pour in the milk and mix with a fork.
Put in the ice cream.
Mix with an eggbeater until everything is foamy.
Pour into 4 glasses. Serve.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Return to heat and mix in chili seasoning, chili, sour cream and tomatoes. Pour hamburger mixture into crock-pot and add Velveeta cheese. Stir occasionally until cheese is melted.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet over moderate heat, stirring until pinkness disappears.
Stir in cheese, potted meat, oregano, sage, fennel, Italian herbs and garlic powder.
Add tomato sauce. (At this point, mixture may be refrigerated for later serving.)

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Layer all of the ingredients as listed.
Cover dish and bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: cherry dream squares
directions: Combine cake mix, 6 tablespoons margarine and 1 cup rolled oats.
Mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
To remaining crumbs, add 1 egg, mix until well blended.
Press into prepared pan and pour cherry pie filling over crust.
Spread to cover evenly.

title: grilled squash or zucchini
directions: Wash and cut off ends of squash or zucchini; slice lengthwise, making slices about 1/8-inch thick.
Rub lightly with vegetable oil.
Roll in cornmeal (this will be a light coating).
Place on a hot grill; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Also use other seasonings, if desired.
Cook until soft to the touch.
The amount you prepare will depend on size of squash and number of people being served.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Put cherry pie filling and pineapple into a 9.5 x 13.5 x 2-inch baking dish, then put white sugar on top of that.
Put dry cake mix on top of that.
Do not stir.
Melt butter or margarine. Put on top of cake mix.
Do not stir.
Put chopped pecans on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until it's golden brown.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix juices shortly before serving.
Add berries and ginger ale (rum as desired).
Pour over ice in punch bowl.
Garnish with orange and mint sprigs.

title: sky-high strawberry pie
directions: Melt frozen berries in saucepan.
When almost boiling, add the soaked gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Put in fridge and when cold, but not set, pour into 2-quart mixer bowl.
(Be sure beaters and bowl are very cold.)
Add sugar, whites, lemon juice and flavoring.
Beat on high for at least 15 minutes or until very high and fluffy.
Lightly fold in 1/2 cup Cool Whip*.

title: baked chicken
directions: Spray casserole or baking dish with Pam.
Place skinless, boneless chicken breasts in the bottom.
Top with cheese.
Spoon soup over top and pour milk over soup.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing mix.
Spread over top and cover with lid or foil.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: fiesta turkey pie
directions: Cook turkey until no longer pink. Stir in salsa. Press roll dough onto bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate to form crust. Spread meat mixture over crust; sprinkle with cheese. Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 350° or until browned.

title: vodka slush
directions: Dissolve sugar and Jell-O with tea while tea is still warm. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Freeze in covered container.
Spoon into glass and mix with Sprite to consistency of "slush."
Mixing by the glass is best.

title: creamy swiss and broccoli soup
directions: Boil ham in water for 10 minutes.
Add broccoli; cook until tender.
Gradually add milk to flour; stir well to blend. Gradually add milk mixture to ham mixture, stirring constantly, until mixture slightly thickens.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add cheese and seasonings.
Cook until cheese melts slightly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: zesty cauliflower(for microwave cooking)
directions: Wrap cauliflower in wax paper.
Cook on Full power for 6 minutes per pound.
Place in casserole.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Top with sauce and sprinkle with cheese.
Cook on Full power for 2 to 3 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Crush the cookies. Melt butter and mix with crumbs.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boil and stir in peach jello.
Cool completely.
When cooled, stir in buttermilk and Cool Whip. Chill.
Pecans can be added.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes until tender; peel.
Shred potatoes. Combine potatoes with sour cream, 1 cup cheese, carrot, onion, parsley, salt, dill weed and pepper.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese; sprinkle on paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven 30 to 40 minutes.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into loaf and bake at 350°.

title: crab stuffed tomatoes
directions: Chop onion, celery and bacon finely and fry in butter with the bread crumbs until the onion is tender.
Flake crab meat.
Add crab to the onion mixture and stir in lightly beaten eggs.
Season to taste.
Cut the tops off the tomatoes and scoop out seeds.
Stuff with the crab mixture, sprinkle with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve on hot toast.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in gumdrops and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix like meat loaf and shape into 3 rolls. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Unwrap and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 1 hour. When they are cool, re-wrap and refrigerate.

title: rhinoceros in orange sauce
directions: In a large heavy saucepan brown the rhinoceros in the butter. Add the garlic, onions, parsley and seasonings and saute until the onions are golden.

title: brunt's favorite chicken enchilada casserole
directions: *Choose your own strength, we use Old El Paso medium.

title: hershey chocolate pie
directions: Melt bars in double boiler.
Add marshmallows and milk.
Mix until well blended and pour in crust.
When cool, top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Garnish with shaved chocolate.

title: pickled mushrooms in brine
directions: Clean the mushrooms and slice in quarters or thirds, according to their size. Combine 1 tablespoon salt, vinegar, water, rosemary, a few peppercorns, bay leaves, onion and garlic in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Cook 15 minutes.

title: green bean and bacon casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Mix all of the ingredients together and heat covered in microwave for 5 minutes.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Melt butter or margarine in skillet. Saute mushrooms 5 minutes, until soft. Add beef broth, red wine and gravy browning; keep at a low boil for about 15 minutes, until reduced to desired amount of sauce (watch closely; liquid will reduce quickly at the end). Serve as a side dish or spoon over steak.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Beat milk, cream and egg yolk together.
Put in microwave on High for 2 minutes, then add brown sugar, butter and flour and cook on High.
Check every 2 minutes and stir until thick, about 8 minutes.
Makes one pie; double for 2 pies!

title: cheesy pineapple dessert
directions: Combine crumbs and butter.
Reserve 1/2 cup of the mixture. Firmly press remaining crumb mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Set aside.

title: pig lick 'n cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, eggs and mandarin oranges (not drained) and mix well.
Pour into 3 cake pans and bake according to directions on cake box.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well together.
Add blackberries and nuts; stir gradually.
Bake in layers at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or oblong for 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Mix squash, onion, soup, 1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese, mushrooms and sour cream.
Crumble crackers and add to other ingredients.
Put remainder of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: steve's fruit juice slush
directions: Squeeze fruit; remove seeds.
Put juice with pulp in blender. Add sugar, vanilla and protein powder.
Add ice; blend on high. Stop intermittently to stir.
Blend to a slush.
Pour into glasses and enjoy.

title: heavenly hash browns
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
May be frozen.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Cream sugars, margarine, vanilla and eggs.
Sift and add flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add remaining ingredients. Drop by large tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: home-style scalloped potatoes
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper until blended. Gradually add milk. Bring to boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until sauce thickens. Place half of potatoes in a greased 3-quart baking dish. Pour half of sauce over potatoes. Repeat layers. Bake uncovered at 350° for 70 minutes or until potatoes are tender and top is lightly browned.
Serve immediately. Yield: 8 servings.

title: tater tots pieces
directions: Cut slices of cheese into thirds.
Cut bacon slices into halves and cook until still limber (about half cooked).
Wrap each Tater Tot with cheese and 1/2 strip of bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.
This makes a lot.
Be sure to place on greased cookie sheets.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: fruit swirl coffee cake
directions: Beat first 7 ingredients in large bowl on low speed until blended.
Beat on high 3 minutes, stir in flour.
Spread 2/3 of batter in greased jelly roll pan.
Spread pie filling over the batter.
Drop remaining dough by tablespoon on top.
Bake at 350° until light brown 45 minutes.
Drizzle glaze while warm.

title: reesee cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and roll into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet, not too close together.
Press a Hershey Kiss in the center of each cookie.
Bake at 350° for minutes only. Let cool on sheet before removing.

title: nutty buddy pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese, milk, peanut butter and Cool Whip. Pour into pie shells.
Drizzle top with Hershey syrup.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Cover pies and freeze.
Keep in freezer until ready to serve.

title: orange jello fluff salad stuff
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Let set one hour in fridge. Save one teaspoon jello to sprinkle on top for garnish.

title: apple bread(1 large loaf)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 minutes, then turn on rack to cool.
May use more apples, if desired.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook meat, onion and garlic until meat is browned.
Drain off fat.
Stir in the undrained tomatoes and next 4 ingredients. Cover.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring often.

title: annie's cabbage soup
directions: Prick sausages and bring to boil in water to cover.
Boil 25 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Slice 1/2-inch thick.
In large pot, put sausages.
Cut cabbage as if for coleslaw (1/4-inch wide, 3-inch lengths).
Add to pot.
Add onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until cabbage strips are soft.
Easy and delicious. Better next day.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with margarine.
Mix onion, cabbage, celery soup, mayonnaise, egg, pepper and salt all together well.
Spread in casserole dish, then top with cheese. Then add cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Mix butter with garlic, chives and parsley flakes.
Wrap butter in wax paper and freeze for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: walnut-butterscotch fudge
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with foil, letting ends extend above pan on 2 sides.

title: crock-pot chili #2
directions: Brown meat in small amount of oil in a large skillet. Add onion and garlic; cook until softened. Drain.
Put in slow cooker. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low 8 to 10 hours.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Mix milks, cheese, butter, eggs, salt and pepper together, then macaroni. Place mixture in crock-pot. Layer some cheese strips on top. Cook in crock-pot 3 hours on low.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Mix together and serve with apples or pears.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat until light.
Whip sour cream and fold into egg mixture.
Add raisins, nutmeg, salt and lemon juice and mix.

title: wilted cole slaw
directions: Mix vegetables together and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar. Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan and boil 3 minutes.
Pour over cabbage mixture and mix well.
Let sit in refrigerator in tightly covered container for 24 hours before serving.
Shake container occasionally to mix.
Will keep 2 weeks.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Melt butter and add coconut.
Brown over medium heat.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add eggs to butter and coconut mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients into large bowl.
The potatoes, eggs, onions, pickles and mayonnaise.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Chill, if desired, or eat while hot.

title: italian chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Pour 1/3 Italian dressing over chicken. Add potatoes, carrots, butter, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Cover.
Cook on 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters; roll into balls in sugar and cinnamon.
Place 1/2 into greased Bundt pan.
Boil brown sugar and margarine for 1 minute only.
Pour 1/2 over biscuits; add remaining biscuits and pour in the rest.
Bake 35 minutes.
Invert and allow to sit for 10 minutes.

title: chicken soup(low in fat)
directions: In a large cooker or pot, on medium-high heat, pour in 6 cups water.
Add the peeled diced potatoes.
Cook while preparing the chicken in the microwave as directed on package.
Also while chicken is cooking, blend in the blender the tomatoes and picante sauce.
When chicken is done, cut into cubes.
Add the Ramen noodles and the sauce packages to the pot.
After noodles soften, stir in chicken and tomato mix.
Lower heat to simmer; heat until the potatoes are tender.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Brown onions, celery and peppers in shortening.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer until done.
Add cooked chicken.
Cook spaghetti.
Pour sauce over spaghetti.
Bake for 15 or 20 minutes.
Cover with grated cheese and heat.

title: onion casserole
directions: Grease 1 1/2-quart dish. Separate onions into rings. Put in casserole dish. Mix cheese and soup; melt. Can add a little milk. Pour over onions. Put potato chips on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until brown on top.

title: egg foo young
directions: Boil for 5 minutes.

title: fruit and nut bars
directions: In small bowl, mix wafer crumbs and butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with pecans and cherries, arranging cherries in decorative pattern.
Pour condensed milk over top.
Allow to set a few minutes.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cut while warm.
Be sure not to overcook.
Good to make at Christmas.

title: granny mangham's chicken and dumplins
directions: Place chicken in large pot or pressure cooker with enough water to cover.
When done, remove the skin and bones.
Add onion to broth.
Make a stiff biscuit dough.
Roll out on floured board until very thin.
Cut into 3-inch strips.
Drop into boiling broth. Reduce heat and simmer a few minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste. If broth is too thin, add a little flour to thicken.
"I always hold my hand over the pot and say, Lord, this is all I can do for it.
Now, you do the rest."
This makes enough for "dinner on the grounds."

title: bonnie's sheet cake
directions: Sift sugar, flour, soda and salt in bowl.
In pan on stove, bring oleo, water and cocoa to boil.
Pour over dry ingredients and add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: ottolene's pot roast
directions: Brown meat on all sides in oil in Dutch oven or large round boiler.
Add tomato sauce, water, onions, other sauce and seasonings.
Cover; simmer over low heat for 3 to 4 hours.
Add water if needed.
Add carrots and potatoes about an hour before serving.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift soda and flour.
Cream sugar, butter and Crisco until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at the time, beating well. Add vanilla.
Add flour mixture with sour cream.
Beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Pour into large greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool in pan for about 10 minutes.
Frost with Caramel Icing.
Is also good with fruit.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Chop fine onion, celery and green pepper.
Brown with ground meat.
Add soup, water, catsup, relish and Worcestershire sauce. Cook in Dutch oven or electric skillet approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: texas chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix flour and sugar well.
Add next four ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add to dry mixture, then add eggs and stir well.
Mix together buttermilk, soda and vanilla and pour into batter.
Pour in large greased oblong pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 425°.

title: raw potato pancakes
directions: Wash, pare and shred potatoes.
Put in ice water to prevent discoloration.
Let stand 10 minutes and drain.
Mix potatoes with eggs and dry ingredients.
Heat shortening in frypan, having shortening 1/8-inch deep.
Drop pancake batter in by spoonfuls and spread around.
Fry until well browned on one side; turn and brown on other side.
Makes about 8 medium sized pancakes.

title: old time watermelon pickles
directions: Eat the watermelon. Save the rind.
Keep in refrigerator, then cut rind into 1-inch pieces.
Paring the green and red from the rind, place in large pot. Cover with a mixture of salt and water. Cover and store in refrigerator overnight.
The next day, put spices in small cheesecloth bag. Add vinegar and sugar to boiling water.
After the sugar is dissolved, boil gently for 5 minutes. Add drained watermelon rind and boil gently for 45 minutes. Remove spice bag.
Spoon rind into hot sterile jars. Seal at once.
Wait 4 weeks before using.

title: candied yams
directions: Put all ingredients in large pot and bring to slow boil.
Peel yams and slice lengthwise.
Be sure each slice is coated when put into pot with above ingredients so it won't turn dark.
Cook without lid until tender.
(Recipe can be doubled, tripled, etc.)

title: hamburger cubill-style
directions: Divide into 4 equal portions.
Form into patties.
Broil 7 minutes, turning once.
Split 4 egg twist buns (or your choice). Place a lettuce leaf, burger, tomato and onion slice on each bun.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese well, add sugar, beat well, then add eggs one at a time, add vanilla, salt and flour.
Put in a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: almond stuffed dates with bacon
directions: Put an almond in each date.
Wrap a piece of bacon around each stuffed date and secure with a toothpick.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Place dates on foil and bake in preheated 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
Remove to rack or paper towel; drain.
Serve warm.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: philadelphia cream cheese cake
directions: Cream cheese and sugar, 1 pkg at a time.
Add sour cream, eggs and vanilla.
Blend together well.
Do not grease pan. Spread crescent rolls on bottom and
the sides a little in a 9 x 13 glass baking dish.
Pour cream cheese mixture on top of crescent rolls and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: wassail bowl
directions: Combine cider and sugar in a large saucepan.
Tie allspice, cloves and cinnamon sticks in a porous cloth; add cider.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove spices and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Garnish with orange and lemon slices.
Serve hot.

title: taco salad
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, crumble beef.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cover.
Microwave at High 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir after 3 minutes.
Drain well.
Add chili beans.
Cover.
Microwave at High 6 to 9 minutes until hot.
Set aside and keep warm.

title: brown sugar cherry cookies
directions: Mix together first 8 ingredients.
Stir 1 cup chopped cherries into dough.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Boil water and Sure-Jell for 3 minutes.
Pour in strawberries. Mix and fill jars.

title: a happy family
directions: Prepare any size home container by lining it with one Bible for each part of the first 3 ingredients.
Place all ingredients before the Lord for supervision, then combine in a mixing bowl in order listed.
(Children may need occasional light whipping to avoid a lumpy mixture.)
Pour well mixed batter into the home container and bake in a regulated oven of adversity and happiness. Insert sword of truth in center to test for quality.
When sword comes out clean of bad feelings, though and actions, the family is ready for the sweet topping of the Lord's approval.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar and baking powder.
Stir in the margarine or butter to mixture.
Separately add together the milk and egg.
Stir and bring the raisins to a boil for 3 minutes.
Add to first mixture.
Also stir in nuts/seeds.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together in mixing bowl or 4 cup Pyrex measuring cup. Cook 8 minutes on High power.
Add butter and vanilla; stir and cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Add soda; stir quickly and pour out onto Teflon coated cookie sheet.
When cool it will pop right off.
I like to stretch it after it has been poured out and is cool enough to handle.

title: baked kidney beans
directions: Mix all together well.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 2 or more hours.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into ball and garnish with shrimp.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: cinnamon 'n sugar muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 muffin cups. Beat eggs; stir in milk and applesauce.
Add 1/4 cup margarine. Stir in flour, raisins, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder, salt and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Stir until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Fill muffin cups about 2/3 full and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon. Immediately dip top of warm muffins into melted butter, then into cinnamon and sugar mixture.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
(Reserve broth.)
Do not salt chicken because soup is salty.
Line bottom of Pyrex dish with deboned chicken.
Heat cream of chicken soup with broth.
Bring this to boil so it won't be lumpy.
Pour over chicken.
Add can of Veg-All.
Mix melted margarine, buttermilk and flour.
Pour over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until crust is lightly brown.

title: grossman green goop
directions: Make one day in advance.
Put aside small portion of Cool Whip and fruit to decorate later.
Mix Cool Whip and pudding.
Add fruit with 1/2 liquid.
Stir well and add chocolate chips. Refrigerate and decorate prior to serving.

title: ann's chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Line large baking dish with 1/2 bag of Doritos.
Boil, debone and chop chicken.
Do not use the skin.
Combine chicken, cheese and onion and place over Doritos.
Layer the other 1/2 bag of Doritos on chicken mixture.
Combine soups, broth and Ro-Tel in a bowl and pour over chips.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
This recipe will freeze well.

title: grandmom wohlfarth's german turkey filling(20 pound or more turkey)
directions: Put through processor in this order:
Peppers, parsley, apples, celery, liver and onions.
Cut crust from bread.
Cut each loaf in half and break into small pieces.
Need large container.
Knead it all together.
Add marjoram, thyme, salt, pepper, eggs, and sausage meat (break in pieces).
Knead it all together with hands until there is no sign of the bread.
Mix this up the day before.
Cover and store.
Fill front and back of turkey.
Sew skin over.
Don't pack too tightly.
Left overs can be cooked in oven in a covered casserole dish for about one hour at 350°.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour rectangular pan, mix half of the cake mix in with all ingredients except frosting, marshmallows and nuts.
Combine other half of mix and the nuts. Stir until satisfied with texture.
Spread in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or longer, until marshmallows are a golden brown.
Heat frosting until smooth and thin, then drizzle over top.
Best eaten when barely warm from the oven.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Melt butter in a baking dish.
Add oil.
Add chicken.
Bake meat side up for 50 minutes at 350°.
Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Pour out some of the butter and oil from the baking dish and turn the chicken over.
Pour sauce over the chicken. Cover the dish and cook for 20 minutes.

title: family doughnuts
directions: Add sugar to melted shortening.
Beat well.
Add eggs to sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with milk to sugar mixture.
Dough will be very soft.
Chill thoroughly until it can be rolled and cut.
Roll 1/4-inch thick and cut with doughnut cutter.
Fry in deep fat (360° to 370°).
Turn once. Drain on paper towels.
Eat plain or sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: barbecue fish bake(serves 4)
directions: Combine onion, celery flakes, tomato sauce, mustard and brown sugar.
Pour over fish and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut-buttered popcorn
directions: In a large roasting pan, combine popcorn and nuts; keep warm in a 250° oven.
Butter sides of a heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan; combine sugar, honey and corn syrup in pan.
Bring mixture to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil hard for 2 minutes; remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Immediately pour over popcorn mixture, stirring to coat well.
Cool; break into bite-size pieces. Makes 3 quarts.

title: pan de muerto(a mexican bread served on religious holidays)
directions: Bring milk to boiling.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar, salt and shortening.
Add eggs and yeast and beat until mixture is well blended and yeast is dissolved.
Add flour and mix to a moderately stiff dough.
Turn out on a floured board and knead lightly a few minutes until dough is smooth.
Cover with a damp cloth and let rest 30 minutes.
Cut dough into 3 equal-sized pieces and roll each piece into a rope 12-inches long.
(Save out a small portion of dough and form a cross to decorate the top of bread.)

Make a braid of the three ropes, pressing ends together to seal them, then place braid on a lightly greased cookie sheet. Cover with damp cloth and let rise in a warm place until light and double in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.
Brush with melted shortening and bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
If desired, brush baked loaf with melted butter after taking it from oven.
Cool loaf thoroughly before slicing.

title: new potatoes with lemon butter
directions: Peel each potato, leaving a 1 1/2-inch	band around middle. Cook potatoes in Dutch oven in boiling water to cover 20 minutes or until tender; drain. Place in large bowl. Bring butter and next 8 ingredients to a boil in a saucepan over medium-high heat. Remove from heat. Drizzle over potatoes, tossing to coat.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: apple crumble
directions: Mix together 1 1/2 cups flour, oats, brown sugar, cinnamon and melted butter.
Press 1/2 of mixture in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch greased baking dish.
In a large bowl, combine sliced apples with 1 tablespoon flour and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Turn into crust. Sprinkle with remaining half of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pizza pasta casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef and onion until meat is no longer pink: drain. Stir in spaghetti sauce and pasta. Transfer to two greased 13 x 9 baking dishes. Sprinkle with cheese. Arrange pepperoni over the top. Cover and freeze one casserole for up to 3 months. Bake the second one, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 25-30 min. or until heated through.

title: soft chocolate frosting
directions: Pour boiling
milk
over
first four ingredients.
Cook very slowly for 15
minutes,
stirring every 2 or 3 minutes at the end of 15
minutes,
beat
hard
for 1 minute.	Cool for 5 minutes. Add vanilla and salt.
Makes enough for 1 cake.

title: peach bellini
directions: Place puree, Schnapps and lemon juice in a tulip glass.
Fill with champagne.
Serves 1.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil until golden and tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in chili powder and cook 1 minute.
Add all remaining ingredients except butter.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat; simmer uncovered, stirring often, for 30 minutes.
Stir in butter.
If any is left over, put in a covered jar.
Can be stored in the refrigerator for months.

title: strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: Beat softened cream cheese until smooth.
Add strawberries, sugar and vanilla; beat until well mixed.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate several hours.
Garnish with whole strawberries and kiwi slices.

title: oriental rice casserole
directions: Add rice to 2 1/4 cups boiling water; reduce heat.
Cover and cook 40 minutes or until water is absorbed.
Cook onion and celery in butter until soft.
Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: petite "philly" pinwheels
directions: Separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Spread with cream cheese.
Sprinkle with ham and olives, pressing lightly.
Roll up, starting at short end.
Seal edges. Cut each roll into four slices.
Place cut side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 17 minutes or until golden brown.

title: biscuit pizza
directions: Lightly butter cookie sheet.
Press biscuits with buttered fingers to preferred thickness.
Lightly spread spaghetti sauce in center of biscuit.
Leave a ring of dough on outer edge of biscuit.
Sprinkle cheese over sauce.
Place meat on cheese.
Top over with cheese again. Bake in
a 350° oven approximately 15 minutes or until cheese melts and outer edge of dough turns golden brown.
Allow to cool and then enjoy.

title: chimichangas
directions: Soften tortilla shells by spreading a light layer of butter on one side and placing in microwave for 15 seconds.
Brown ground beef.
Heat refried beans.
Place 1 tablespoon of beef, beans and cheese (more if desired) in center of each tortilla (unbuttered side).
Fold each side over like a burrito.
Fry in butter on medium heat until each side is a golden brown.
Add a small amount of butter until each after flipping sides.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Mix cream
cheese,
mayonnaise, salt and chopped shrimp together.
Shape into
ball and wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate until cold.
Remove
from refrigerator 30 minutes before serving and pour
cocktail	sauce
over
top.
Serve with Town House crackers.

title: old bay maryland crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into cakes.
Deep-fry until golden brown, 2 to 3 minutes.
I prefer special or lump crab meat, but claw can be used.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: golden jezebel sauce
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in blender and blend quickly.
Store at least 24 hours.
Pour over cream cheese and serve with crackers.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Blend butter, onions, poppy seed and mustard.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Return to room temperature.
Spread each biscuit with butter mixture after baking by package directions.
Add ham. Cover with foil.
Warm in oven 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
