directions: Dissolve soda in hot water; set aside.
Mix oil, sugar, eggs and pumpkin.
Add water and soda, then sifted ingredients.
Stir well.
Bake in large loaf pan or 3 small loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: baked cheese omelet
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Preheat oven to 375°. Slice Monterey Jack cheese and place on bottom of baking dish.

title: ken's favorite soup
directions: Brown ground meat. Add the rest of the ingredients, except the cabbage, green beans and the macaroni and simmer for 20 minutes. Add the last three items and cook until the vegetables and the macaroni are tender.

title: toffee bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, vanilla and egg yolk.
Stir in flour and salt.
Press in greased rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake until very light brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Crust will be soft.
Immediately place chocolate chips on crust.
Put back in oven until melted.
Spread evenly. Sprinkle with nuts; cut into bars while warm.
Yields 32 (2 x 1 1/2-inch) bars.

title: fig jam
directions: Thoroughly mix figs, gelatin, lemon juice and sugar in
a large saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour quickly into glasses or jars.
Cover at once with 1/8-inch of hot paraffin.
Makes 6 medium glasses.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix according to taco seasoning mix.
Mix nacho chips, lettuce, tomato, cheese and onion.
Add hamburger mixture.
Top each serving with taco sauce and sour cream, if desired.

title: stuffed hamburgers
directions: Make 2 large hamburger patties and flatten them out (so that you have a top and bottom patty).
Place the remaining ingredients on top of one patty, then put the other patty on top. Pinch edges together like a pie.
Fry or grill slowly until the bottom is done.
Turn over gently and brown the other side.

title: crisp peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add beaten eggs and beat thoroughly.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir into cream mixture.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Press with fork (dipped in flour) to make a crisscross design.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Yields about 10 dozen.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Liberally butter a 12 x 10-inch cake pan.
Place sliced jalapenos on bottom.
Mix cheeses together.
Pour on top of peppers; add beaten egg.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until light brown.
Cool in pan; cut in squares.
Serve warm.

title: baked fruit
directions: Arrange pineapple, oranges and prunes in a shallow baking dish.
Pour wine over fruit.
Combine sugar and spices and sprinkle over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter meringue pie
directions: Combine
peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Stir with a fork until
mixture resembles coarse meal.
Spread mixture in cooled pie crust; set aside.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes roughly.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until bubbling.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana muffins
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine butter and sugar, mix together until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs, mixing well after each.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Gradually stir in dry ingredients, just until moistened.
Add nuts, mixing gently.

title: spoon corn bread
directions: Slowly add the cornmeal to the boiling water, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick.
Remove from the heat and add the salt and butter.
Then add the milk and beaten egg yolks.
Fold in the beaten egg whites and place in a greased shallow baking dish (6 1/2 x 10 x 2-inch).
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Shape teaspoon of dough into ball.
Flatten on ungreased cookie sheet, approximately 1/4-inch, with fork.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese pie
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except for pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes in a spring-form pan.

title: lemonade
directions: In a gallon pitcher, empty frozen lemonade concentrate.
Rinse can with water several times.
Add Kool-Aid and sugar.
Fill with water; stir until all is mixed well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix and place in casserole dish.
Mix 1 1/2 cups cracker crumbs and 3 tablespoons melted margarine.
Put on top of casserole last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Form into loaf.
Bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: yummy cider
directions: Combine and simmer until ready to use. Orange slices with cloves may be used to float on top.
This is delicious and is good to use in Wassail bowl at Christmas.

title: donna towners christmas pickles
directions: Drain liquid from pickle strips.
Add ingredients and put in refrigerator.
Turn jar upside down daily to dissolve sugar.
Well seasoned in two weeks.
Keeps in refrigerator for long time.

title: scandanavian fruit soup
directions: Cook the tapioca, sugar, salt and water for about 7 minutes. Remove from stove and add the remaining ingredients.
Top with lime sherbet.

title: jordan's famous cookies
directions: Mix together butter and brown sugar.
Add powdered sugar and peanut butter, then add chocolate chips and marshmallows.
Roll into balls and put on cookie sheets.
Put in freezer for 1 minute. Take out and eat.

title: spaghetti with fresh tomato sauce
directions: Skin the tomatoes by placing them in boiling water for 1 minute only.
Lift tomatoes with a perforated spoon and plunge into a bowl of cold water.
Peel off the skin then drain tomatoes on paper towels.
Chop tomatoes into cubes and mix with herbs, olive oil and seasoning.
Put into a glass bowl and cover and allow to sit for at least 30 minutes.
Cook the spaghetti as directed, then drain. Toss spaghetti with tomatoes and serve immediately.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, apples and oranges in blender.
Mix sugar with ground mixture.
Prepare Jell-O with hot water.
Mix with fruit and refrigerate.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Fry shrimp and onion in oil. Add eggs, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Stir constantly. Add rice and soy sauce; fry for 5 minutes.

title: heavenly fruit dip
directions: Combine sugar, flour, pineapple juice, egg and butter in saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Cool.
Mix with whipped cream and refrigerate.
Serve with sliced fresh fruit.

title: fresh apple dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, margarine, brown sugar and cinnamon until crumbly.
Save 2/3 cup crumbly mixture.
Press remaining crumbly mixture into bottom of ungreased pan.
Put apple slices on crumbly mixture.
Beat sour cream and egg together.
Spread over apples.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbly mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until topping is light golden brown.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Mix in flour, salt, baking powder, cocoa and nuts.
Spread in bottom of greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until bars test done.
Sprinkle marshmallows atop and bake 3 minutes more.
Cool.
Melt together chocolate bits and peanut butter.
Str in cereal and spread this mixture atop cooled bars.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen and kids love them.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Heat griddle and spray with cooking spray.
In bowl, combine flour, oats, baking powder and cinnamon.
In small bowl, mix together milk, egg whites and oil.
Pour liquid ingredients into dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened.
Pour 1/4 cup of batter on top griddle for each pancake.
When tops are covered with bubbles, flip and cook until golden brown.
Serve with fruit sauce. (Recipe follows.)

title: spicy squash casserole(shared by mrs. glenn hill)
directions: Stir into squash mixture and microwave at 70% of power about 10 minutes.
Stir a couple of times during cooking.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups seasoned stuffing mix or croutons.
Microwave at 70% of power for about five minutes.
Top with more stuffing mix or croutons and microwave about 3 or 4 more minutes, uncovered, at full power or until hot and bubbly.

title: good habit tuna melt
directions: Preheat broiler.
In small bowl, combine tuna, celery, red onion, mayonnaise and mustard. Add seasonings and mix well.
Toast bread and spread with tuna mixture. Top with cheese.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, salt and syrup into 1-quart glass pitcher. Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Remove and add peanuts.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Remove and add oleo and vanilla.
Microwave 2 minutes.
Remove and stir in soda; it will get foamy.
Keep stirring until all soda is dissolved.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet.
When cooled, crack into pieces.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, oil and carrots.
Combine cinnamon, salt, soda, flour and baking soda to egg mixture.
Add nuts after mixing well.
Place in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy paella
directions: Remove sausage meat from casings.

In a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot olive or salad oil, cook sausage meat and chicken until brown, stirring sausage frequently to break it up. Spoon off all but 1 tablespoon drippings from skillet.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Heat 2 cups milk in double boiler.
Stir in rest of the items and cook until thick.
Beat egg whites and add to cooked mixture. Pour into pie crust.

title: salisbury steak with mushroom gravy
directions: Combine meat, pepper and salt.
Shape into 3 or 4 plump oval patties.
Pan-fry in hot oil in a skillet or broil 4 to 6 minutes each side.

title: grandma's chocolate pie
directions: Scald milk in top of double boiler, until scum forms (lift off scum).
Beat egg yolks and set aside.
Sift flour, sugar and salt. After milk is scalded, add dry ingredients a little at a time, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat about 5 minutes until slightly thickened.
Very slowly, add egg yolks a little at a time and stir.
Cook about 3 minutes more or until thickened.
Remove from heat and add chocolate mixture and vanilla until smooth. Cool slightly and pour into an 8-inch pie shell.

title: chicken fillets
directions: Dip chicken pieces in egg mixture and then coat with bread crumbs.
Heat in pan of oil for about 3 minutes on each side. Place in a baking pan layered, overlapping and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Heat in oven for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate peanut butter truffles
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt chips with butter.
Stir in cocoa until smooth.
Add sweetened condensed milk and vanilla; cook and stir until thickened and well blended.
Remove from heat; chill until firm enough to handle.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in nuts or cocoa powder.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg and salt.
Shape firmly into loaf (8 x 4). Place in shallow baking pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Blend all but last 2 ingredients and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Then top with corn flakes and melted oleo. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: delicious fruit cobbler
directions: Put butter in baking pan.
Mix together flour, sugar and milk. Pour flour and sugar mixture over butter.
Pour fruit over top of flour mixture.
Cook 20 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: Sprinkle salt over chicken.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Saute onion and garlic in shortening until golden brown.
Add pepper and paprika; stir and add water.
(Don't let paprika burn.)
Cook until tender (45 minutes).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish. Top with Ritz cracker crumbs and more grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raspberry delight salad
directions: Combine gelatin with hot water.
Add ice cream; stir until thoroughly dissolved.
Combine undrained pineapple, nuts and sliced banana.
Add to gelatin mixture.
Pour into a quart mold; chill until firm.

title: corn soup
directions: Cut the tops of kernels of ears of corn.
Back scrape cobs to get all juices.
Cover with water and cook for 5 to 10 minutes. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add milk.
Cook on low heat until milk is hot, not boiling.

title: hot sandwiches
directions: Butter insides of buns with mixture of last four ingredients. Add ham and cheese.
Wrap each in foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand out of oven for 10 minutes before serving.

title: spicy chicken and corn
directions: In skillet, in hot margarine, cook half of the chicken until browned, stirring often.
Remove; set aside.
Repeat with remaining chicken.

title: mom mertens' baked beans
directions: Saute bacon and set aside; saute hamburger and onion in the same pan.
Carefully stir in other ingredients until blended. Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour (or for several hours in a crock-pot on medium heat setting).

title: knox blocks
directions: Stir all gelatine in hot water until dissolved.
Fold in Cool Whip until melted.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan sprayed with Pam.
Chill until set.
Cut into blocks and serve.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until custard is set.

title: peter pan choco surprise
directions: Cream peanut butter, oleo and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Combine flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add gradually until well blended.
Chill dough at least 30 minutes for easier handling. Wrap about 1 level teaspoonful of dough around each chocolate piece, place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove and cool slightly.
Roll in powdered sugar and let cool completely.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs, sugar, milk, vanilla, flour and margarine until well combined.
Fold in coconut.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch pie plates.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Crust forms as pie bakes.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll out dough to a 10 x 14-inch rectangle. Beat egg and add Parmesan cheese. Brush dough with egg/cheese mixture, leaving 1-inch border.
Spread cold cuts in layers on dough. Sprinkle with Italian dressing. Fold short ends in and roll up dough, pinching ends sealed with water.
Place on greased cookie sheet and let rise 1/2 hour.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pita crisps
directions: Separate pitas in half (two round layers).
Mix butter, parsley, oregano, onion and garlic.
Brush butter mixture on rough sides of the pita bread.
On top of each sprinkle 2 tablespoons of cheese.
Preheat the oven to 350°.
Spread pita bread on ungreased cookie sheets and heat 10 to 15 minutes until cheese is melted. Cool pitas slightly and break into bite size pieces.

title: chicken ball
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and shape into a ball; roll in your choice of nuts.

title: no crust quiche
directions: Beat eggs with flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat and bake for 35 to 40 minutes longer.
Cut into small squares and serve hot.
May be frozen and reheated.

title: tangy chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Dip cut up fryer parts in sauce. Place chicken, skin side down, in shallow pan.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt butter in an 11 x 7 1/2-inch pan and tilt to be sure all sides are coated.
Layer the next four ingredients in pan and then pour 1 can Eagle Brand milk over this.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325° until delicately brown.
Loosen from pan; cool and cut into squares.

title: frozen pea salad
directions: Alternate layers of vegetables.
Put sugar, Bac*Os and salad dressing on top.
Cover; let set in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to serve, stir from top to bottom.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Thaw dough in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, tear 1 of the dough loaves into pieces about 1-inch in diameter.
Sprinkle pieces over bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
In medium bowl, blend pudding, sugar, butter, milk and cinnamon.
Spoon over dough pieces and sprinkle nuts on top.
Tear remaining dough loaf into 1-inch pieces and sprinkle over top.
Cover with cloth and place in warm place to rise until doubled (3 to 4 hours).
(Rising takes longer because dough is cold.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven and invert on sheet of foil. Remove pan and cool.
Cut into rolls.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter, peanut butter, sugars and egg together.
Stir flour into mixture.
Add vanilla. Chill.
Roll dough into walnut size balls.
Place balls about 2 inches apart on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake in oven at 375 degrees for about 10-12 minutes or until golden brown, but not hard.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: corn casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients (except muffin mix) in greased casserole dish, then fold in dry corn muffin mix.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour. Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine the 1/3 cup sugar and the cornstarch. Stir in the milk, chocolate and 1 tablespoon butter or margarine. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Reduce heat. Cook and stir 2 minutes more. Gradually stir about 1 cup of mixture into egg yolks. Return mixture to saucepan; bring to boiling. Cook and stir 2 minutes more. Stir in vanilla. Turn the hot pie filling into the baked pie shell. In another saucepan, combine the beaten egg, evaporated milk, the 1/2 cup sugar and 1/4 cup butter or margarine. Cook and stir over medium heat just until the mixture is thickened and bubbly. Stir in the coconut and pecans. Spread the pecan mixture evenly over the chocolate filling. Cool the pie on a wire rack. Chill thoroughly.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cut up and cook cauliflower for 5 minutes.
Drain water.
Add cheese, mayonnaise and soup, stirring well.
If not enough liquid, add another can of soup.
Add onion flakes and seasoning.
Place in a large casserole dish and cover with Pepperidge Farm dressing mix.
Place in oven at 325° for 30 minutes or until top is brown.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Wash tomatoes and slice thin.
Large tomatoes may be quartered before slicing; small ones may be sliced whole.
Mix sugar, salt, spices and flour; add to the tomatoes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in water till tender.
In a separate pot melt butter and add enough flour to thicken.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add milk slowly to make a sauce of desired consistency.
Add 3
bouillon cubes and some of the water from broccoli, careful not to make it too thin.
Add 1 jar of cheese whiz, mixing till cheese melts.
Add broccoli slowly, don't mix too hard or broccoli will break.
Season with salt and pepper if desired.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Grind tomatoes, cabbage, peppers, onions and hot peppers if you want it hot.
Put into a dish pan.
Put salt over and let it stand for about 1 hour or longer.
Squeeze all of the juice out. If you used hot peppers, use rubber gloves!
Pour sugar, vinegar, mustard and celery seed and cook until it changes color, from 20 to 30 minutes.
Put into jars and seal.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook in crock-pot on low 2 to 4 hours.

title: sparkling raspberry spritzer
directions: Place raspberries in container of an electric blender.
Top with cover; process until smooth.
Strain raspberry puree and discard seeds.
Combine raspberry puree and grape juice in a medium pitcher, stirring well.
Stir in club soda just before serving.
Serve immediately.
Yields 1 1/2 quarts.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Clean chicken.
Use blender to make "flour" from stuffing and cheese.
Dip chicken into butter, then roll in "flour".
Place chicken in baking dish so pieces do not touch.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
(Chicken cut into strips will only take about 30 minutes to bake.)

title: cavatappi pompilio
directions: Cook cavatappi according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in a large pot, heat cream and add garlic, onions and mushrooms.
Cook three minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in butter, capicolla ham and basil.
Stir until butter melts.
Add hot pasta, pea pods and sauce, Parmesan, salt and pepper.
Let thicken.
Serves 8.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling into baking dish and spread.
Add crushed pineapple and spread.
Then add cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top then slice margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until cake is brown.

title: praise recipe
directions: Stir the cup of faith with the 2 cups of laughter until it begins to make a bubbly sound.
Mix in the agape love until it begins to ring.
Now pour the entire mixture into a willing heart. This batch of praise is then ready to serve to the King.

title: "best ever" cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and milk.
Add dry ingredients with raisins and coconut.
Fold in beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Add breakfast food carefully so flakes do not break. This is a stiff mixture.
Place spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix as you would for cake.
Add apples and mix in.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: louise's meaty dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake until brown at 400°.

title: barbecued venison
directions: Brown lean meat in 2 tablespoons shortening.
Add chopped onion, vinegar, brown sugar, ketchup, water, Worcestershire sauce, prepared mustard and celery.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer slowly about 1 1/2 hours.

title: mounds cake
directions: Pour cake mix into greased and floured jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. While cake is baking, melt marshmallows, sugar and 1 cup milk. Add coconut to mixture. Spread over warm cake.

title: foolproof delight
directions: In a clear glass bowl, layer broken pieces of angel food cake, scoops of vanilla ice cream and strawberries.
Use at least 2 layers of each.
Pour strawberry juice over top to run down inside of bowl.
Top with Cool Whip.
Can be frozen overnight.

title: turkey salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve 2 tablespoons liquid.
Toss together turkey, pineapple, grapes, celery and nuts.
Mix together pineapple liquid and mayonnaise.
Add to salad and toss to coat completely.
Add season salt to taste.
Chill.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Melt and cool marshmallows.
Add milk and whipped cream.
Pour this mixture over crust of graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter.
Pour can of blueberry pie filling over top of cream mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Put in greased baking dish.
Place cooked and sliced chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, wine and curry powder; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle all over.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve immediately.
(Can be made early and refrigerated, then baked.)

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder and ginger three times.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cream butter, slowly beat in sugar and beat thoroughly.
Add beaten eggs and molasses.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk; beat after each addition.
Chill 2 to 3 hours at least.
Turn on lightly floured board.
Roll 1/8-inch thick, but sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in 375° oven about 12 minutes.

title: j. r.'s lasagna
directions: In large skillet, brown pepperoni and ground beef slowly and drain.
Add garlic, oregano, 1 teaspoon salt, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Simmer uncovered 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cook noodles.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Store in closed container.
To make one batch, mix 6 tablespoons of dry mix to 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add 3/4 cup cold water.
Put in popsicle molds.
Way cool!

title: applesauce crazy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients in an 8-inch square pan.
Add vanilla, oil, water, honey (if used) and applesauce; mix well with fork.
Stir in raisins and nuts (or chopped apple).
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven, using potholders or oven mitt.
Let cool before you cut it.

title: grandma's tea cakes(my favorite cookie when i went to grandma's.)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cream sugar and butter; add the eggs to the mixture.
Mix well, adding flour, 1 cup at a time.
Add milk a little at a time until dough is easy to knead.
Remove a portion of dough the size of a softball, flour sparingly and roll out to thickness of a pencil.
Select your favorite cookie cutter to cut out shapes.
Place cookies 1 inch apart on a greased cookie sheet, decorate and bake at 350° until edges are brown (about 8 to 10 minutes).

title: beef noodle oregano casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown beef with onion and garlic in shortening. Add oregano.
Mix in mushroom soup (undiluted).
Add tomatoes, cooked noodles, Worcestershire sauce, sugar and diced cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir in flour, soda and salt.
Then add nuts.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Bake about 1 hour at 325°.

title: christmas punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add sugar and juices.
Add enough water to make a gallon.
Slice orange into thin pieces and peel off rind.
Drop fruit into punch bowl.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: layered dip
directions: Mix together and put in pan.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Add Cool Whip; mix well. Set in refrigerator. Chill a few minutes.
Layer a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with graham crackers, then spread with pudding, then crackers until all has been used.
Last layer must be graham crackers. Ice like a cake with chocolate icing.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in dressing for 2 hours.
Cook chicken on grill.
Saute onion, peppers and mushrooms.
When chicken is cooked, put sauteed vegies on chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese is all melted.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet, pressing all edges together.
Bake according to directions on package.
Let cool. Mix together softened cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread over crescent rolls.
Cut veggies up into bite size pieces and place on top of cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Refrigerate.
Serves 12 to 15 people.

title: caramel bars
directions: Combine flour, oatmeal, sugar, soda, salt and margarine.
Save a little for topping.
Place the mixture in the bottom of an 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels.
Add milk or cream; sprinkle chips and pecans over mixture in pan. Spread caramel mixture over this; top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine in large bowl:
shortening, sugar, eggs and molasses. Mix well.
Add and blend well flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded spoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°. Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Freeze or bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: from the garden raspberry ribbon pie
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add sugar, berries and lemon juice.
Chill about 1 hour in refrigerator or 10 to 15 minutes in freezer.
Mix cream cheese with confectioners sugar and vanilla. Whip the heavy cream.
Fold into cheese mixture.
Alternate raspberry and cream layers in cooled crust (white-red-white-red) and chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash in a small amount of salted water until tender. Mash squash and add the other ingredients, mixing well.

title: crock-pot casserole
directions: Brown beef; in crock-pot place all vegetables.
Add hamburger and sprinkle in salt and pepper.
Add soup and water.
Cook for 4 to 5 hours on high or 8 to 10 hours on low.

title: butter nut pound cake
directions: Flour and grease "stem" pan (Bundt pan).
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in cold oven for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: eight minute lite n fruity pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; stir 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes and stir until thickened, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Blend in Cool Whip with mixer until smooth.
Fold in fruit.
Chill until mixture mounds.
Spoon into crust.
Chill 2 hours.

title: chicken potpie
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees.
Mix filling ingredients in medium bowl.
Place on pie crust in 9 inch pie plate.
Add filling and top with other crust.
Fold edges under and crimp.
Cut four slits in top to vent.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until pastry is golden and filling is hot.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown meat according to taco package.
Drain off liquid when done.

title: ribbon jello salad
directions: Mix first flavor of jello with 1 1/2 cups boiling water. Divide in half.
Mix one half with 2 to 3 heaping tablespoonfuls of sour cream.
Whip well to blend.
Pour this into an 8-inch clear square Pyrex dish and refrigerate until firm.
Leave plain jello at room temperature.
When firm, pour clear half over sour cream mixture carefully.
Refrigerate until firm.
Repeat this process with each flavor, totaling about 10 layers.
Use flavored jello in any order desired to make an interesting combination. Kids love this colorful jello.

title: four layer delight cake
directions: Mix and spread in bottom of 9 x 13 dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chalupa
directions: Add chilies, garlic, pinto beans and seasonings to pork.
Add water to cover.
Cover pan and cook 6 hours.
Remove pork from bone; shred meat; cook down to desired thickness or add a little water if too dry.
Serve over chips with cheese, onion, lettuce, tomatoes, guacamole or chopped avocado, sour cream, olives and salsa.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour a 13 x 9 cake pan.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips in saucepan over low heat.
Pour this mixture over cereal and mix thoroughly until cereal is well coated.
Put half of cereal mixture into grocery bag with powdered sugar and shake until coated.
Add rest of cereal and shake well.
Store in covered container.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix thoroughly.
To make individual cups of hot chocolate, fill cup almost half full of dry mix; add hot water.

title: orange barley
directions: Brown barley lightly in margarine.
Add onions and garlic. Stir over moderate heat for 5 minutes.
Add spices and mushrooms. Stir to mix.
Add stock, juice and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cover tightly and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until liquid is absorbed and barely tender.
Add liquid if necessary. Barley should be firm and chewy.
Serves 30.

title: poppy seed egg noodles
directions: In large pot, bring water and salt to boil.
Add noodles and cook uncovered until al dente (4 to 8 minutes); drain.
Warm butter and sour cream in pot in which noodles cooked.
Add noodles and poppy seed, toss gently to mix.

title: pumpkin bread(makes 25 servings)
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salad oil, water and pumpkin in order given. Sift together the dry ingredients and mix well in separate bowl. Add dry ingredients to the liquid a little at a time.
Pour into 6 or 7 well greased Number 2 cans.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: marmalade
directions: Dice rhubarb; add a little water.
Cook until done.
While still hot, add Jell-O.
Stir in 1 small can crushed pineapple.

title: sukiyaki (stir-fry beef)
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add meat and brown.
Sprinkle half of sugar over meat while browning.
Add all vegetables and stir about 3 minutes.
Add rest of sugar, soy sauce and sherry and cook a few minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix and pour in mold.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Soak beans all night, then cook until done with salt pork. Then mix in ketchup and syrup.
Put in oven at 350° for 2 to 3 hours or longer until juice is thick.

title: veal oscar
directions: Simmer veal in a bit of water until done.
Heat crabmeat.
Cook asparagus.
Place 1 slice of veal on each of 4 plates.
Add a layer of crabmeat.
Place 4 asparagus spears on top.
Spoon Hollandaise Sauce over top.

title: *rocky road cookies
directions: Mix chips, condensed milk and butter in the top of a double boiler.
Stir until the ingredients are melted and blended. Remove from heat; add peanuts and marshmallows.
Pour into a wax paper lined 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and spread.
Refrigerate until firm.
Remove wax paper; cut into squares.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix together the other ingredients and pour into casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: braided bread
directions: Add 4 to 5 cups water to oil, milk, salt, 1/2 cup sugar and egg.
Combine yeast and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add warm water and let stand 5 minutes.

Add yeast-sugar mixture to egg mixture. Gradually stir in enough flour to make stiff dough, with right consistency, smooth and elastic (comes away from sides of bowl). You may start with mixer, but unless yours is a heavy-duty mixer, you'll need to mix most of it by hand.
Knead 10 minutes on a floured surface.
Add flour as needed to keep dough from sticking. Place dough in large, oiled bowl and turn to coat.
Let dough rise until double.
Punch down and repeat.
Remember to keep dough covered with warm, moist cloth.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook 1/2 pound of lasagna noodles.
Mix 1/2 pound of cottage cheese with 1/2 pound of cottage cheese and 1/2 cup of Parmesan cheese.
Layer noodles, sauce and cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: barbara's chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in 9 x 13 pan. Place cheese slices over chicken. Mix soup and water and spread on top of cheese. Mix stuffing with melted butter and spread over top of soup.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 6 servings; double ingredients to serve twelve.

title: tuna and macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.

title: chicken dijon
directions: In skillet, in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove; pour off fat.
In same skillet, combine soup, water, mustard and pepper; heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet; cover and cook over low heat until chicken is no longer pink.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mom's rolls
directions: Mix first four ingredients and let cool.
Mix next 3 ingredients.
Add yeast mixture to cooled water mixture.
Add eggs, beaten.
Blend in several cups of flour until dough slightly sticky.
Let rise twice.
Shape into rolls.
Bake at 425° until golden, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: crawfish fettucini
directions: Melt Parkay, then saute onions, celery, bell peppers, parsley and garlic (spicy seasonings to your taste).
Stir in flour to thicken sauce, about 1/4 cup.
Add crawfish.
Cook for 15 minutes. Add mushroom soup.
Stir to warm.
Add half and half.
Stir to warm.
Boil 16 ounces of fettucini noodles.
Stir 1/2 pound of each cheese into sauce until melted.
Mix in noodles.
Pour into large greased dish.
Put remaining cheese in chunks on top of noodles.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: icebox cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well.
Bake at 350° in sheet cake pan for 25 minutes.
Cool cake.
Don't overcook.

title: vegetable cheese casserole
directions: Thaw cauliflower and peas enough to break apart.
Drain onions, potatoes, carrots and mushrooms.
Combine all vegetables in 3-quart casserole.
Make a white sauce of milk, butter and flour. Cut Velveeta in cubes and add to white sauce.
Stir until melted. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: flat bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll very thin on a floured surface and cut in squares or diamond shapes.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until brown.
Remove and cool on rack.
Put butter on and enjoy.
Makes about 12 dozen small pieces.
(This dough handles well to roll very thin.)

title: hamburger-vegetable bake
directions: Mix meat, egg, salt, pepper and next four ingredients.
Shape into 12 large balls and brown on all sides in hot oil.
Remove balls to large casserole.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Bring butter and water to boil.
Remove from stove top.
Stir in 1 cup flour to form ball.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time.
Spread on greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. While crust is baking, mix pudding according to package directions.
Reserve 1/2 cup of milk to thin cream cheese.
After cream cheese has been thinned, add to pudding.
Pour mixture over cooled pastry crust.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Right before serving, drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: simple egg drop soup
directions: Mix the can of chicken
broth
with
1 can of water and bring to a slow boil
(you
can make your own chicken broth or use other brands,
however,
I
prefer
Campbell's).
Mix
egg white and sugar; whip in
a
bowl
with
a fork until blended. Slowly start pouring the
egg white into the broth until gone. This should take at least 1 minute.
Add green onion, peas and carrot slice.
Turn off
heat
and
let
stand 5 minutes, then serve.
You can double this recipe or triple.

title: squash dressing
directions: Boil squash 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together except 1/2 package of stuffing mix.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix on top of dressing for casserole.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mock "fry magic"
directions: For golden brown chicken, roll in powdered milk instead of flour.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash the cucumbers.
Put in a pan of cold water; let stand overnight.

title: hamburger cheese dip
directions: Fry and drain hamburger.
Place ingredients in a crock-pot on low.
When cheese melts, it's ready.

title: coconut pineapple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box. Bake on a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch cookie sheet. Bake15 to 25 minutes. Cool.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add other ingredients in order listed.
Use enough flour to make batter spoon easy.
Bake in greased muffin pans at 425°.
Makes approximately 2 dozen rolls. Use as much as you need, then store the rest of the batter in the refrigerator, covered.
Keeps for 2 weeks.

title: yellow cake
directions: Measure into mixing bowl the flour or cake flour, sugar, milk, Crisco, salt and baking powder.
Beat vigorously (2 minutes if by hand).
Add milk, vanilla and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased cake pan.
Bake according to oven directions.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips.
Pile lightly into baking dish.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese and potato chips.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.
Serve warm.

title: luscious broiled fish
directions: Place fish in a shallow broiler pan.
Mix the mayo, cheese, salt and pepper together.
Spread on fish; sprinkle onion on top. cover the pan with aluminum foil (do not let foil touch fish). Place under a preheated broiler for about 7 minutes.
Remove the foil and continue to broil until onion is golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: lobster newburg
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and stir until smooth. Gradually add cream and stir until blended.
Bring mixture slowly to boiling point.
Let simmer gently, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens (about 1 minute).
Add lobster meat and bring to boiling point again.
Beat egg yolks and sherry together.
Add a little hot mixture to egg, then stir egg mixture into lobster sauce.
Add pepper and salt.
Pour into scallop shells or ramekins and brown under broiler.
Serves 6.

title: low calorie mock pork barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients together and simmer over low heat for 15 minutes.

title: breast of chicken on rice(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix soup and milk.
Set aside 1/2 cup of this mixture.
Stir together remaining soup mixture, rice, mushrooms with liquid and 1/2 of the onion soup mix.
Pour into ungreased baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Pour remaining soup mixture over chicken and sprinkle with remaining onion soup mix. Cover.
Bake 1 hour, covered.
Remove cover and bake 15 additional minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in finely chopped walnuts and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: chicken stuffing casserole and pimento mushroom sauce
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package and spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass dish.
Layer thickly with chicken. In saucepan, melt butter, blend in flour.
Add salt and pepper.
Add cool broth and thicken.
Stir in eggs quickly.
Pour over chicken and dressing. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let set for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: mock turtle soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer for 1 to 2 hours.

title: fudge
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt; gradually add milk.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Wait until fudge becomes a little ball.
Take off stove and stir until shiny.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: On a large round or oval plate, layer as follows:

title: broccoli bake
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, covered, and 30 minutes uncovered.

title: aunt millo banana split cake
directions: Mix pudding and smooth onto crust.
Add a layer of pineapple. Slice bananas and layer on pineapple.
Top with Dream Whip. Decorate with whole cherries.
Sprinkle lightly with a little crushed graham cracker crumbs.
Keep in refrigerator.
